title: lazy tacos
directions: Put 1/2 C burger mixture on tortilla, fold over. Fry in oil on low to medium heat on each side until brown. Serve hot with shredded cheese, lettuce and tomato on side.

title: to shell nuts
directions: Place in 8 oz. glass measuring cup or bowl and microwave 4 - 5 minutes, covered.
Nuts will slip right out of shell easily after cracking.

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix together in a large bowl the Raisin Bran, sugar, flour, soda and salt, then stir in the eggs, oil and buttermilk.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes in greased tins.
Makes a big bowl of muffins.
You can bake some a day at a time or bake them all and freeze some for later.

title: chinese chicken
directions: In a paper bag, mix together cornstarch, salt, pepper and sugar.
Shake chicken in bag.

title: baked fruit
directions: Mix together. Place in a deep baking dish, cover with foil. Bake at 350 degrees for one hour.

title: herb bread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
At 1-inch intervals, make diagonal cuts in bread; don't cut through bottom.
In a small bowl, combine remaining ingredients until well blended.
Spread mixture between bread slices.
Wrap bread completely in foil; bake 15 to 20 minutes or until herb butter is melted and bread is hot.
Yields 8 servings.

title: pear salad
directions: Place pear halves on lettuce leaves, cover with grated cheese. Add mayonnaise on top.

title: tea cakes
directions: Mix all together; roll out and cut.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for about 10 to 20 minutes.

title: chocolate cake cookies
directions: Mix with spoon the cake mix, oil and eggs until all moist and mixed together.
Fold in chips, M&M's or nuts.
Drop by teaspoons on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes. Yields 5 dozen.

title: mexican cheese dip
directions: Melt butter and stir in flour in a double boiler.
Add rest of ingredients and cook for 30 minutes.

title: coconut filling for layer cake
directions: Mix milk and sugar; let come to a boil, then add grated coconut.
Let boil.
Add well beaten egg white; let boil.
Put between layers and on top of layers.
Put Seven-Minute Icing on cake.
Sprinkle small amount of grated coconut on top of cake.

title: triple chocolate bundt cake
directions: Combine in a large bowl the first 4 ingredients.
Mix by hand 2 minutes.
Add the chocolate chips. Bake in greased and floured Bundt cake pan at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Turn out while hot. Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: zucchini flats
directions: In a shallow bowl, combine first 8 ingredients.
Beat until smooth.
Cover and refrigerate at least 15 minutes.
Cut zucchini in half crosswise, then lengthwise slices about 1/4-inch thick. Lightly dust each with flour.
Heat oil over medium heat.
Dip each slice in cheese mixture.
Cook a few at a time until golden.

title: pattie's oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine and let stand for 30 minutes to 1 hour the eggs, raisins and vanilla.
Cream together the shortening and sugars. Sift together the flour, salt, soda and cinnamon.
Add dry ingredients to sugar mixture and egg-raisin mixture.
Stir in the oatmeal and pecans.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 350° until lightly browned (approximately 10 to 12 minutes).

title: marinated garden peas
directions: Bring oil, vinegar and sugar to a boil. While boiling, mix together the rest of the ingredients. Add to mixture and store at least overnight. Will keep for 3 to 4 days longer. Serves 6 to 8.

title: broccoli rice
directions: Cook rice and broccoli.
Pour into greased casserole dish. Saute onion, celery and garlic in butter.
Mix into rice and broccoli.
Mix remaining ingredients and stir well.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: banana and pineapple pie
directions: Arrange bananas, sliced, on crust.
Beat cream cheese in large bowl with wire whisk until smooth.
Gradually beat in milk; add pudding mixes.
Beat until well blended.
Spread evenly over banana slices.
Pour pineapple evenly over pudding mixture. Spread Cool Whip over pineapple.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown meat slowly; spoon off excess fat.
Add next 5 ingredients.
Simmer, uncovered, 30 minutes, stirring occasionally. Cook noodles in large amount of boiling salted water until tender; drain and rinse.
Combine remaining ingredients, except Mozzarella. Place half the noodles in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Spread with half the cottage cheese filling; add half the Mozzarella cheese and half of the meat sauce.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 375° for about 30 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting in squares.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: artichoke squares
directions: Saute onions and garlic in oil.
Add artichoke hearts, cracker crumbs, onions, Tabasco sauce, salt and pepper to eggs.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 375°.
Cut into squares.
Serve either hot or cold.

title: chicken noodle casserole
directions: Put noodles in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Lay pieces of chicken on top of dry noodles.
Mix soups and water.
Pour it over chicken.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours or until done.

title: all-bran bread
directions: Put shortening, sugar, salt and all-bran into a bowl of boiling water.
Stir until fat melts.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add well beaten eggs and yeast that has been soaked in lukewarm water until it is dissolved.
Add flour; beat well.
Knead real good the first time and don't knead again after it rises.
Just punch down and place in loaf pans.
When you let it rise the first time, brush the top with butter.
Bake at 420° for 20 minutes until done.
(I bake at 350°.)

title: kirby nuckols' icebox rolls
directions: Mix warm water, 1 teaspoon sugar and yeast; set aside.
Add salt, 1/3 cup sugar and shortening to 1 cup boiling water.
Add 2 cups flour and beat well.
Add yeast mixture, beaten eggs and balance of the flour.
Beat until smooth.
Cover and keep in icebox until ready to use.
Shape in rolls or loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes, reduce heat and bake 10 minutes more for loaf pans.
Grease tops with margarine last 5 minutes.
Makes 36 rolls or 2 loaves.

title: zucchini with sausage
directions: Brown sausage in skillet; add remaining ingredients except cheese; mix well.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until set. Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: margie's lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger; drain oil.
Add spaghetti sauce and tomato sauce.
Set aside.

title: soy "chicken" and dumplings
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large pot (Dutch oven type); bring to a boil, lower heat, cover and simmer until the vegetables are tender, but crisp.
First, separate Chic-ketts into 1 and 1 1/2-inch pieces.
Tear all small pieces off.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Dip chicken into melted butter and roll into dry mixture.
Place in shallow pan and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Do not turn.

title: golden pumpkin muffins
directions: Combine Bisquick mix and sugar.
Stir remaining ingredients into dry ingredients until thoroughly blended.
Fill muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes or golden brown. Makes 1 dozen muffins.

title: taco beef soup
directions: In a large saucepan, cook ground beef and onion until meat is browned.
Drain off excess fat.
Add water, undrained tomatoes, undrained kidney beans, tomato sauce and taco seasoning mix. Simmer covered 15 minutes.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Stir in partly thawed strawberries and bananas.
Spread 1/2 of the mixture in a 7 x 11-inch Pyrex dish.
Spoon sour cream over the mixture, then add remaining Jell-O mixture.
Chill until firm.

title: crab and rice bake
directions: Strain through a sieve and throw solids away.

title: dip
directions: Combine cheese spread and sour cream in saucepan.
Stir over low heat until smooth.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Serve warm with vegetables, chips or breadsticks.

title: weight watchers cabbage-rice casserole
directions: Brown the turkey and green onions.
Put the cabbage and uncooked rice/potatoes in a sprayed 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add the browned turkey and onions to the pan.
Mix tomato sauce, water, bouillon, pepper and Worcestershire and then pour sauce on top. Cover pan with foil.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Serves 4.

title: barbecue whitefish
directions: Cut fish into serving size pieces 1-inch thick.
Mix remaining ingredients well and pour over fish.
Marinate fish for 4 hours. Place fish on grill over low coals.
Baste fish with marinade. Cook until fish flakes when tested, about 15 minutes.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Mix top four ingredients. Bring to a boil. Pinch biscuits in pieces and drop in broth. Reduce heat slightly and cook until dumplings have doubled in size.

title: crab and scallop casserole
directions: Chop bell peppers and celery very fine.
In mixer beat eggs and milk until well blended.
Add everything, except crab and scallops. Grease and spray large glass dish, 9 1/2 x 12-inches.
Use Pam. Pour in the mixture.
Add crab meat and scallops.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until casserole is set, but not real firm.
Let set 10 minutes before serving.
Scallops may be omitted.
Serves 8.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix first four ingredients in saucepan.
When mixture comes to a boil, boil for 4 minutes, stirring often.
Turn off heat and add oats, peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir until smooth.
Drop onto wax paper to make desired size of cookies.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Crumble ingredients and sprinkle over potato mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes uncovered.
The time depends upon the depth of your dish.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Mix and pat into an 11 x 13-inch pan the flour, oleo and nuts. Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese and sugar and spread over cooled, baked crust.
Heap fruits on top of crust.
(Canned fruits must be well drained.)
Take 1/2 cup apricot preserves and heat just enough to make syrupy.
Dribble on top as a glaze.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup nuts on top and chill.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl, except pie crusts.
Pour into pie crusts.
Chill overnight.

title: southwest chicken
directions: Heat the oven to 350°.
Place the chicken breast and pineapple juice in the roasting bag.
Bake in the oven for 1 hour.
Take the cooked chicken breasts out of the roasting bag and place on a cookie sheet.
Put 1 slice of Provolone cheese on each chicken breast and sprinkle Cheddar cheese on each one.
Place them in oven long enough for the cheese to melt.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Sift flour, salt, soda and baking powder.
Blend shortening, sugar, eggs, milk and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients to oats, nuts and chips.
Add to rest of mixture.
Bake at 370°.

title: texas cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Bring margarine, water and cocoa to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Add flour, sugar, salt and soda.
Add eggs and sour cream.
Bake 25 minutes in an 11 x 14-inch pan.

title: pittsburgh casserole
directions: Melt butter in large skillet.
Saut sliced onions 4 to 5 minutes.
Add kielbasa and brown (3 to 4 minutes on each side). Add beer; reduce heat and simmer for 25 minutes, uncovered.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: cranberry punch
directions: Mix well.
If not serving immediately, don't add ginger ale and sherbet.
Add them when ready to serve.
Makes 3 1/2 quarts.

title: bean burgers
directions: Shape ground beef into 8 thin patties about 3 1/2 inches in diameter.
Brown patties in 10-inch skillet, cooking to desired doneness.
Drain.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Top each of 4 patties with 1 cheese slice; cover with remaining patties.

title: sausage balls
directions: Melt cheese slightly. Mix in Bisquick with a fork. Add sausage. Form small balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 250° for 30 minutes or until slightly brown.

title: manicotti
directions: Mix hamburger, refried beans, onion, cumin, oregano, garlic powder and pepper together.
Stuff manicotti noodles with mixture and place in baking dish.
Mix salsa, tomato sauce and water together.
Pour over stuffed manicotti noodles.

title: stay-a-bed stew
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large casserole dish (2 to 3 quart dish) and cover tightly.
Put casserole in 275° oven.
Let cook for 5 hours, without checking.
This can be cooked in a crock-pot.
Yield:
5 to 6 servings.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Brown ground beef. Mix all ingredients and cook on low for approximately 1 hour.

title: mothers candied sweet potatoes
directions: Peel and cut potatoes into medium size cubes; place in dish. Mix sugar, butter, vanilla and flour together and pour over potatoes. Bake 350° for 30 to 40 minutes until tender.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown and drain meat.
Add taco mix as per directions.
Layer on large tray:
Fritos, meat mixture, beans (drained and rinsed), lettuce, tomatoes, olives and top with cheese.

title: pecan bars
directions: Bake in long pan at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cut in squares while warm.

title: fat free soup
directions: Prepare and cut up vegetables suitable for soup.
Using large pot, cover vegetables with water.
Bring to boil.
Cover; reduce heat, simmering until vegetables are soft.
Try salt, pepper, garlic or bouillon as added flavoring.

title: layers of veggies
directions: Saute onion, green pepper and mushrooms.

Place sliced potatoes in the bottom of a 2 1/2-quart nonstick baking dish. Alternate layers of carrot, rice, onion mixture and zucchini. Stir seasonings into mashed tomatoes and pour over vegetables; cover.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours and serve.
Serves 8.

title: frozen cranberry delight
directions: Mash cranberry sauce and lemon juice with fork and spread in pan 1 1/2 inches thick.
Whip the heavy cream.
Fold in sugar, mayonnaise and nuts.
Spread mixture on top of cranberry sauce. Freeze overnight if possible.
Cut into 2-inch squares when ready to serve.

title: ham loaf
directions: Have your butcher grind the meat or use your food processor. Mix all ingredients well except for bacon.
Shape in loaf. Place in shallow pan. Cover with bacon strips. Bake, uncovered, 1 3/4 to 2 hours at 375°.
During the last 3/4 hour, baste with the following sauce every 15 minutes.

title: manicotti
directions: Brown ground chuck and drain.
Add other ingredients together. Cook slow for 1 hour, all except cheese.
Boil noodles for 20 minutes and drain.
Stuff meat sauce inside of noodles.
Place in large casserole dish and sprinkle with cheeses over each layer until gone.
Cook for 15 minutes at 350°.
Ready to eat.

title: white buttermilk cake
directions: Cream together shortening, sugar and 2/3 cup buttermilk.
Add unbeaten egg whites.
Beat well, but not too dry (may look curdled).
Add remaining ingredients and beat well.
Bake in greased and floured 11 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until tester comes out clean.

title: italian bread treat
directions: Chop tomatoes by hand into very small chunks.
Combine oil, vinegar and herbs.
Add tomatoes and marinate in refrigerator at least 1 hour.
Arrange bread slices on cookie sheet and add tomatoes.
Top with cheese and broil until cheese melts.
Good appetizer.

title: viennese brownies
directions: Combine softened cream cheese, sugar, egg and almond extract.

title: speedy burrito
directions: In a saucepan heat oil on high heat.
Add garlic, seasoning, red chili pepper, beans and 1/2 c. Griffin's Old Santa Fe Picante Sauce. Mix well and cook for about 5 minutes.
Remove from heat. Take a tortilla, in the middle place beans mixture, sprinkle with vegetables and cheese.
Roll it up and sprinkle some cheese on top and microwave at 45 seconds or until the cheese is melted.
Do the same with rest.
You can choose your own topping if you like or make addition to the above topping.
Enjoy it with Griffin's Old Santa Fe Picante Sauce.

title: potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes until tender.
Cool.
Mix all other ingredients together and beat until light and fluffy.
Pour over potatoes and stir until potatoes are coated.
May need more salt.
You may garnish with sliced boiled eggs.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Cook the noodles in salted water until tender; drain.
In another saucepan, combine other ingredients.
Cook until cheese is melted and ingredients are well blended.
Pour into greased with butter casserole dish and top with crushed potato chips.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.

title: red velvet cake icing
directions: Cook flour and milk until very thick.
Cool. Cream butter, sugar and vanilla. Add to flour mixture and beat until it is like whipped cream.
Ready to frost cake.

title: ginger cream cookies
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar; beat in egg.
Stir in molasses.
Sift dry ingredients; add alternately with water.
Drop from teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350°.
Frost while warm.

title: sausage and cheese dip
directions: Brown sausage in a skillet. Drain the excess fat.
Melt the cheese in a microwavable dish.
Add a can of Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Mix in with the sausage.
Serve with Fritos or Tostitos chips.
(It is better served warm.)

title: batter rolls
directions: Pour water into a large mixing bowl, add yeast.
Let stand a few minutes, then stir to dissolve.
Add half the flour, sugar, salt, soft shortening and egg.
Beat with mixer on medium speed 1 1/2 to 2 minutes (or beat by hand with a wooden spoon).
Add rest of flour and stir in by hand until the flour disappears.
Scrape down batter from sides of bowl.
Cover bowl with waxed paper and let rise in warm place until doubled, about 30 minutes.

title: apple cobbler
directions: Melt butter
in
a
13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Heat oven to 350°. Stir raisins, cinnamon and sugar into apples. Heat until hot.
Mix together
1 cup sugar, flour and milk.
Pour batter over melted butter.
Pour
apples
over all. Bake 45 minutes. Serve warm.

title: oriental ramen salad
directions: Mix cabbage, onions, almonds and sunflower seeds in a large bowl.
Break the dry Ramen noodles on top of the cabbage mixture. (Save the packages of dry seasoning for the dressing.)

title: quick strawberry pie
directions: Place jello, sugar, cornstarch, food coloring and boiling water in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil and boil for approximately 3 minutes until mixture is clear.
Cool slightly.
Arrange fresh cut or whole strawberries in a baked pie shell.
Pour glaze over berries.
Chill until firm.
Top with whipped cream.

title: cheese ball
directions: Cut up stuffed olives; mix with other ingredients.
Roll in pecans.
Chill.

title: fun cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt; set aside.
Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Blend in flour mixture; slowly stir in M&M's and nuts.
Drop heaping teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake for 8 to 11 minutes.
Cool 1 minute; place on wire cooling rack.
Makes 5 dozen 2-inch cookies.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars; add eggs and continue beating until fluffy.
Add flour, soda, salt, baking powder and vanilla. Mix well until blended.
Add rolled oatmeal and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Bake until done (11 to 13 minutes) at 350°.

title: garden vegetable soup
directions: Cook bacon and reserve 3 tablespoons grease to saute green pepper, onion and mushrooms until limp.
Set aside.
In pot, mix broth, both cans of soup, broccoli, cauliflower and corn.
Heat until hot, then add sauteed vegetables.
Add pepper and simmer for 5 minutes.
Add half and half, then cook until hot.

title: chocolate rice krispies
directions: Cook sugar and syrup over medium heat until bubbles.
Remove from heat. Stir in peanut butter; mix well. Add Rice Krispies. Press in buttered 13 x 9-inch pan. Melt chips and pour over top.

title: impossible buttermilk pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease pan.
Beat all ingredients until smooth.
Bake approximately 30 minutes until knife comes out clean.
Cool 5 minutes.

title: creamed limas and beef
directions: Drain cooked beans.
Shred dry beef; cook in butter 5 minutes. Blend in flour; stir in milk and cook until thickened.
Add beans, onions, salt and pepper to taste.
Put in shallow baking dish.
Top with crumbs; sprinkle with paprika.
Bake for 20 minutes at 375°.
Serves 6.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Toast sesame seed and almonds in 350° oven until light brown. Toss together cabbage, onion, noodles, seed and almonds.
Mix together in separate bowl the sugar, vinegar, oil, salt and chicken flavoring packet.
Pour over noodle and cabbage mixture and toss.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: In a 3-quart pan, bring water to a boil; add broccoli and onion. Boil 10 to 12 minutes. Add seasoning and cheese.
Stir until cheese melts.
Add milk, cream and butter.
Heat to boiling. Add 1/2 cup cold water to flour, stirring until smooth. Slowly add to mixture, stirring rapidly. Cook and stir until thick.
Add bouillon cubes.

title: real pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar well.
Add unbeaten eggs, one at a time, alternately
with
flour.
Add
flavoring.
Place in a cold oven and set
temperature
at
and cook for 2 hours without peeping.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°. Mix all ingredients and pour into pie crust. Place second crust on top and vent. Bake 40 minutes. Let stand for 10 minutes.

title: bread pudding
directions: Pour into greased baking dish; bake at 350° for about 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: marinated carrot salad
directions: In a saucepan, cook carrots in salted water until tender; drain.
Meanwhile, to make marinade, combine soup, sugar, vinegar, salad oil, mustard and Worcestershire sauce.
In a shallow dish, arrange alternate layers of onion, pepper and carrots.
Pour marinade over all; refrigerate 6 hours or more.
Makes about 6 cups.

title: tea sandwiches
directions: Dissolve 1 envelope of gelatin in 1/4 cup of cold water.
Put in dish and set in hot water until melted.
Grate carrots, celery, cucumbers, onion and green pepper.
Drain and mix with gelatin. Add mayonnaise, lemon juice and salt to taste.
Let stand 2 or 3 hours.
Spread a thin layer between 2 slices of bread.
Cut off crusts and cut in 4 pieces.

title: yeast biscuits
directions: Mix together yeast, water and sugar. When yeast dissolves, add cooking oil,
buttermilk and soda.
Mix well. Add flour.
Put in a covered bowl.
Let rise 3 or 4 hours or overnight.
Stir slightly and dip out on floured board.
Work with hands to form biscuits. Bake at 350° about 30 minutes.

title: williamsburg hot spiced punch
directions: Simmer cider, cinnamon sticks and lemon juice for 15 minutes. Tie nutmeg and cloves in small cheesecloth bag and put into simmering cider long enough to give it desired taste.

title: chili cheese ball
directions: With the blender or electric mixer combine the cheeses and add the spices (not the chili powder).
Shape in 2 logs.
On waxed paper, sprinkle the chili powder; roll logs until coated.
Wrap in Saran and refrigerate at least 3 days.
Serve with crackers.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and butter in 2-quart saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until melted, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Gradually beat in beaten eggs.
Add pecans and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Pour in 9-inch pie shell and bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Garnish with pecan halves before baking.

title: mickey mouse pancakes
directions: Pour three silver dollar size circles of batter onto griddle so they merge into the mouse head-and-ears symbol.
Cook, flip and finish.
Transfer to plate.
Make eyes, nose and smile with cinnamon candy.
Let kids pour syrup.
Serve with milk and orange slices.

title: chicken swiss(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Place chicken in a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Arrange Swiss cheese slices over chicken, overlapping as needed.
In a bowl, mix soup and wine/juice.
Spread on top of cheese.
Crush croutons and sprinkle on top of soup/wine.
Drizzle melted butter over all. Bake in a 350° oven for 45 to 60 minutes.
Do not overburn croutons.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Cream shortening, sugar, molasses and egg until creamy.
Add dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Chill.
Roll in sugar and put on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.

title: mustard greens
directions: Wash and clean mustard very thoroughly, changing water 2 or 3 times.
Strip large middle stem from each leaf of mustard by folding together and pulling out.

title: broccoli-cheese-rice casserole
directions: Brown onion in
butter.
Add
cream of chicken soup and milk. Stir until well
blended.
Add
it to broccoli and rice in casserole dish
and
stir
well.
Sprinkle Velveeta on top. Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: 60 minute rolls
directions: Add yeast, shortening and sugar to milk.
Stir well.
Add egg, salt and flour.
Let rise 15 minutes.
Work down.
Let rise 15 minutes.
Shape into rolls.
Place on greased pan.
Let rise 15 minutes.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until done.
Makes 30 rolls.

title: quick apple crisp
directions: Peel, core and slice apples.
Place in lightly buttered pan. Sprinkle sugar mixture and dry cake mix over apples.
Drizzle melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: seasoned pretzels
directions: Heat oven to 250°.
Place pretzels in a large shallow baking pan.
Combine oleo, dip mix, Worcestershire and salt.
Pour over pretzels and stir well.
Bake 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes. Pour on waxed paper to cool.
Store in airtight container.

title: pie filling fruit cake
directions: Cook cake according to directions on box (make 3 layers).
Mix pie filling or strawberries with the glaze.
Put this between the cake layers.

title: heart healthy vegetable lasagna
directions: Cook lasagna noodles according to directions (slightly firm). Cool in cold water, then drain.

title: raspberry pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except dressing.
Grease and line baking dish with 1/3 dry dressing.
Pour in mixture.
Cover with rest of dressing.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: taco dip
directions: Brown the ground beef.
Then add taco mix.
Follow instructions on package; let cool.

title: banana split cake(low calorie)
directions: *Do not add sugar; can use frozen strawberries.

title: potato dumplings
directions: Mix the ingredients and drop by teaspoon in hot broth of any kind.
Cook, covered, 15 to 20 minutes.

title: cracker salad
directions: Chill 4 to 5 hours before serving.

title: curried okra
directions: Saute onion and celery in the bacon grease. Add the okra and cook about 5 minutes.
Add the remaining ingredients and cook about 30 minutes.

title: mexican puff ol
directions: In bottom of greased 9-inch pie plate, place olives, cheese, chiles and onions. Combine eggs, biscuit mix, milk and seasonings in blender; blend 15 seconds on high. Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes. Serve with salsa or picante sauce, if desired.

title: coconut sour cream layer cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions, making two 8-inch layers.
Cool.
Split layers.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Sift together dry ingredients and cut in shortening.
Add yeast to buttermilk and mix with dry ingredients.
Turn out onto a floured surface.
Knead and roll out, cut into biscuits.
Bake at 375° until brown.

title: brown rice
directions: Stir together in casserole dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; add balance of ingredients, except cheese, and simmer slowly for 2 to 3 hours.
Boil and drain lasagna noodles.
Layer in baking pan a layer of noodles, layer of meat sauce and layer of cheese.
Repeat layers until you end up with cheese on top.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: zucchini canoes
directions: Cook bacon in skillet, drain on paper and crumble.
Set aside. Keep fat.
Hollow out zucchini in canoe shapes.
Keep flesh. Blanch "canoes" in water 2 minutes.
Drain and set aside.
Chop reserved flesh and saute in bacon fat until crisp-tender.
Combine with bacon and all remaining ingredients except breadcrumbs. Sprinkle teaspoon of crumbs in each canoe, add mixture.
Place in shallow pan and add 1 inch hot water.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until knife inserted into zucchini comes out clean.

title: dishpan cookies
directions: Mix all together; shape into small balls.
Put on cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 325°.

title: caramel icing
directions: Stir together and cook on low heat until it bubbles and threads.
Frost cake and sprinkle coconut on top.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Cream sugar and melted butter. Add eggs.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake 40 to 45 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: macaroni and cheese bake
directions: Cut cheese into 1/2-inch cubes.
Melt butter in a small saucepan; blend in flour and seasonings.
Cook over low heat, stirring, until mixture is smooth and bubbly, but do not allow to brown.
Remove from heat and stir in milk.
Add one cupful of the cubed cheese and stir until melted.
Cook macaroni following directions on package and drain.
Butter an 11 1/2 x 7 1/2 x
1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Place half the macaroni in the bottom of the dish.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup cubed cheese over macaroni.
Place the remaining macaroni next and top with remaining.
Bake at 350° for 32 to 40 minutes.
Serve hot.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: quick cowboy stew
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Add remaining ingredients to a large pan and add ground beef and simmer for 10 minutes.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Combine cucumbers and onions in large bowl.
Layer with salt; cover with ice cubes.
Let stand 1 1/2 hours.
Drain and rinse. Place remaining ingredients in a kettle and bring to a boil.
Add cucumbers and onions.
Return to a boil.
Pack hot into hot jars to within 1/4-inch of top.
Remove any air bubbles.
Adjust caps. Process 15 minutes in hot water bath.
Yields 6 pints.

title: wassail
directions: Heat to a boil and simmer for 1 hour; serve.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine soups, chicken broth and tomatoes and set aside. Grease 3 qt. casserole dish.
Layer half of tortilla pieces half of chicken, half of onion and half of cheese in the casserole. Pour half of chicken broth mixture over layers.
Repeat layers of tortillas, chicken and onion; then pour remaining chicken broth mixture over top.
Add remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° F. for 45 to 60 minutes.
This casserole can be frozen and reheated.
Serves 8.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Cook macaroni, drain; cut corned beef into chunks.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into 2 quart dish.
Cube 4 slices of bread; melt 1 stick margarine and pour over cubed bread.
Place buttered crumbs over corned beef mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: energy pickups(quick and easy)
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll into balls.
Roll in coconut or graham cracker crumbs.
Place on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Chill 20 minutes.

title: dee's sally lunn
directions: Place lukewarm skim milk and yeast in mixing bowl.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Stir.
Add canola oil, honey, salt and egg whites.
Beat with electric mixer.
Gradually add flour.
If batter is thin, add more flour.
Leave batter in bowl and let double in size.
Pour into buttered 10-inch angel food cake pan.
Let stand about 1 hour or until batter has risen to about 1 inch from top of pan.
Bake about 50 minutes in 350° oven or until bread is golden brown.

title: christmas chocolate pizza
directions: Melt chocolate	chips,	almond bark and marshmallows in large bowl in
microwave	or
over
hot
water.
Stir
in Rice Krispies and
nuts.	Spread	in pizza pan.
Sprinkle M&M's and coconut over top.
Melt	remaining 2 ounces almond bark with 1 teaspoon oil and drizzle
over
the M&M's and coconut.
It is pretty and good!

title: pork chops with rice
directions: Brown chops.
Spread rice in bottom of pan.
Sprinkle soup mix over top.
Save a little for top of chops.
Also spread mushrooms and pimento on top of rice.
Add 3 cups liquid, hot water and juice from mushrooms.
Place chops on top of rice.
Cover with foil.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Remove foil.
Bake 10 minutes longer.

title: apple pie
directions: Mix and blend first 5 ingredients together until creamy.
Pour into greased dish (not too shallow).
Layer apple pie filling on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 400°.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash, onions and carrots in just
a little water until tender, then drain thoroughly.
Add
remaining
ingredients, except
stuffing mix and margarine and
mix
well.
Mix stuffing mix and margarine and place half in
a
large shallow casserole. Add squash mixture and top
with
remaining stuffing.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: granny's cookies
directions: Cream together sugar and butter or shortening.
Add eggs; beat hard.
Add in soda; cut in a small amount of hot water.
It will foam.
Add flour; mix in a bowl.
If dough is real soft, mix a little more flour.
Roll out and cut.
Place on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: 4-h peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream the Crisco until soft.
Add the 2 sugars gradually to the Crisco until smooth.
Have the brown sugar packed down.
Add the whole egg all at once.
Add the peanut butter.
In a separate bowl, sift the flour and soda together, then add to first mixture. Roll into about 1-inch balls.
Place on unoiled baking sheet. Flatten with a fork both ways on cookie dough and bake in a 425° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 30 small cookies.

title: lazy day cobbler
directions: Melt butter in deep baking dish in oven.
Blend together 1 cup sugar, flour and milk.
Pour over butter.
Do not stir.
Empty can of cherries over top of batter.
If using pie filling, do not use sugar.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lemon pudding cake
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat egg yolks until thick.
Blend in lemon juice, peel and butter or margarine.
Combine sugar, flour and salt; add alternately with milk.
Beat egg whites until stiff; fold into batter.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart baking dish; set in a pan of hot water.
Bake at 350° about 45 minutes or until lightly browned.
Serve warm, topped with Cool Whip or whipped cream.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown meat; add onions and bell pepper.
Boil lasagne strips and drain.
Drain meat and turn off.
Add tomato sauce and dry ingredients.
Mix cream cheese, sour cream and cottage cheese together in separate bowl.
Layer dish with 3 lasagne strips. Spoon 1/2 meat mixture over them.
Spread cheese mixture over meat mixture.
Lay 3 more strips over cheese mixture.
Spread rest of meat mixture.
Spread Parmesan cheese over top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli; drain good and season with salt and pepper. Combine all ingredients in large bowl, mixing well.
Pour into a casserole dish.
Bake for 45 minutes to an hour at 350°.

title: recipe for success
directions: Be careful of your selection.
Do not choose too young and take only such as have been raised in a good moral atmosphere. Some insist on keeping them in a pickle, while others keep them in hot water.
This only makes them sour, hard and sometimes bitter. Even poor varieties may be made sweet, tender and good by garnishing them with patience.
Wrap them in a mantle of charity, keep warm with a steady fire of devotion and serve with peaches and cream.

title: chess squares
directions: Heat the first 2 ingredients on low heat.
Add others in order.
Pour into two 8-inch square pans greased with butter and floured.
Bake for 30 or 40 minutes at 300°.
Cool just a little; cut into squares.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: jello pie with cookie crust
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Grease pie pan.
Pat mixture into pan and bake for 15 minutes at 375°. Cool.

title: breakfast power drink
directions: Mix in blender.
Blend 2 minutes or until ice is chopped.

title: potato leek soup
directions: Cut bacon crosswise into thin slices. In a large saucepan over medium heat, cook bacon, stirring occasionally until crisp, 5 minutes. Add potatoes and leeks and cook until leeks are wilted, stirring occasionally, 5 minutes. Add water and bring to a boil over medium high heat. Reduce heat to medium low and simmer until potatoes are tender, 15-20 minutes. Stir in 1 cup milk, mustard, salt and pepper. Working in batches, puree soup in food processor until smooth, about 20 seconds per batch. Return soup to sauce pan and stir in remaining milk. In a small bowl whisk together the egg yolk and cream, then stir into soup and simmer until hot. Garnish each serving with chopped parsley, and black pepper if desired. Makes 6 servings.

title: jiffy stew
directions: Brown ground beef in a large skillet (remove excess fat). Add following ingredients: onion, juice, potatoes, carrots and spices and simmer briefly.

title: more please hot dish
directions: Brown ground beef. Add onions and celery. Cook until browned. Add remaining ingredients, except noodles. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes, stirring once or twice while baking. Sprinkle noodles over top. Bake 10 minutes longer. Serves 8 to 10.

title: orange salad
directions: Sprinkle dry jello over cottage cheese and toss with all ingredients except Cool Whip. Fold in Cool Whip last.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all together and put in casserole.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cream the sugar and shortening, then add eggs, one at a time, beating
all
the time.
Place salt and soda in buttermilk.
Add lemon extract to sugar, shortening and egg mixture, then
add flour and buttermilk a little at a time, ending with flour. Grease tube pan and dust with flour.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Remove from oven and cool in upside-down pan.

title: banana pudding
directions: Combine pudding mix and milk; beat until pudding is thickened. Add sour cream and Cool Whip (reserving enough for topping). Layer pudding, wafers and bananas.
Top with remaining Cool Whip.

title: sum roll cookies
directions: Combine brown sugar and eggs.
Beat well.
In another bowl, combine flour, baking powder and baking soda.
Add dry mixture to egg mixture.
Stir in pecans and vanilla.
Mix well and pour onto a greased 11 x 15 x 1-inch cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes.
Cut into bars.

title: mark's savory sausage
directions: *Use 4 to 5 ounces barbecue sauce per pound of sausage.

title: oatmeal fruit-nut drop cookies
directions: Mix together the first 4 ingredients.
Sift together the flour, soda, baking powder, salt and cinnamon and stir into the buttermilk mixture.
Stir in the remaining ingredients.
Drop rounded teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake in 400° oven for 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes about 5 1/2 to 6 dozen cookies.

title: carrot soup
directions: Saute onion in oleo.
Add celery, chicken broth and sliced carrots.
Cook until carrots are tender.
Put all in blender. Blend until pureed.
Add milk and nutmeg.
Heat and serve.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Spread peanut butter on a Ritz; top with another and repeat until all Ritz are used.
Melt bark in saucepan.
Dip sandwiches in bark, coating completely.
Place on wax paper until set.
Makes 50.

title: corn fritters
directions: Sift flour with baking powder and salt. Beat eggs.
Add milk and salad oil. Stir in flour mixture, then corn. Drop by tablespoons into fat heated to 365°.
Fry 3 to 5 minutes, turning once.
Makes 5 or 6 servings.

title: butterscotch bars
directions: Melt butter in 2 quart saucepan.
Remove from heat and stir in brown sugar.
Add eggs, then beat well and stir in vanilla.
Add dry ingredients, coconut and nuts to brown sugar mixture.
Mix well.
Spread in greased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cut in bars while warm.
Remove from pan when almost cool.
Makes 3 dozen bars.

title: lorraine's chili quiche
directions: Melt butter in pan, approximately 11 x 15 x 2-inch.
Add flour and baking powder to beaten eggs and beat to blend.
Add chilies and cottage cheese to egg mix.
Pour over melted butter. Sprinkle with salt and grated cheese.
Bake 15 minutes at 400° and then reduce temperature to 350° and bake 40 minutes.
Cut into small squares and serve hot.
May be made ahead and frozen.

title: primavera with a twist
directions: Cook pasta according to directions and drain. Cook asparagus according to directions and drain.
In 2 1/2-quart casserole, combine pasta, asparagus, pimento and meat.
In medium saucepan, melt oleo. Stir in flour and cook 1 minute.
Gradually add milk, broth and dill weed.
Stir until mixture boils and thickens. Add to casserole.
Mix well. Cover and bake in preheated oven at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Can be microwaved on High for 8 to 10 minutes, stirring after 4 minutes.
Makes about 4 servings.

title: cool pink fruit dip
directions: Put cream cheese in small bowl.
Add gelatin and milk to cream cheese.
Beat with wire whisk until well blended and smooth.
Put mixture into serving bowl.
Put bowl into refrigerator to chill until serving time.
Take bowl out of refrigerator.
Let dip stand at room temperature to soften slightly (about 15 minutes).
Place bowl on large plate.
Arrange dipping size pieces of fruit on plate around serving bowl.
Makes about 1 1/2 cups of dip.

title: peanut butter frosting
directions: Beat until smooth and spread on favorite cake.

title: aunt charlotte's jello salad
directions: Use a jello mold.
Mix strawberry jello with 1 cup boiling water.
Add 1 cup strawberry juice (if not enough juice, add water to measure 1 cup).
Add in 2 tablespoons lemon juice.
Pour into mold.
Add strawberries.
Refrigerate until set.
Mix cream cheese, mayo, milk and nuts until spreadable.
Spread over strawberry jello.
Set in refrigerator.
Mix lemon jello with 1 cup boiling water.
Add 1 cup peach juice (if not enough juice, add water to measure 1 cup).
Add in 2 tablespoons lemon juice. Pour over nut mixture.
Add peaches.
Refrigerate until set.

title: eddie's famous cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients and roll into small balls; press flat with fork.
Bake at 350° for 5 to 10 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Blend until smooth first 5 ingredients.
Gradually add the flour, soda and salt.
Fold in raisins and chips.
Batter will be very stiff.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Yields 6 dozen (approximately).

title: fig preserves
directions: Wash figs in warm soda water and rinse well.
Cut ends off or peel, if preferred.
Put water and sugar on to boil about 10 minutes.
Put figs in and cook until syrupy, about 2 hours.
Put in jars and seal.

title: banana blitz(diabetic recipe)
directions: Pour boiling water into blender.
Add gelatin and blend at low speed until completely dissolved, about 30 seconds.
Add ice cubes and stir until ice is partially melted.
Blend for 30 seconds. Mixture should be cold.
Add milk and banana slices; blend until smooth.
Spoon into dessert dishes.
Chill until set (at least 30 minutes).
One-half cup equals 1/2 fruit (also low in sodium and cholesterol).

title: easy filled cookies
directions: Heat oven to 400°. Mix well the shortening, sugar and eggs. Stir in water and vanilla.
Sift together and stir in flour, salt, baking soda and cinnamon.
Drop with teaspoon onto ungreased baking sheet.
Place 1/2 teaspoon of date filling on dough and cover with 1/2 teaspoon of dough.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.

title: old-fashioned sour cream cookies
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Mix shortening, sugar, egg and vanilla thoroughly.
Measure flour; blend dry ingredients.
Add to sugar mixture alternately with sour cream.
Divide dough; roll out to 1/4 inch thick on well-floured board.
Cut with 2-inch cutter. Place on greased baking sheet.
Sprinkle with sugar or, if frosted later, do not use sugar.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes 4 to 5 dozen.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown meat and add onion to brown.
Add everything else and bring to boil.
Lower heat and cook for 2 hours.
Serve over noodles.

title: cream cheese cookies
directions: Cream together butter and shortening.
Add sugar and cream cheese; mix well.
Add salt and vanilla; beat well and add flour. Divide dough into rolls and wrap in wax paper.
Chill and slice thin.
Bake at 325° for about 10 minutes or until light brown. Remove from pan.
Cookies become crisp as they cool.
Top with a pecan half or cinnamon sugar, if desired, before baking.
You may also drizzle chocolate over them after baking.

title: creamy vegetables over linguini
directions: Melt butter in very large skillet.
Add broccoli flowerets, carrot slices or peels, chopped peppers and onions.
Saute until vegetables are softer, but not fully cooked.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken breasts until well done; bone and dice.
Mix 1 cup of chicken broth with chicken and celery soups.
Prepare stuffing mix as directed on package.
Starting with chicken, layer in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish the chicken, stuffing and soup. Dribble butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Melt cheese and oleo, then stir in cocoa.
Beat in powdered sugar.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Pour in buttered pan.

title: buttery cinnamon skillet apples
directions: Core apples, leaving peelings on; cut in half.
In 10-inch skillet, melt butter over medium heat for 3 to 4 minutes.
Mix cornstarch and sugar together.
Add to melted butter and mix well.
Add remaining ingredients and cook over medium heat, spooning sauce over apples occasionally, until apples are fork-tender and sauce is thickened, 12 to 15 minutes.

title: one pan potatoes and chicken dijon
directions: While potatoes cook, in large skillet, toss and brown chicken in oil over high heat for 5 minutes.
Add potatoes, saute and toss until potatoes are lightly browned.
Add barbecue sauce and tarragon.
Toss until heated through, 20 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water; set aside.
Sift flour, baking powder, soda, salt and sugar.
Cut in shortening.
Add milk to yeast mixture and combine with flour mixture.
Knead slightly. Roll out to 1/2-inch thickness; cut.
Place in pan and brush lightly with melted butter.
Let rise 30 minutes or refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 400° until golden brown, 10 to 15 minutes.

title: lemon carrots and snap peas
directions: Peel the carrots.
Cut in half lengthwise, then cut each half into slices.
String the snap peas.
Cook the carrots and peas separately in boiling water until tender, about 10 minutes for carrots and 5 minutes for snap peas.
Drain.

title: vicky's meatballs
directions: Mix ingredients and form into walnut sized meatballs (make hands wet).
Arrange on 15 x 10-inch baking sheet.

title: diabetic pineapple parfait
directions: Sprinkle gelatin over water. Place over low heat, stirring constantly until dissolved. Add ice cream, pineapple and strawberries. Stir gently until mixed. Refrigerate. Do not freeze.

title: reese squares
directions: Mix cracker crumbs, peanut butter, margarine and sugar together.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan or dish.
Melt 4 to 5 blocks of almond bark to cover top.
Let harden.
Cut into 1 inch squares.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Mix milk, shortening, sugar and salt.
Cool to lukewarm.
Mix yeast in warm water.
Stir and mix with milk, egg and half of flour.
Mix well.
Add rest of flour.
Turn out on floured board and knead about 10 minutes until smooth.
Place dough in warm greased bowl.
Brush with melted butter. Cover and let rise in warm place for 2 hours or until doubled in size.
Shape into rolls.
Cover and let rise until doubled in size, about 1/2 to 3/4 hours.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 20 minutes.

title: lime gelatin salad
directions: Melt marshmallows in boiling water in bowl. Add gelatin; stir until dissolved. Chill until partially set. Add pineapple, pecans and cheese; mix well. Fold in whipped topping. Chill until firm.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Cream sugar and oil; mix in eggs.
Beat flour and soda into mixture.
Add pumpkin and cinnamon.
Add nuts and coconut.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: easy brunswick stew
directions: Mix all ingredients and simmer for 1 hour.

title: time-to-spare ribs
directions: Will also need 1 large Reynolds oven cooking bag.

title: kamaboko dip and crackers
directions: Combine ingredients and chill.
Serve on Ritz crackers.

title: kookie brittle
directions: Combine margarine, vanilla and salt; blend well.
Gradually beat in sugar.
Add flour, then morsels.
Mix well.
Press evenly into ungreased 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes. Cool, then break in irregular pieces and drain on absorbent paper.

title: coffee cake
directions: Crumble the first 5 ingredients.
Keep out 1 1/2 cups; add 1/3 cup flour and set aside.
To rest, add gradually the milk and vanilla for stiff batter.
Put into well-greased loaf pan.
Squeeze together rest and sprinkle on top; add cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, approximately.
While still hot, add confectioners sugar to top.

title: pickled smelt
directions: Clean and cut smelt into bite-size pieces.
Mix 4 cups water and pickling salt for brine.
Put smelt into brine using plastic, glass, pottery or stainless steel container.
Let stand 48 hours. Rinse well with cold water; drain.
Cover smelt with vinegar and let stand 24 hours in a covered container.
Stir once or twice. Mix together 2 cups white vinegar, sugar and spices together in large saucepan.
Bring to a full rolling boil over medium heat. Remove from heat and cool.
Drain vinegar from smelt.
Put fish into clean pint jars.
Include at least 1/2 sliced onion and lemon slices in each jar.
Pour cooled brine over smelt.
Fill jar within 1/2-inch of top.
Seal and refrigerate.
Sample after 2 weeks.

title: zucchini pancakes
directions: Wash and shred zucchini.
Sprinkle with 1/2 teaspoon of salt and set aside for 30 minutes.
Drain and reserve liquid.
Saute onions in butter until softened.
Place zucchini and onion in large bowl.
Add eggs, flour, salt and pepper.
Pour oil in skillet and drop rounded tablespoonfuls into oil.
Flatten with back of spoon. Cook 1 minute on each side.
Remove pancakes and drain on paper toweling.
Serve immediately.

title: zucchini-tomato bake
directions: Layer half the zucchini, tomato and onion in a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with half the salt and cheese. Repeat layers.
Crumble bacon on top.
Cover and microwave on High for 6 to 8 minutes.

title: fruit cocktail congealed salad
directions: Bring jello, cream cheese and juice from fruit cocktail to a boil.
Cool.
Add fruit cocktail and nuts.
Then fold in whipped cream.
Refrigerate to congeal.
Makes medium size Pyrex dish.

title: party punch
directions: Combine Kool-Aid, sugar and water.
Stir until Kool-Aid and sugar are dissolved.
Add pineapple juice and orange juice and stir.
Chill until ready to serve.
Add ginger ale before serving.

title: saltine toffee (heath bars)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line cookie sheet with aluminum foil and cover entire pan with saltine squares.
Melt on stove the butter and sugar.
Pour mixture over crackers and bake approximately 15 minutes, until golden brown.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with chips.
Let melt and spread with a spatula. Cool, then break apart.

title: rice krispie treats(a favorite at youth fellowship)
directions: Dissolve each package in 1 cup boiling water; set aside to cool.
When cool, add 1 cup vodka to cherry Jell-O and pour into glass or ceramic serving dish.
Chill.
When slightly firm, add a layer of sliced bananas.
Repeat with orange layer (adding 1 cup vodka to orange Jell-O).
When slightly firm, add more bananas. Finally, add the top layer of lemon, not neglecting to add 1 cup vodka.

title: fudge frosting
directions: Combine sugar and salt. Melt chocolate in milk; add sugar mixture. Cook until a few drops form soft ball when dropped in cold water. Remove from heat. Add butter and vanilla. Let cool, then beat to spreading consistency.

title: meatball sweet and sour sauce
directions: Saute pepper and onion in margarine.
Add other ingredients to about 30 to 45 meatballs.
Heat 5 minutes in microwave or 20 minutes on stove.
Freeze other meat balls for another time.

title: armadillo on half shell
directions: Clean armadillo thoroughly!
Remove all flesh and hair from shell (use a whole shell not a broken one, i.e., messy road kill). Saute meat in butter until brown.
Combine other ingredients and simmer until done.
Replace ingredients and meat into shell.
Cover with Parmesan and bread crumbs.
Microwave on Medium setting for 5 minutes.
Oven bake at 300° to 350° for 30 minutes.

title: rockwood scallop potatoes and ham
directions: Peel and slice potatoes, layer in roasting pan with ham.
Mix soups, evaporated milk and onion soup mix; warm mixture to blend, pour over potatoes and ham (with knife lift potatoes around side of pan to allow some soup mixture to go down into potatoes).
Cover. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: crab bisque
directions: Combine all ingredients, adding the cream last.
Heat to serving temperature.
Do not let the soup boil.
This is a marvelous, rich soup and the recipe fills 6 generous bowls or makes an appetizer for 12.

title: okra-tomato gumbo
directions: Wash okra.
Remove stems and slice in circles.
Saute onion in bacon drippings until soft.
Add okra and cook until lightly brown.
Add tomatoes and seasonings.
Cover skillet and simmer 20 minutes.

title: ritzy raspberry punch
directions: Combine the cranberry-raspberry juice and limeade concentrate. Just before serving, add the seltzer water.
Top with lemon sherbet, if desired.
Makes 9 servings.

title: tropical pineapple coconut bars
directions: Mix ingredients.
Reserve 1 1/2 cups of crumbs.
Pat rest of mixture in an 11 x 13-inch pan.

title: best ever chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together the shortening, brown sugar and white sugar. Add eggs and vanilla and beat well.
Sift together and add flour, baking powder and salt.
Lastly, stir in the chocolate chips; nutmeats may also be added at this time, if desired.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.

title: dressing
directions: Mash all ingredients in food processor.
Add broth from chicken to good consistency.
Brown at 350°.
This recipe makes a large pan.

title: fudge sauce
directions: Mix these in heavy pan.
Cook at least 5 minutes.
No need to stir constantly.
Add vanilla.
(If doubling, use full can of evaporated milk.)
Saves well in the refrigerator.
Delicious over ice cream.

title: beans for a crowd
directions: Brown bacon and onion in skillet.
Drain off fat.
Add all ingredients to a crock-pot and stir together until well mixed. Cook on low 6 hours.
Can also be baked in the oven at 325° for two hours.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Spread crescent rolls completely over a cookie sheet to form the crust.
Bake at 400° for 7 to 10 minutes or until golden. Cool.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Wash and slice green tomatoes thin.
Soak in salt water for 30 minutes.
Drain.
Dredge in flour.
Fry in oil in skillet.
You may sprinkle a bit of sugar on tomatoes while in skillet.
Enjoy!!

title: shoestring salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, except shoestring potatoes.
Stir potatoes in just before serving.

title: slaw
directions: Mix sugar, vinegar, Wesson oil, mustard, celery seed, salt and turmeric.
Bring to rolling boil; pour over cabbage, onion and pepper.
Let stand for several hours before serving.
Keeps for several days in refrigerator.

title: diabetic cookies
directions: Combine raisins, dates and water.
Boil together for 3 minutes, stirring constantly to avoid sticking.
Cream together eggs, margarine, vanilla and sweetener.
Sift together cinnamon, flour and soda.
Add flour mixture to creamed mixture.
Add cooled raisin/date mixture.
Chill.
Drop by spoonfuls on a baking sheet. Bake at 350° until brown, about 10 to 12 minutes.

title: black iron skillet cornbread
directions: Melt shortening in heavy skillet.
Sift dry ingredients into bowl.
Add the egg and milk; mix well.
Pour into the same skillet and stir again to mix the shortening with the batter.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes.

title: picnic eggs
directions: Slice eggs in half and remove yolk to a medium sized bowl. Mash yolks with fork and stir in remaining ingredients.
Add a spoonful of yolk mixture back to egg white.
Serve cold.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Scrub potatoes; steam until almost tender.
Plunge into cold water, then peel, grate coarsely and grate onion; mix.
Beat egg with salt, pepper and milk; add to potato-onion mixture.
Combine lightly.
Preheat oil on cookie sheet.
Drop by tablespoon onto sheet and flatten with back of spoon.
Bake at 350° until bottoms brown, about 20 minutes.
Turn and brown other side, about 15 minutes more.
Makes 16 pancakes.

title: pink cloud
directions: Drain pineapple and heat juice.
Dissolve jello in juice.
Set aside to cool.
Stir in cottage cheese, pineapple and Cool Whip. Pour into mold and set overnight.

title: chili
directions: Brown beef; drain.
Add onions and garlic; brown all together until onions are tender.
Add chili powder, tomatoes (optional to crush tomatoes first), tomato sauce, tomato paste and kidney beans.
Let boil, cover and then simmer 30 to 45 minutes, stirring occasionally.
(Optional:
Add salt and pepper to taste and chopped green pepper, added with the onion and garlic, if desired.)

title: butter crunch pie crust
directions: Mix all together by hand; spread into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 400°. Remove from oven and stir with fork. Press into a 9-inch pie pan to cover bottom and sides. Great for fruit pies or instant jello pudding pies.

title: marzetti
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and green pepper.
Drain off fat. Stir in next nine ingredients.
Spoon into a greased 3-quart casserole.
Top with cheese.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: strawberry trifle
directions: Bake cake as directed.
Cool.
Cut cake crosswise in half. Pour 1 package of the strawberries with syrup over cake.
Slice 1 of the bananas over strawberries.
Spread with half of the pudding.
Place other half of cake on this and then repeat layers (strawberries, bananas, etc.).
Cover.
Chill at least 4 hours. Spread over trifle.
Sprinkle with almonds.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Add boiling water.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add slowly a small amount of hot mixture to beaten egg yolks, return to remaining hot mixture and cook 1 minute or until thick.
Remove from heat.
Add butter, lemon juice and grated peel.
Pour into baked pie shell.

title: leaf lettuce dressing
directions: Combine ingredients and chill.
Serve over green salad.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Cook hamburger, onion and bell pepper.
Add tomatoes, Worcestershire sauce and ketchup.
Cook noodles and drain. Alternate hamburger mixture and noodles in casserole dish.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat in hot oil; add onion and garlic.
Cook until transparent.
Add tomatoes, tomato paste, tomato sauce, salt and basil and cook until sauce is thickened.
Stir in olives.

title: party baked beans
directions: Combine beans, pineapple, molasses and mustard in a 1 1/2-quart casserole. Combine brown sugar, cinnamon and cloves and sprinkle over beans. Top with the 8 scored frankfurters.
Brush with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serves 4 to 6.

title: 4x sugar cake
directions: Cream butter well.
Add sugar alternating with eggs and with sifted
flour;
add
flavoring;
beat,
beat.
Pour into greased tube
pan.
Bake
at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Don't open oven during the 1st hour of baking.

title: swedish meatball appetizers
directions: Combine meats with onion. Soak bread crumbs in milk.
Add eggs, salt, allspice, and pepper.
Mix with meat and onions.
Form into small balls.
Roll in flour and brown in hot fat in large skillet, turning often.
When lightly browned, remove from skillet, blot, and put in medium casserole bowl which has been greased.
Pour sauce over hot meatballs and bake 30 minutes at 300°. May be served either hot or cold.
May also be partially baked, cooled, wrapped, and put in freezer.
Thaw at room temperature or in microwave.
Makes 25-30 small balls.

title: cranberry float
directions: Combine juices in punch bowl.
Pour in ginger ale.
Top with small scoops of sherbet.

title: grilled smoke sausage
directions: Heat preserves in small saucepan over low heat 5 minutes. Remove from heat and stir in lemon juice and mustard.
Grill sausage on uncovered grill over low heat, brushing with apricot glaze. Continue to grill and glaze sausage about 5 minutes longer. Great with baked potato and mixed vegetables.

title: crock-pot green chili
directions: Brown pork with salt, pepper and garlic salt.
Put meat, tomatoes and green chilies and green chilies in crock-pot.
Cover with water; cook for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Add cream of mushroom soup.

title: ham bone soup
directions: Cover the ham bone with water in a large kettle and boil until meat is almost tender.
Add remaining ingredients, except corn. Cover and cook slowly for 3 to 4 hours, adding corn during last 15 minutes.

title: candy fudge
directions: Mix together margarine, milk and sugar in a heavy saucepan. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly.
When it reaches a soft ball stage when tested in cold water, remove from heat and pour over the marshmallow cream and chocolate chips.
Beat until smooth.
Pour into a greased Pyrex dish.
Cut into squares when cool.
Makes a large amount of fudge.

title: microwave fudge
directions: In a 4-quart microwavable bowl, microwave margarine on High heat for 1 minute or until melted.
Add the sugar and milk; mix well with melted margarine.
Microwave 5 more minute or until the mixture begins to boil (at round 3 minutes, stir mixture and microwave the remaining 5 minutes).
Stir mixture again and scrape bowl, continue to microwave 6 more minutes (again stirring after about 3 minutes).
Mixture should be good and bubbly by now; remove from microwave and gradually stir in the chocolate chips until melted.
Then add remaining ingredients.
Mix until good and smooth and pour into 13 x 9-inch lightly greased pan.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: butter ring
directions: Blend flour, 2 tablespoons sugar and salt and cut in butter as for pie crust.
Dissolve yeast and 2 teaspoons sugar in milk.
When foamy, add egg yolks which have been beaten with cream.
Combine with flour mixture and mix well.
Chill several hours or overnight. Divide into 3 parts.
Cut each part into 3 pieces and roll and twist to form butter ring.
Bake at 350° to 375° until golden brown.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Rub outside crust off angel food cake and save.
Break 1/2 of cake into bite size pieces and place on bottom of compote.
Cap strawberries and mix with glaze.
Spread half over cake.
Mix both boxes of pudding with 3 cups of milk.
(I use sugar-free pudding and skim milk.)
Beat until thick; add Cool Whip.
Spread half of this mixture over layer of berries and glaze.
Repeat layers (cake, berries, pudding).
Sprinkle cake crumbs on top and decorate with large berries.
Refrigerate until ready to eat.

title: chunky fruit compote
directions: About 10 minutes before serving, in a large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Makes 4 servings, about 215 calories per serving.

title: macaroon bars
directions: Cream butter and 1/2 cup sugar.
Beat in egg yolks, one at a time.
Gently beat in flour and salt.
Stir in 1 cup of coconut, nuts and rind.
Spread in 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or golden brown on edges.
Beat egg whites; add cream of tartar until foamy throughout.
Gradually add remaining sugar, beating after each addition.
Beat in juice and beat until stiff peaks.
Spread over cooled mixture.
Sprinkle with remaining coconut.
Bake at 375° until topping is golden brown, 10 to 15 minutes.
Cool and cut into bars.
Store in tightly covered box.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: In a saucepan, over medium heat, mix all ingredients, except broccoli.
Cook until blended.
Pour over broccoli in a buttered baking dish.
Sprinkle with Pepperidge Farm stuffing, mixed with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes until bubbly.

title: fettuccine alfredo
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Gradually stir in cream, cheese and egg. Then stir in fettuccine.
Add some Parmesan cheese on top.

title: cookie cake
directions: Divide wafers into two equal piles.
Spread whipped topping on each wafer and stack one on top of the other until you have 2 stacks.
Lay them down on their edges, side by side on a plate and use the rest of the whipped cream or topping to frost your cake. Cover with waxed paper and refrigerate for 3 hours.
When you cut into the cake, cut it diagonally and it will look like a layer cake.

title: barbecue meatballs
directions: Mix ground beef, onion soup, beaten eggs and cracker crumbs together and form into 1-inch balls.
Brown meatballs in cooking oil.
Remove from skillet and hold.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt margarine in large cast-iron skillet. Place split chicken in a bag with flour, salt and pepper.
Shake well.

title: sandy's mushroom swiss bread
directions: Slice bread diagonally one way, then the other way, making a diamond effect.
Place bread on foil; stuff generously with Swiss cheese and mushrooms.
Melt butter and mix with all other ingredients.
Pour over bread.
Cover with foil and seal.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix flour and shortening with salt until well blended; add cold water.
Makes 1 shell.

title: broccoli cheddar twice baked potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes well.
Dry and pierce several times with fork. Bake at 400° for about 1 hour or until soft.
Cool.
Cut potatoes in half lengthwise; carefully scoop potato pulp into bowl (leave 1/2-inch of pulp to keep the potato skins intact).
Set potato skins aside.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: In large bowl, beat eggs 5 minutes.
Add sugars, vanilla and butter.
Mix well to combine.
Add flour, salt and soda.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Spray cookie sheets.
Drop by ice cream scoop onto cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Let cool 5 minutes, then remove to wire rack to finish cooling.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Sift together dry ingredients, except nuts and set aside. Mash bananas; add eggs, vanilla and oil, beating well.
Fold chopped nuts into the batter and pour into a greased and floured medium size (8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch) loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool bread in pan for 20 minutes.

title: seafood gumbo
directions: Heat soup over low heat.
Gradually add milk and cheese.
Stir constantly and cook 15 minutes. Add shrimp and crabmeat.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes until shrimp are pink.
Serve over noodles.
Serves 4.

title: peach delight pie
directions: Mix first three ingredients together and spread in 9 x 12 pan or two 9-inch pie pans.
Bake until light brown in 350° or 400° oven.
Let cool completely.

title: cheese loaf
directions: Combine flour and cheese.
Combine egg, oil and milk.
Add liquid mixture to cheese mixture.
Mix just enough to moisten cheese mixture.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pan (9 x 5 2 3/4).
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Break up first 5 ingredients.
Spread thin in oblong casserole dish.
Mix remaining ingredients and spread over vegetables. Refrigerate (best overnight).

title: jello salad
directions: Drain blueberries, reserving juice.
Measure in a measuring cup; add enough water to juice until you have 1 cup of liquid. Heat to boiling.
Dissolve Jell-O in hot juice.
Add 1 cup cold 7-Up; mix.
Add blueberries and pineapple.
Pour in dish and refrigerate.
Mix softened cream cheese and Cool Whip.
Top.

title: carrot pie
directions: Put mashed carrots in bowl; add butter, flour, sugar, eggs and milk.
Mix well.
Pour in an unbaked pie crust and bake in a 400° oven until nicely browned.
Use meringue topping, if desired.

title: venison chili
directions: Melt butter in large saucepan.
Add the onions and cook at medium heat until transparent, hot brown; add the ground venison and cook until lightly brown.
(Break it up with a fork.)
Add the tomatoes, tomato paste, beer, salt, Tabasco and chili powder. Lower heat and simmer for 45 to 50 minutes.
If spaghetti is used, prepare according to the package directions and add during the last 15 minutes of cooking time.
Serves 8.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken breasts.
Cut in small pieces.
In a 13 x 9 x 2-inch glass baking dish, line bottom with chicken.
Mix soup and sour cream; spoon over chicken.
Top with crushed Ritz crackers, mixed with butter or margarine.
Spread on top and heat at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: ziti casserole
directions: Cook ziti.
Put a thin layer of sauce on the bottom of a casserole dish.
Then add a layer of ziti. Mix 1 egg into the Ricotta cheese.
Spread a thin layer over the ziti.
Repeat the layers and put the Mozzarella cheese on top.
Bake at 375°.

title: hollenbeck hoagies
directions: Spread bread with cream cheese on top and bottom.
Layer cheese, onions, meat and green peppers.
Broil 5 minutes until cheese melts.
Tune into a good football game and chow down!

title: poppy seed-filled ravioli cookies
directions: Mix sugar, shortening, margarine, vanilla and eggs in large bowl.
Stir in flour, baking soda and salt.
Divide dough into 4 equal parts.
Cover and refrigerate 2 hours.
Place 1/2 cup poppy seed, the almonds, milk, 2 Tbsp. honey, lemon peel and lemon juice in blender or food processor.
Cover and blend until liquid is absorbed.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Stir together the sugar, flour and cornstarch.
Add eggs, milk, melted butter, lemon juice and grated lemon rind.
Beat with mixer until thoroughly blended.
Pour into unbaked 9-inch pie crust and bake at 375° for 35 to 45 minutes or until a knife inserted into center comes out clean.

title: do nothing cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Mix well with blender and pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes and at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix the cream cheese and grated sharp cheese real good.
Mix all other ingredients with cheese mixture.
Roll in a ball; refrigerate until hard.
Roll cheese ball in about 1/2 package of chili mix; serve with crackers.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Grease baking sheet very heavily.
Combine sugar, syrup and salt in a 3-quart bowl (microwavable).
Stir in peanuts. Microwave at High (100%) until light brown, 8 to 10 minutes, depending on your oven, stirring once or twice.
Stir in remaining ingredients until light and foamy.
Quickly spread on baking sheet as thin as possible for brittle candy.
Break into pieces once it is cool.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cheese and chips, and place in greased
two-quart
bowl.
Spread cheese and chips on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yield:
4 to 6 servings.

title: macaroni - egg salad
directions: Cover macaroni with cold water; drain.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Refrigerate overnight for best results.

title: broccoli-cheese casserole
directions: Prepare broccoli according to package, then drain.
Add mixture of cheese, rice, onions, soup and crackers.
Put in casserole dish and bake at 350° until done.

title: watch your weight soup
directions: Fresh carrots, broccoli and cauliflower may be substituted but takes longer.

title: owens' peppers rellenos
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cut off the tops of each bell pepper and set aside.
Hollow out the inside of each pepper, discarding the seed and membrane.
Take care not to puncture the outside skin.
Combine in a large bowl the sausage, ground beef, eggs, salsa, garlic powder, tortilla chips, chopped onion and cubed cheese.
Mix everything together well.

Next, using a tablespoon, press the meat mixture into the bell peppers, not over-filling. Now sprinkle the grated cheese over the top of the meat in each bell pepper, put the tops on each pepper and bake for 45 minutes.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix shortening, sugar and eggs. Combine remaining ingredients.
Roll into small balls.
Roll in a mixture of 2 tablespoons sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon.
Place 2 inches apart on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes. Makes 5 dozen.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook sugar, wax and Karo in large skillet on high until turning tan.
Turn to low.
Quickly add nuts.
Work fast.
Add flavor and baking soda, stirring while adding.
Pour onto warmed cookie sheet, not too hot or wax will flame.

title: ambrosia waldorf salad
directions: Combine cranberries and sugar.
In a large bowl, combine the marshmallows, apples, grapes, pecans and pineapple.
Add cranberries and mix well.
Fold in whipped cream.
Cover and chill.
Sprinkle with coconut before serving.
Yields 12 to 14 servings.

title: make your own vanilla
directions: In bottle of rum, put whole vanilla bean with a few slits in it.
Let set for 6 months.

title: green enchiladas with spicy sauce
directions: In skillet, cook tortillas one at a time in hot oil for 15 seconds on each side.
Do not overcook or they won't roll.
Place 2 tablespoons shredded cheese and 1 tablespoon onion on each tortilla; roll up.
Place seam side down in an 11 3/4 x 7 1/2 x 1 3/4-inch baking dish.

title: antipasto rolls
directions: Drain olives and peppers.
Cut peppers into 1-inch strips. Lay slice of Prosciutto flat.
Center a strip of pepper on each slice and roll jelly-roll fashion.
Fasten with toothpicks.
Makes about 15 rolls.

title: barbecue pecans
directions: Melt butter.
Add other ingredients.
Pour over pecans.
Toss until coated.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Stir 3 times during baking period.

title: mcgorp(good ol' raisins and macadamia nuts)
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large zip lock bag and eat.

title: cranberry nut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs and beat well.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Add to mixture alternately with cranberry sauce.
Last, add water and nuts.
Place in 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
(Makes 2 aluminum foil loaf pans; great for Christmas gifts.)

title: haupia(coconut pudding)
directions: Add liquid to cornstarch slowly until smooth paste.
Mix all ingredients.
Cook over medium heat, stirring to prevent lumps, until thick.
Pour into pan and refrigerate until cool.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: bean casserole
directions: Cook bacon.
Remove bacon from pan.
Add onions, garlic, vinegar and sugar to bacon grease.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Add to bean and bacon in casserole.
Bake at 350 for about 1 hour.

title: brownies for diabetics
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cream the butter and sweetener until light and fluffy. Add chocolate.
Beat until smooth. Beat in eggs and vanilla. Add flour, baking powder and nuts.
Beat until smooth. Spread in greased 8 x 8-inch pan and bake for 30 minutes or until shiny.

title: molasses drop cookies
directions: Mix ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Brown bread crumbs.
Melt 1 stick oleo with crumbs in skillet. Put chicken in casserole dish. Add vegetables, soups and onion. Put brown bread crumbs on top.
Add cheese on top and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: egg rolls
directions: Mix all together.
Place spoonful on corner of wrapper, moisten edges with water or beer and roll them up.
Fry in oil until light golden brown. Can freeze and re-fry to crisp them. Serve with hot mustard or sweet and sour sauce.
Makes approximately 190 to 200 egg rolls.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Combine cranberry sauce and sugar; set aside.
Dissolve jello in juice from pineapple plus enough water to make 1 cup.
Chill until almost set.
Add cranberry mixture, pineapple (drained), nuts and celery.
Chill until firm.

title: asparagus stuffed potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes at 400° for 1 hour or until done.
Cut thin slice off the top and scoop out the pulp (carefully) leaving shell in tact.
In mixing bowl, mash pulp with milk, sour cream, onion, salt and pepper until smooth.
Fold asparagus into mixture.
Fold into shells.
Crumble bacon on top.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Cream butter, oil and sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla and sour milk. Add dry ingredients.
Stir in zucchini.
Spread in greased and floured 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: crumpets
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Dissolve yeast in water.
Beat eggs; add milk, butter, salt and sugar.
Add yeast mixture and flour, beating until smooth and well blended.
Cover and set aside in warm place for 15 minutes.

title: roquefort cheese dressing
directions: Mix together and serve at once.

title: new potato salad
directions: In 1-quart saucepan, combine potatoes with enough water to cover; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and let simmer until potatoes are fork-tender, about 25 minutes; drain well.
Transfer potatoes to salad bowl and set aside.

title: brownies
directions: In a large mixing bowl, cream cocoa, sugar and margarine.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flour, nuts and vanilla.
Spread into a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 27 minutes.
Test for doneness with a toothpick inserted in center or they are done when sides turn in.
Frost when cool if desired.
Cut into squares.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle pecans, then coconut on bottom of pan.
Prepare cake mix as directed on box, then pour over pecans and coconut.
Beat oleo, cream cheese until smooth, then add vanilla and powdered sugar and beat until well blended.
Spoon mixture in large heaping spoonfuls on top of cake, avoiding the sides of the pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.
Cake will seem not done, but as it cools, it sets.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients well and add next 5 ingredients and mix well.
Place 1/2 of mixture into a baking dish (9 x 12-inches).
Cover with egg slices.
Put remaining mixture over egg slices.
Cover with crushed potato chips. Bake 1/2 hour at 450°.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Fold carrots, cheese and soup together.
Put into buttered casserole dish.
Put buttered bread crumbs on top.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: hot fudge pudding dessert
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Blend in milk.
Beat in butter and vanilla until smooth.
Pour into 8 x 8-inch pan.
Combine sugar, brown sugar and cocoa.
Sprinkle over batter.
Pour hot water over top.
Don't stir.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Combine pulp, baking soda, sugar and eggs. Slowly add milk. Add remaining ingredients and beat with mixer until smooth. Slowly add 2 sticks melted butter.
Pour into 3 greased loaf pans. Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Cool before removing from pans.

title: white bean soup
directions: Saute carrots, celery and onion in olive oil.
Add soaked beans and fill pan with water and chicken broth.
Cook until tender, about 2 or 2 1/2 hours.
Add the fennel seed after the beans have been cooking for an hour.
Cook small tube pasta until firm; add to beans.
Add chopped raw spinach.
Cover, shut off stove and let spinach cook in the soup.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add garlic cloves if you want when you saute carrots and celery.
Add water or broth if soup gets too thick.

title: corn dip
directions: Mix well.
Refrigerate and serve with chips or crackers.
