title: rice krispies squares
directions: Melt butter in saucepan over low heat.
Add marshmallows. Stir until melted and well blended.
Remove from heat; stir in cereal.
Press in buttered 9 x 9-inch pan.

title: custard
directions: Add milk to sugar in 4-quart heavy pan.
Heat slowly.
Beat eggs with mixer and add to milk.
Cook on low heat until it starts to get thick.
Add vanilla.
Cool.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken until done.
Debone chicken and cut up.
Cover bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with chicken.
Mix together the soups and sour cream until smooth.
Heat the mixture and pour over chicken.
Top with crumbs (stuffing mix).
Melt margarine in chicken broth and pour over crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes until bubbly.

title: cranberry-apple relish
directions: Place cranberries, Splenda, water and orange juice in medium saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Boil 3-4 minutes or until cranberries start to thicken and water has reduced by half.
Pour into bowl; cover and chill 2-3 hours or overnight.
Add diced apple and one-half of the raisins to cranberries.
Stir well.
Chill until ready to serve.
Just before serving, sprinkle remaining raisins over cranberries as garnish.
Serve chilled with roast meats or poultry.
Makes 20 (1-oz.) servings.

title: spinach and rice
directions: Saute onion ni butter until tender but not brown.
Combine onions, spinach and broth.
Bring to a boil.
Add rice, salt and pepper.
Stir well and simmer for about 20 minutes or until rice has absorbed broth and is tender.

title: cheater cajun jambalaya
directions: You will need a 3-quart casserole with lid.

title: chicken-noodle casserole
directions: Cook chicken.
Debone and chop in small pieces.
Saute butter, green pepper and onion.
Cook macaroni and drain.
Combine all ingredients and put in greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: tuna sensation(dip)
directions: Mix, cover and put into refrigerator for 2 to 3 hours to allow flavors to blend.
One half hour before serving, remove from refrigerator and let stand at room temperature so that the mixture will be of dipping consistency.
Serve as a dip with crackers or potato chips.
Makes about 1 2/3 cups dip.
If a thicker consistency is desired, cut down on the sour cream.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread on top of cooled crescent roll crust.
Top with vegetables of your choice such as:
tomatoes, black olives, red peppers, green peppers, shredded carrots, mushrooms and onions. Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Have salsa available to top with when serving.

title: zucchini-garlic pasta
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions.
Meanwhile, in large skillet over medium heat, cook bacon until crisp.
Remove with slotted spoon and set aside; discard all but 2 Tbsp of drippings.
Saute onion and garlic in drippings until tender, about 3 minutes.
Add zucchini and salt; cook until tender, about 6 minutes.
Add pasta to zucchini mixture.
Add lemon juice and bacon; toss.
Transfer to serving bowl and sprinkle with cheese. Yield: 6-8 servings.

title: dip for raw vegetables
directions: Blend ingredients in blender until creamy.
Chill before serving.
Use with low calorie raw vegetables, i.e.
cucumber stalks, carrot sticks, celery sticks, etc.

title: science soup for 450
directions: If you have enough to fill the size of a bathtub, that's about right.

title: angel pie
directions: Butter a 9-inch pie plate and set it aside.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook zucchini and onion together until almost done; drain very well.
Cook rice as directed; reserve.
Place zucchini mixture in buttered 9 1/2 inch shallow casserole.
Sprinkle cooked rice on top.
Mix soup and milk, then pour over top of rice.
Top with cheese slices.
Mix crumbs and melted butter; sprinkle over cheese. Place casserole in pan of water.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Makes 6 servings.

title: icebox rolls
directions: Scald
milk.
Add
sugar,
shortening
and
salt.
When cool, add
yeast	and dissolve.
Add 2 cups flour.
Beat until smooth. Let
stand	1
hour.
Add
more flour, soda and salt. Knead, make out into rolls.
Let stand about 2 hours and bake. This sponge may be placed in icebox and used for several days.

title: caribbean ice cream pie
directions: In a large skillet, stir coconut in melted butter over medium-high heat until golden and toasty.
Reserve 2 tablespoons for garnish.
Press remainder into bottom and sides of 9-inch pie plate and chill.

title: easy sloppy joes
directions: In browning dish, saute the beef, onion, bell pepper and chili powder.
Add the tomato soup, salt and pepper; simmer a few minutes.
Split and toast in broiler or oven the buns or rolls. Top with burger mixture.
Serves 2, generously.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Bake at 350° until brown.

title: dirt cake
directions: You will need 1 large flowerpot, 1 artificial flower (optional) and gummy worms (optional) for this recipe.

title: french toast
directions: Beat egg in a rather flat bowl (soup plate is perfect).
Stir in the salt, granulated sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg until combined well.
Heat large frying pan or griddle on low to medium.
Melt butter or margarine but not browned.
Dip one slice of the bread into egg mixture for a few seconds; turn bread over in egg and let soak a few seconds, being careful not to break up bread.
Cook on hot griddle (low to medium heat) about 5 minutes on each side or until golden brown.
Repeat with rest of the bread slices. Transfer to warm plates and sprinkle with confectioners sugar. Use desired topping:
warm syrup, jelly or fresh fruit.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut broccoli in bite size pieces. Add all remaining ingredients. Refrigerate overnight.

title: pecan brittle
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and water.
Bring to boil, then add pecans (broken or halved).
Cook slowly until the syrup is brown. Remove from heat and add the other 3 ingredients.
Pour as thinly as possible onto a well-greased cookie sheet.
Allow to cool and then break into small pieces.

title: chocolate-peanut butter pie
directions: Combine peanut butter and powdered sugar until crumbly. Reserve 1/4 cup mixture.
Sprinkle remaining peanut butter mixture in bottom of baked pie shell.
Prepare pudding mix with milk according to package directions.
Pour pudding into shell.
Chill until set.
Beat heavy cream until stiff.
Spread on top of pie. Sprinkle with 1/4 cup reserved peanut butter mixture.

title: green pea salad(with shrimp, optional)
directions: Combine all ingredients and add as much mayonnaise as needed. Refrigerate 2 hours.
Add cold boiled shrimp for main dish.

title: mother's strawberry snow mountain pie
directions: Bake and set aside the pie crusts.
Hull, wash and drain strawberries.
Combine egg whites and vanilla; beat until peaks are formed.
Boil together water and sugar.
Cook until mixture forms a hard thread.
Pour over beaten egg whites, beating as you pour.
Continue beating until mixture forms peaks.

Slice strawberries into prepared crusts and top with boiled frosting. This pie is best put together just before serving as the combination of frosting and berries may cause crust to get soggy if it sits too long.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together in a large bowl.
In another bowl, beat eggs and oil.
Add carrots and mix well.
Add to dry ingredients and mix well.
Divide evenly between two 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Check to be sure.
Some oven temperatures vary.

title: nutty bars
directions: Pour butter into cake mix.
Add 3/4 cup pecans.
Press into 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Mix cream cheese and brown sugar. Press onto cake mixture.
Sprinkle with 3/4 cup chopped pecans. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let cool.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Mix cookie mix according to instructions on the box.
Spread dough on ungreased pizza pan and bake 12 minutes or until golden brown.
When completely cool, mix together cream cheese, whipped topping and sugar.
Spread over crust.
Slice fruits and sprinkle with Fruit Fresh or dip in lemon juice.
Then place on crust sparingly.
Refrigerate.
Serve in small wedges.

title: captains country chicken
directions: Roll chicken in mixture of flour, salt and pepper. Brown in oil. Remove to roaster. Add onions, pepper and garlic. Cook slowly until tender. Add tomatoes, curry powder and thyme. Heat thoroughly. Pour over chicken. Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Mix all ingredients. Top with a few maraschino cherry halves.

title: colorful corn salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine the first 12 ingredients. In a microwave-safe dish combine oil and garlic. Microwave, uncovered, on high for 1 minute. Cool. Whish in lime juice. Pour over the corn mixture and toss to coat. Cover and refrigerate until serving. Yield: 16-18 servings.

title: tasty tuna salad
directions: Mix all together and serve on croissants.

title: banana cake
directions: Fold creamed shortening and sugar in eggs.
Add dry ingredients, milk and bananas.
(Make sure they are mashed.)
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° until done.

title: oven caramel corn
directions: Prepare popcorn.
Cook syrup, oleo, sugar and salt for 5 minutes.
Remove from stove.
Add soda.
Stir well.
Pour over corn and mix well.
Spread on 2 cookie sheets.
Bake in 200° oven for 1 hour.
Stir at least once in oven.
Too high heat can burn brown sugar.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix all wet ingredients together.
Then add all dry.
Mix well and pour into greased bread pans 3/4 full.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until done inside.

title: date balls
directions: Melt margarine; stir in sugar, salt and dates.
Cool for 4 to 5 minutes.
Stir.
Add Rice Krispies and nuts.
Dip by spoonful and roll in powdered sugar.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff, adding cream of tartar, salt, sugar and vanilla.
While beating, fold in chocolate chips and nuts.
Spoon small mounds of mix onto wax paper lined cookie sheet.
Preheat oven and turn off heat.
Let cookies stay in oven overnight.
Do not open oven door until morning.

title: herb dip(for fresh vegetables)
directions: Mix mayo and sour cream first, then add rest of ingredients.

title: turkey casserole
directions: Combine sugar, salt, turkey, celery, green pepper, onion, lemon juice, mayonnaise, cheese, soup and 1 cup cracker crumbs in baking dish.
Sprinkle with remaining 1 cup cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: harvard beets(microwave)
directions: In a 1-quart casserole dish, combine sugar, cornstarch, salt and pepper; stir in vinegar, liquid and beets.
Cook, covered, for 6 minutes or until mixture boil and thickens, slightly stirring during the last half of cooking time.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Cut up vegetables into thick slices.
Place in layers with salt.
Allow to stand 3 to 4 hours, then drain.
Mix remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Add vegetables and boil for 5 minutes.
Place in hot jars and seal.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Heat chicken, chicken broth and 1 2/3 tablespoons dry milk together to a low boil.
Mix flour, baking powder and salt in a bowl.
Mix corn oil, water and 1 tablespoon dry milk together. Pour liquid mixture into dry
mixture.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoon into boiling chicken mixture.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes.

title: meat knishes
directions: Scramble hamburg in frying pan.
Mix in chili sauce, onion powder, peppers and onion to taste.
Drain; cool 1/2 hour in refrigerator.
Place 1 tablespoon hamburg mixture in center of crescent roll; wrap around.
Bake on cookie sheet as on package.

title: pie crust
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cut in Crisco until thoroughly mixed.
Add water, mix well.
Do not over handle.
Makes 2 or 3 crusts.

title: mixed mashed potatoes
directions: Bake or boil potatoes, already peeled.
Add margarine, salt, pepper, milk and syrup.
Whip with blender.

title: no-peek soup
directions: Add water to large casserole.
Bake all ingredients, covered, at 325° for 4 to 4 1/2 hours.

title: fresh apple bread
directions: Cream 1 cup sugar and margarine.
Add eggs and apples. Mix in dry ingredients, vanilla, buttermilk and nuts.
Pour into loaf pan.
Sprinkle top with remaining 3 tablespoons sugar and cinnamon. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate chip pecan pie
directions: Divide pecans and chips into 2 pie crusts.
Combine melted butter and beaten eggs.
Add sugar and corn syrup.	Divide between the pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: haystacks
directions: Melt
peanut
butter
and butterscotch morsels over low heat in medium saucepan.
Stir in Chinese noodles and peanuts. Scoop out
teaspoons
of	haystacks
and put on a cookie sheet covered with wax paper.
Cool.

title: pilgrim soup
directions: Do not drain vegetables.
Do not add extra water.

title: yeast potato rolls
directions: Heat water until warm.
Add butter and milk.
Mix 2 cups of the flour with the yeast, potato flakes, sugar and salt.
Add liquid mixture.
Add eggs and mix.
Gradually work in remaining flour. Set aside to rest in buttered bowl.
Cover with cloth while rising. When dough is double in size, punch down and let rise again until doubled.
Punch down a second time and shape into desired size rolls.
Let rolls rise a little before baking at 425° for 10 minutes or until light brown.

title: mexi-dip
directions: Cook ground beef in skillet, stirring occasionally, until brown and drain excess fat.
Stir in mustard, 1/4 to 1/2 teaspoon chili powder, onion, pepper, beans, tomato sauce and seasoning mix.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Spread into ungreased pie plate.
Mix sour cream, Cheddar cheese and 1/4 teaspoon chili powder together.
Spread sour cream mixture over beef mixture. Top with shredded lettuce and cheese. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: good peach pie
directions: Put cornstarch and sugar in a saucepan.
Slowly add water and cook until thick.
Remove from heat and add jello.
Set this mixture in refrigerator until it begins to set.
When it starts to thicken, add peaches.
Return to refrigerator and when it has thickened again, put into the pie shell.
Refrigerate for at least 3 hours.
Serve each piece with whipped cream.

title: mandarin orange jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add sherbet and let cool.
Add oranges and pineapple.
Chill until set.

title: chicken divan
directions: Remove bones from chicken, but leave skin on.
Place skin side down; pat and spread to make cutlet.
On each breast half, put a slice of ham, a piece of cheese and a spear of broccoli (put flowerets at each end).
Roll up chicken.
Fasten with toothpicks. Place on rack in baking pan with a small amount of water underneath.
Cover and bake 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake 30 minutes longer, or until done.
Serve with a sauce made from the drippings, mushrooms and white wine, if desired.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Heat 2 tablespoons oil in skillet.
Add onions and mushrooms. Cook over medium low heat until soft.
Remove to bowl and keep warm.
Add remaining oil to skillet and stir-fry beef until brown on outside and pink inside.
Add other ingredients.
Stir over low heat to combine and heat thoroughly.
Season to taste and serve.

title: golden baked chicken
directions: Beat egg with water, salt, pepper and basil.
Drop the chicken pieces into this and stir until well coated.
Roll each piece in bread crumbs.
Place in 13 x 9 buttered shallow pan and dot with butter.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour.
Makes 4 servings.

title: turnip fluff
directions: Pare turnips and boil in salted water.
Drain; mash (makes 2 cups mashed).
Add light cream or evaporated milk, egg, oleo, brown sugar and corn meal or Cream of Wheat.
Bake 40 minutes in 350° oven.

title: sausage-zucchini boats
directions: Cook zucchini in boiling water until barely tender, about 10 minutes.
Cut squash in half lengthwise. Scoop out pulp, leaving about 1/4-inch rim around shells so they will stand upright. Finely chop squash.

title: baked corn
directions: Beat eggs and salt well. Stir in milk, sugar, cornstarch, crumbs and butter.
Add corn. Pour into 2-quart casserole and bake at 325° for 1 hour or at 425° for 30 minutes.

title: kool delight
directions: Combine cottage cheese, jello and drained fruit; mix well. Blend in Cool Whip.
Chill.

title: cauliflower cheese bake
directions: Cook
cauliflower
for
minutes
or
until
tender. Drain. Spread mayonnaise, mustard and cheese on
the
head of the cauliflower.
Bake in oven at 375° for 15 minutes or until it is brown on top.

title: chicken a la ristow
directions: Place chicken breasts in baking pan.
Prepare stuffing and place on chicken.
Put slice of tomato on chicken breast.
Spread the chicken soup in pan.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: sue's burritos
directions: Stir-fry meat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Heat until hot. Heat flour tortillas in skillet.
Spoon meat mixture onto tortillas, fold over and eat.

title: stuffed breast of chicken
directions: Wash and dry breasts.
On rib side of breast, open up with knife or fingers to make a pocket.
Stuff with prepared dressing. Spray a shallow roasting pan with Pam and arrange breasts in single layer.
In a bowl, mix soups.
Pour over chicken. Sprinkle chilies and pimientos on top.
Sprinkle with paprika and parsley.
Bake in preheated oven for 1 hour at 350°.
Serve over rice or noodles.
Can be prepared in advance, oven ready.

title: fruit tea
directions: Boil tea bags.
Remove and add sugar; mix well then add orange juice and lemonade.
Add water to make 1 gallon.

title: apricot delight
directions: Mix apricot nectar and sugar in saucepan and bring to boil. Combine the reserved apricot nectar and cornstarch.
Reduce heat and slowly stir in cornstarch mixture and cook until thickened. Remove from heat and stir in almond flavoring.
Break pieces of angel food cake and placed in the bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour mixture while hot over cake pieces.
Cool and top with whipped topping and slivered almonds.
Chill before serving.

title: black raspberry pie
directions: Pour mixture into unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 350° for 20 minutes.
This makes a great red raspberry pie, too!

title: cheese chowder
directions: Add all ingredients together and cook for at least 1 hour.

title: pecan pralines
directions: Cook sugar, syrup and cream to soft ball stage.
Stir in pecans, vanilla and butter.
Beat until color lightens.
Drop spoonfuls on wax paper.

title: pumpkin cheese cake
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and 1 tablespoon milk in a bowl with a wire whisk, until smooth.
Stir in whipped topping.
Spread on bottom crust.
Refrigerate.
Pour milk and pumpkin in bowl and mix in pudding with wire whisk until thickened.
Stir in pumpkin and spices with wire whisk and mix well.
Spread over cream cheese layer; distribute evenly.
Refrigerate 3 hours before serving.

title: dessert pancakes
directions: Mix flour, sugar, butter, milk and eggs together.
Add just enough water to be able to pour batter.
In a nonstick pan, pour batter, 1/4 cup per pancake.
Cook at 350° until bubbles form. Turn and cook until second side is brown.

title: beignets(fast, easy, drop doughnuts)
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, heat water, butter, sugar and salt until boiling.
Remove from heat and add flour all at once.
With wooden spoon, stir ingredients until fully combined and mixture leaves sides of pan and forms a small ball.
Add eggs, one at a time, until smooth and glossy.

title: green chile enchiladas
directions: Cook beef and garlic in a skillet, stirring until crumbled and no longer pink. Remove from heat. Drain. Stir in shredded cheese and onion; set aside. Heat the next 3 ingredients in a saucepan over medium heat. Stir until melted. Stir in chiles and pimento. Spoon about 1/3 cup meat mixture onto tortilla; roll up tightly and place in a lightly greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Top with cheese sauce. Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes. Uncover and bake 10 more minutes.

title: chicken casserole from aunt thelma
directions: Grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix chicken, cream of chicken soup, mayo, lemon juice and curry powder.
Blanch for 5 minutes the broccoli, carrots and cauliflower.
Drain, then add to chicken mixture.
Melt Velveeta cheese and mix with corn flake crumbs, parsley flakes and melted butter and spread over chicken mixture already in pan.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: applesauce nut cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan until moistened, then stir vigorously with fork for 1 minute.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes.
Store in cool place.

title: wheat germ cookies
directions: Mix altogether and spread on greased 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until bubbly.
While still warm, cut in bars and remove from pan.
(Don't let them harden in pan.)

title: percolator punch
directions: Pour liquids into percolator.
Set basket with other ingredients into percolator.
Perk until ready.
Makes a great warm holiday punch.

title: black bean soup
directions: Cover beans in 2-inches of water and soak overnight.
Drain. Rinse.
Add all other ingredients, except sour cream.
Add just enough water to cover by 1-inch.
Bring beans to a low simmer for 2 hours or until tender.
Do not boil.

title: sour cream substitute
directions: Mix together milk and cold water.
Blend mixture with cottage cheese, lemon juice and salt.
Keep refrigerated.
Contains 1/2 the calories of sour cream.

title: kool-aid punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid, sugar and water; stir until dissolved.
Stir in pineapple juice.
Put in a 4-quart covered container.
Freeze for several hours or overnight.
When ready to serve, partially thaw; chop with vegetable chopper.
Add ginger ale.
Should be the consistency of a slush.
Pour into punch bowl.
Use Kool-Aid in the color you want your punch to be.
Serves about 25.

title: stuffed french bread
directions: Split French loaf; remove bread and crumble it.
Chop pepper and onion.
Mix cheese and soup in pan to melt.
Cook ground beef, onion and pepper; drain.
Mix all together and stuff into bread. Wrap loaf in foil.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes until warm.

title: instant spice tea
directions: Mix all ingredients and store in airtight container.
Use 2 teaspoons to 1 cup boiling water.

title: chinese rice casserole
directions: Brown meats with onion, celery and bell pepper.
Add all other ingredients except soy sauce and simmer 20 minutes, then add 1/2 cup water and 1/4 cup soy sauce.
Stir well.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Saute onion and pepper in oleo.
Add mushroom soup, chicken broth, pimento and chicken.
Cook slowly until heated thoroughly. Cook spaghetti until tender.
Put layer of spaghetti, layer of sauce, top with Parmesan cheese and grated cheese.
Layer to the top of the dish.
Bake about 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Spray pan with nonstick spray.
Sprinkle with brown sugar. Arrange sliced pineapple and cherries in pan on top of brown sugar.

title: italian-style pork soup
directions: Brown pork pieces in oil with onion and garlic.
Pour off drippings.
Sprinkle Italian seasoning, salt, basil, fennel and pepper over pork.
Add tomatoes and water; cover tightly and simmer 1 hour.
Add green pepper, zucchini and pasta to pork.
Increase heat to medium-low and continue cooking, covered, 30 minutes or until vegetables and pasta are done.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: yum yum cake
directions: Bake the cake mix, mixed with the eggs and pineapple juice, in a low, flat pan.
Cool cake.
Mix the pudding with the cream cheese, milk and crushed pineapple.
Spread on cake.
Top with the Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with toasted coconut and cherries.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Brown hamburger with onion; drain fat and place in 4-quart saucepan.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 2 hours.
Add salt as desired.

title: bob's chili
directions: Fry turkey meat and drain.
Add all other ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Then simmer for 2 hours.

title: chuckwagon slaw
directions: In large bowl, combine salad dressing and seasonings.
Add cabbage and seasonings.
Add cabbage and beans, mixing lightly but thoroughly.
Cover and chill to blend flavors.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except mushroom caps and 2 cans soup; place in a large casserole.
Place rolls on top of casserole. Bake at 350° until light golden brown.
Mix mushroom caps and soup.
Heat and pour over individual servings.
Complete meal with salad.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix
all
ingredients.	Cook
5 minutes.
Keep hot over barbecue
pit.
Tie piece of clean cloth on fork and dab sauce on meat while cooking.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill and make into ball. Serve with assorted crackers.

title: chicken salad in toast cups
directions: Thoroughly mix all ingredients, except bread and butter. Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut out 30 (2-inch) rounds of bread. Brush both sides with melted butter; press into 1 3/4-inch muffin pans.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes or until golden around edges.
Cool. Fill each little cup with about 1 1/2 teaspoons chicken salad filling.

title: cukes and cream
directions: Combine cucumbers, radishes and onions in large bowl. Cover and refrigerate 1 to 2 hours.

title: corn and rice casserole
directions: Cook yellow rice as on the package directions.
Add margarine. Put in spices to your taste preference.
Add the can of Mexicorn, adding the liquid also (do not drain).
Mix well.
Then add can of cream of celery soup.
Mix well.
Put in oven at 350° and bake for 35 to 45 minutes, until it is heated thoroughly.
Add the package of grated cheese on top of this and place back in the oven until the cheese has bubbled on top.

title: unbelievable cheesecake
directions: In a large mixing bowl, beat together the cream cheese, sugar, lemon rind and lemon juice until the mixture is light and fluffy. Drain the mandarin oranges, saving the fruit and 1/2 cup of the juice.
In a small saucepan over medium heat, add the milk. Carefully add the egg yolks, stirring constantly.
Bring to a boil, then remove from the heat.
Slowly beat the gelatin mixture into the cheese mixture.
Stir in the sour cream.
Beat the egg whites until they form soft peaks, then fold them into the cheese mixture. Arrange half the orange segments on the crust in a 9-inch spring-form pan.
Pour the batter over the oranges.
Refrigerate the cake for 4 hours or until set.
Top the cake with whipped cream and the remaining orange segments.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar. Add eggs and beat until fluffy. Blend into dry ingredients and bananas.
Add nuts.
Bake in loaf pan 1 hour at 350°.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef.
Drain.
Add spaghetti sauce and stir.
Let simmer.
Cook noodles.
Drain.
In greased 9 x 13-inch pan, spread sauce over pan.
Put layer of noodles over sauce.
Put another layer of sauce over noodles.
Sprinkle cheese over sauce.
Repeat layers until you run out of noodles or sauce.
Cover completely with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Serve.

title: cranberry sauce with raspberry vinegar
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in heavy medium saucepan over medium-high heat.
Bring to boil, stirring until sugar dissolves. Mix in cranberries, cinnamon stick and orange peel.
Reduce heat, cover partially and simmer until berries burst, about 10 minutes. Remove from heat and cool completely.
Discard cinnamon stick. Cover and chill.

title: fried banana peppers
directions: Split peppers and remove seeds.
Beat egg with milk.
Dip peppers in egg and milk and roll in flour, seasoned with salt and pepper.
Dip again in egg and milk and back into flour.
Fry in deep fat at 360° until golden brown.
Serve at once.

title: pecan kisses
directions: Beat 1 egg white until it stands in peaks.
Mix brown sugar in egg whites and vanilla.
Stir in pecan halves until each pecan half is covered with mixture.
Place each pecan 1 inch apart on cookie sheet and bake 30 minutes in 250° oven.

title: s'mores
directions: Place marshmallow on Hershey candy bar between graham crackers.
Heat in oven or microwave until marshmallow and candy are slightly melted.

title: ham casserole
directions: Mix and pour into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cover with foil. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: chocolate mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix flour, cocoa, baking soda and baking powder; set aside. Mix eggs, sugar and vanilla for 3 minutes or until smooth and creamy.
Reduce speed to low.
Beat in mayonnaise until blended. Add flour in 4 additions with water.
Bake in 2 (9-inch) pans for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: freezer slaw
directions: Sprinkle cabbage with salt.
Let stand 1 hour.
Add celery and green pepper.
Let stand 20 minutes.
Drain well.
Combine water, sugar, vinegar, celery and mustard seed.
Bring to a boil.
Pour over cabbage mixture.
Mix well.
Cool and put in containers. Seal and freeze.

title: golden punch
directions: Mix jello according to directions on the box.
Mix orange juice according to directions on can.
Mix pineapple juice according to directions.
Mix all this together; add water and sugar.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: chili beans
directions: Brown hamburger; drain grease.
Put hamburger back into pan. Add chopped onion and pepper.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook on high for about 20 minutes, stirring frequently.
Let simmer about 15 or 20 more minutes or until onions and pepper are done.
Put into bowls and top with grated Cheddar cheese, if desired.

title: curry glazed chicken
directions: Melt butter and other ingredients in shallow baking pan.
Roll chicken in mixture, covering completely.
Place chicken, skin side up, in pan and bake for 1 hour at 375°.

title: frozen salad
directions: In a large bowl, mix marshmallows, pineapple with juice, and cherries.
Let stand several hours, in refrigerator, stirring occassionnaly.Whip cream and mix together rest of ingredients, combine all, mix well.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together; salt and pepper to taste.
Pour into a greased casserole dish and bake at 325° for 45 minutes. Sprinkle more grated cheese and cracker crumbs on top, if desired.

title: tutti frutti cookies
directions: Mix and let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Make into 1/2 teaspoon rounded small balls.
Bake at 350° for 13 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: no-fat snack mix
directions: In large bowl, combine cereals and pretzels.
Mix dill weed and ranch dressing mix (dry) and shake over cereal mixture.
Mix thoroughly.
Spray with Pam until snacks are moistened, then stir, then spray again, alternating until snacks are well coated with the dry seasoning mixture.
Pour into paper bag, shake every 15 minutes for 2 hours, then it's ready to munch!

title: never-fail seafood souffle
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Generously butter 1 or 1 1/2-quart souffle dish or straight-sided casserole; set aside.

title: mrs. zackery taylor's hickory nut cake
directions: Grease 8 1/4-inch tube pan and flour it.
Cream butter with 1 cup sugar.
Beat egg yolks until light.
Then fold in lemon juice and combine with creamed mixture.
Sift in dry ingredients with milk.
Stir in nuts and flavoring.
Beat egg whites but not dry. Fold in lightly.
Pour into cake pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: prawns lejon
directions: Saute green onion, yellow onion, parsley and prawns in the butter.
Flame with brandy and add the rest of the ingredients and simmer for one minute.
Serve as a first course of entree.

title: corn relish
directions: Blanch corn 2 minutes before cutting off cob.
Drop into cold water.
Chop cabbage and peppers, then cook all together for 20 minutes.
Pack in jars.
Put in water bath for 25 minutes.

title: italian spedini
directions: Brown ground round and sausage; drain well and set aside.
In heavy skillet, brown in 1/2 stick butter the bread crumbs.
Add sausage and ground round to bread crumbs and mix well.
Turn off heat.
Grate (on coarse) the hard-boiled eggs.
Add to meat and crumb mixture.
Add parsley, salt, pepper and oregano.
Add Mozzarella cheese, Parmesan cheese and Romano cheese.
Drizzle with melted butter if dry (consistency of corn meal).
Lay slices of meat flat on waxed paper and spread with bread, meat and cheese mixture.
Roll up (small end to large end) jelly roll fashion and secure with toothpicks.
Slice into 1 to 1 1/2-inch pinwheels (3 to 4 per slice of meat).
Place in shallow, lightly greased pan or dish and bake at 325° to 350° for 30 minutes until meat is brown. Make ahead and refrigerate.
Remove and bring to room temperature. Don't let meat dry out.
Drizzle with melted butter on top.
Serve with a good tomato-spaghetti sauce, heated and served separately.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Cut up cabbage with knife.
Grate small onion on top of cabbage.
Sprinkle sugar over cabbage and onions.
Pour sauce over cabbage mixture.
Refrigerate at least 4 hours.
Toss lightly just before serving.

title: egg custard
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Pour in pie shell. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Beat egg whites with 3 teaspoons sugar and put on top of pie. Chop peppermint candy and put on top egg whites. Brown top of pie.

title: homemade shake and bake coating
directions: Mix all together. Use to coat chicken.
To store, use a tightly sealed container.

title: green enchilada casserole
directions: Melt oleo and add flour.
Add milk, chilies and cheese to mixture.
Heat until all blended well.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except crackers together.
Crush crackers and use 3/4 in casserole.
Mix well.
Place in baking dish and sprinkle remaining crumbs on top.
Bake for 35 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: mush
directions: Stir cornmeal into 1 cup of cold water; set aside.
Bring 3 cups of water and salt to a boil in large saucepan.
Add cornmeal mixture to boiling water gradually, stirring constantly.
Cook for 5 to 10 minutes or until thickened, stirring frequently.
Serve with sugar or milk or chill in pan; slice and fry.

title: dijon baked chicken
directions: Melt butter.
Combine mayonnaise and mustard.
Mix together in shallow bowl.
Dip chicken in liquid, coating evenly.
Roll chicken in herb stuffing mix.
Preheat oven to 325°.
Bake, foil covered, for 70 minutes at 325°.
Bake, uncovered, an additional 10 to 20 minutes.

title: chocolate cheesecake pie
directions: Heat in heavy saucepan all but 1 square of chocolate with 1/4 cup milk until completely melted.
Beat in cream cheese, sugar and remaining milk.
Gently stir in whipped topping until smooth. Spoon into crust evenly.
Grate 1 square of chocolate.
Sprinkle over top of pie.
Freeze until set.
Let thaw at room temperature until pie can be cut.

title: bean salad
directions: Drain about half of liquid from beans.
Combine vegetables. Make a marinade of remaining ingredients.
Pour over vegetables. Refrigerate for 24 hours before serving.
Makes 12 servings.

title: 90 minute rolls
directions: Stir yeast, flour, milk, sugar and salt together.
Add margarine and water.
Mix until smooth.
Stir in 3 cups flour. Cover and let rise 15 minutes.
Turn out on floured board; knead until it doesn't stick to hands.
Pat or roll out to about 3/4-inch thickness.
Cut with glass or biscuit cutter.
Put on greased cookie sheet.
Let rise 15 minutes.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: lime salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water, then mix in cream and mayonnaise well. Add rest of ingredients and stir well. Set in the refrigerator until congealed, 2 to 3 hours.

title: mint-cranberry tea
directions: Fill ice cube trays with cranberry juice.
Freeze until solid, about 3 hours or overnight.
For tea, bring 1 quart water to full boil.
In heatproof bowl or pitcher, pour boiling water over tea. Let stand 5 minutes, until desired strength.
Remove tea bags; discard.
Add mint sprigs and lemon peel strips.
Chill 1 hour. Strain and discard mint and lemon peel.

title: candied citrus peel
directions: Recipe can be doubled,
tripled, etc.,
depending on how much rind you have.
Grate rind slightly to release oil from cells. Cut into thin strips and place in heavy pan.
Cover fruit the 1 1/2 cups water.
Bring slowly to the boiling point.
Simmer ten minutes or longer to remove bitter taste.
Drain and repeat this process at least three times, draining well after each time.

title: peanut butter cup tarts
directions: Combine margarine, sugars, egg, vanilla and peanut butter. Add dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Form small balls.
Spray small tart size muffin tins.
Place 1 ball in each tin.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Let stand about 1 minute.
When removed from oven, place 1 miniature Reese's cup on center of each tart. Remove from tins in 15 minutes.

title: turkey hawaiian(an excellent way to use leftover turkey)
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice; add water to juice to make 1 cup.
In large saucepan, combine juice mixture, broth, peas, mushrooms, celery, onion and soy sauce; bring to boiling.
Cover; simmer for 5 minutes.
Blend cornstarch with 3 tablespoons cold water; add to saucepan.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly. Cut up pineapple.
Stir pineapple, turkey and water chestnuts into saucepan; heat through.
Serve over hot cooked rice.
Serves 8.

title: millionaires candy
directions: Melt caramels and butter in double boiler or heat in microwave for 1 minute.
Stir, then heat about another minute.
Do not heat very long at a time.
After melted, add chopped pecans.
Mix Hershey bars with paraffin in double boiler.
Do not heat in microwave.
Dip candy and place on buttered wax paper to cool.

title: simply delicious peanut butter bars
directions: Mix butter and peanut butter in large bowl.
Add sugars and beat.
Add eggs and milk; beat.
Sift dry ingredients and add to wet ingredients.
In 15 x 11-inch pan (jelly roll pan), spread batter.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes or lightly golden brown.

title: three-bean salad
directions: Drain all the beans.
Toss and let stand a day or two before serving.

title: lemon sponge pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour, salt and egg yolks; beat.
Add juice and rind; stir in milk.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Bake at 420° for a few minutes, then at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: apple hill cake
directions: Mix sugar, oil and eggs.
Add apples (diced).
Sift together flour, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and baking soda.
Add to apple mixture.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Preheat oven.
Serve it hot, warm or cold.
May be eaten with Cool Whip.
Serves 8.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Cook broccoli until just tender; drain.
Beat eggs, cottage cheese and salt together.
Add mix, margarine, onion and broccoli. Bake in iron skillet or 8 1/2 x 11-inch pan for 25 minutes at 400° to a light brown.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: If using frozen vegetables, cook according to package directions, adding onions and celery during the last few minutes. Drain and mix with remaining ingredients, except crackers and margarine.
Pour into greased 9 x 14-inch casserole dish.
Mix together crackers and margarine and sprinkle over casserole.
Bake in a 350° oven until light brown and bubbly.
Serves 8 to 12.

title: ultimate butter cookie
directions: Combine first four ingredients with electrical mixer until smooth and creamy.
Gradually beat in flour.
Wrap dough in plastic wrap.
Refrigerate 1 hour or up to 2 days.
During this time the flavor blends and develops turning our buttery flavor. Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Roll our dough on lightly floured surface to 1/2 inch thickness.
Cut into desired shapes using holiday cookie cutters.
Place on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with decorating sugar (sprinkles).
Bake 1/2 hour to 1 hour.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen.

title: party pork chops
directions: Place pork in single layer in baking pan.
Place 1 onion slice topped with 1 lemon slice on center of each chop.

title: ham barbecues
directions: Combine all of the ingredients and simmer 2 hours.

title: quick pizza
directions: Preheat broiler.
On baking sheet, place toasted pita halves and spread pizza sauce over each.
Top each with half of all toppings listed.
(You can add other toppings you prefer.) Sprinkle each with cheeses and a dash of oregano on each.
Broil until cheeses melt, 1 to 2 minutes.

title: stuffed zucchini boat
directions: Cut zucchini lengthwise; do not cut off ends.
Parboil until tender; do not overcook. Scrape out pulp of zucchini.
Put in strainer to drain water.
Cook meat, onion and garlic.
Add tomato sauce and strained zucchini pulp.
Add meat mixture to zucchini boat and top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.

title: bourbon baked beans
directions: Butter or Pam spray a 2-quart baking dish.
Mix all ingredients, except pineapple and brown sugar.
Bake, uncovered, for 40 minutes after letting set for 3 hours at room temperature, then arrange drained pineapple slices over top and sprinkle tops with brown sugar.
Bake, uncovered, an additional 40 minutes. Delicious!

title: apple streusel
directions: Peel and slice apples.
Place in 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Cover apples with white sugar and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Crumble together brown sugar, oleo and flour.
Pat on top of apples and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: raspberry smoothies
directions: Place all ingredients in food processor or blender, process until smooth. Scrape down sides as needed. Serve immediately.

title: hashed brown potatoes
directions: Cut salt pork in small cubes; fry out enough to make about 1/2 cup fat.
Remove meat.
Chop potatoes fine; add pepper and salt. Mix thoroughly with fat; cook 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Let stand to brown underneath.

title: seafood salad
directions: Hard-boil eggs and cook macaroni noodles.
In a large serving bowl, combine celery, peas and mayonnaise.
Chunk crabmeat (imitation crab will do) into bowl.
Peel eggs and let cool.
Boil macaroni for 8 to 9 minutes.
Drain and rinse with cold water; drain again.
Chop eggs and add eggs and macaroni with crabmeat mixture.
Add relish and stir thoroughly.
If desired, serve immediately or refrigerate for several hours before serving.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Place chicken in baking dish.
Mix jam and dressing; pour over chicken, then sprinkle with soup mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: chicken and pineapple sandwich
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine cubed chicken, pineapple, mayonnaise, green pepper and salt.
Evenly divide mixture into 4 slices of bread and spread to edges.
Top with lettuce leaves and cover with remaining 4 slices of bread.
Cut and serve.
470 calories per sandwich.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Puree 1 avocado, lime juice and garlic in a food processor. Coarsely mash 2 avocados with a fork in a bowl.
Stir in the pureed avocado, cumin, onion, pepper sauce, diced tomatoes, cilantro, and salt and pepper.
Serve immediately with tortilla chips.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine all the ingredients and blend well.
Store in a tightly covered container.
For a single serving, combine 1/4 cup mix and 3/4 cup boiling water in a cup or mug.
Stir to blend.

title: coconut fruit salad
directions: Drain fruits and mix with all other ingredients, then chill and serve.

title: chicken rotel
directions: Cook chicken in salted water. Debone and cut in large pieces. Strain and save broth. Saute onion and pepper in oleo. Add mushrooms, Ro-Tel, cheese, Worcestershire sauce, dry mustard, salt, pepper and water chestnuts. Cook vermicelli 5 minutes in chicken broth. Strain and carefully combine all ingredients. Fills 2 large casserole to serve 12 to 14. Freezes well. Cook when thawed at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream margarine in mixer bowl until light.
Add sugar, beating until fluffy.
Beat in egg yolks, one at a time.
Add flour alternately with mixture of soda and sour cream, mixing well after each addition.
Mix in flavorings.
Beat egg whites in small mixer bowl until stiff peaks form.
Fold gently into batter.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Boil first 3 ingredients together for 6 minutes; remove from heat.
Add marshmallows and peanut butter together and beat well; add vanilla last.
Beat until smooth and creamy.
Spread in buttered pan and cool.

title: chicken stuffing casserole
directions: Mix stuffing as directed on box.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan. Layer half the stuffing on the bottom, half of the chicken, can of mushroom soup, and 1 can of chicken broth.
Layer remaining chicken, can of chicken soup, 1 can of broth and the rest of the stuffing.
Cover and bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: blintze souffle
directions: Melt margarine in baking dish (9 x 13 x 2-inch).
Lay blintzes in pan frozen (not touching).
In blender, put remaining ingredients and blend.
(If you don't have a blender, a mixer is fine.)
Pour mixture over blintzes.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and/or nutmeg.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Uncover and bake an additional 1/2 hour.

title: fudge
directions: Butter an 8 or 9-inch square pan.
In a large heavy saucepan, combine sugar, cocoa powder and salt; stir in milk.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly with a wooden spoon to dissolve sugar.
Clip thermometer to side of pan, making sure bulb does not rest on bottom of pan.
Continue to cook, stirring constantly, to 234°F (112°C); mixture should boil at a moderate steady rate.
Remove from heat.
Drop in butter and vanilla; do not stir.
Cool at room temperature to 110°F (44°C), about 1 hour. Remove candy thermometer.
Beat with a wooden spoon until fudge becomes very thick and loses its gloss.
Immediately spread fudge in prepared pan.
While it is still warm, score in 1-inch squares. Cool and finish cutting.
Makes 64 pieces.

title: mushroom salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add oil and cover.

title: diabetic cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients
into
bowl
and add oil, eggs and prunes.
Mix well.	Add nuts.
Bake in a well-greased tube pan at 300° until cake springs back when lightly pressed.

title: quick fruit punch
directions: Mix well and serve cold or over ice.
Stir again if pineapple settles to bottom.

title: crab mold
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water.
Heat with 1/2 cup soup until dissolved.
Combine with other ingredients and mold.
To serve, unmold on plate and serve with crackers.

title: easy irish soda bread
directions: Melt butter and let cool off a bit.
Place all other ingredients in large bowl.
Add butter and mix by hand.
Batter will be sticky.

title: hawaiian muffins
directions: Combine muffin mix and flaked coconut.
Drain pineapple.
Add pineapple, beaten egg and 2/3 cup milk to dry ingredients.
Blend only until dry ingredients are moistened.
Fill greased muffin pans 2/3 full.
Bake in hot oven (400°) for 15 to 20 minutes or until done.

title: pistachio dessert
directions: Crush Ritz crackers and blend with melted butter.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool well.
Blend ice cream, milk and pudding.
Mix well; pour over crackers and let set.
Top with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle over that with the Heath bars.

title: chicken clarisse
directions: Place chicken in a well-greased baking dish.
Mix all other ingredients together.
Spread over chicken.
Bake uncovered for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: chocolate raspberry brownie cake
directions: In a 2 to 3-quart pan over low heat, stir butter and chocolate just until melted, about 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add in granulated sugar, pecans, eggs and vanilla.
Add flour; stir to mix ingredients well.
Spread batter in a buttered, floured 9-inch cake pan with removable rim.
Next to rim, distribute 1 cup berries in a band about 2 inches wide.
Gently press fruit into batter.
Bake at 350° until top at outside edge cracks and feels firm to touch, 45 to 50 minutes.
Let Brownie cool in pan on a rack.
If made ahead, chill airtight up to 1 day.

title: chocolate crackles
directions: Melt chocolate.
Blend in oil and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat well after each addition.
Add vanilla.
Add flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir into chocolate mixture.
Chill dough several hours.
Drop teaspoonfuls of dough into powdered sugar. Roll around and shape into small balls.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Yields 6 dozen.

title: rhubarb jam
directions: Combine rhubarb and sugar.
Let set overnight.
In the morning, cook until tender (simmer).
Remove from heat and add jello.
Fill sterilized jars and seal.

title: shake and bake
directions: Mix dry ingredients and cut in shortening.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Wash chicken and pat dry.
Remove giblets and neck.
Wash and dry.
Place chicken in a large Dutch oven or 8-quart pot.
Add vegetables, herbs, pepper and water to cover.
Remove giblets after one hour.
Cool and refrigerate.
Bring water to a boil; lower heat to simmer and cover chicken.
Cook about 2 1/2 to 3 1/2 hours until thick portions are fork-tender.
Remove chicken and strain liquid through sieve, reserving the liquid.
Cool chicken completely; cool and refrigerate the liquid.
When chicken is cool enough to remove meat, use fork or knife to remove skin and remove meat to a large container.
You should have about
5 cups of cooked chicken and 5 to 6 cups of broth.
Chicken should be refrigerated no longer than two days and the broth refrigerated no longer than one day.
Freeze separately if you don't use them immediately.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar, syrup and butter. Add eggs and pecans. Fill unbaked pie shell with mixture; bake in hot oven (400°) for 10 minutes. Reduce heat to moderate (350°) for 30 to 35 minutes or until pie is firm in middle.

title: cranberry crunch squares
directions: Cut butter into mixture until crumbly.
Place 1/2 of mixture into an 8-inch square baking pan.
Cover this with 1 can cranberries (whole or sauce).
Spread remainder of oatmeal mixture over the top.
Bake 45 minutes in a 350° oven.
Can be made ahead of time and then heat in oven for a few minutes.
Cut into squares when cool.
Delicious with ice cream.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a large skillet, cook beef until brown.
With slotted spoon, remove beef from skillet.
Pour off all but 1 tablespoon drippings.
Add celery, onion and garlic.
Cook for 4 minutes or until soft while stirring.
Return beef to skillet.
Add tomato sauce, cooked rice, whole kernel corn, tomato paste, basil, Italian seasoning salt and pepper; stir until blended.
Spoon half of mixture into bottom of an 8-inch square baking dish.
Arrange half of the cheese slices over the top. Repeat layers.
Place tomatoes on top.
Bake 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Serves 4.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Mix soup, mayonnaise, cheese and eggs together.
Arrange alternate layers of broccoli, sauce and chicken, ending with sauce in a casserole dish.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Ten minutes before done, cover with bread crumbs or crumbled potato chips.

title: mrs. garnett's icicle pickles
directions: Love even the most unlovely part of yourself.

title: sweet and sour dill pickles
directions: Bring to a boil.
While boiling, in jars put dill or 1 teaspoon of dill seed, 1/4 teaspoon alum, 1/4 teaspoon turmeric and 1 garlic pod.
Pack jar with icicle pickle strips.
Cover with boiling brine.
Put on hot lids.
Hot water bath for 5 minutes.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients.
Pour in greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle bread crumbs over.
Drizzle the melted oleo over crumbs.
Bake at 350° about 35 to 40 minutes.

title: lemon balls
directions: Blend the first 3 ingredients together and form into balls. Roll in powdered sugar.
Bake at 350° until lightly brown.

title: cracker candy
directions: Place saltines, side by side, on a foil-covered cookie sheet. Bring butter and brown sugar to a boil; boil 3 minutes.
Spread mixture over crackers.
Bake 5 minutes at 400°.
Sprinkle morsels over baked crackers; let stand 5 minutes.
Spread evenly. Refrigerate until hard.
Remove foil; break into pieces.
Makes 2 dozen pieces.

title: party franks
directions: In a saucepan, saute onion in oil until tender. Stir in the next 11 ingredients. Add lemon. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered for 20 to 25 minutes or until slightly thickened, stirring occasionally. Discard lemon slices. Place hot dogs in a 13 x 9 x 2 inch baking dish. Top with sauce. Bake uncovered at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes or until heated through. Keep warm, serve with tooth picks.

title: cheese and macaroni casserole
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Add all ingredients together and mix with macaroni, except cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hot buttered cranberry punch
directions: Crush cranberry sauce in a saucepan with fork; mix in sugar, spices and salt.
Add water gradually, beating until smooth with beater.
Stir in pineapple juice.
Heat to boiling point; reduce heat and simmer for 5 minutes.
Pour into punch cups; float a pat of butter in each cup.
Yield:
6 cups.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve strawberry Jell-O in boiling water.
Add cranberry sauce and whisk together.
Add apples.
Add the pineapple with juice.
Mix together and refrigerate overnight.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Wash the sweet potatoes.
Prick each one.
Arrange in a casserole bowl 1-inch apart.
Peel; slice the potatoes.
Add 1/4 cup brown sugar, 1/4 cup butter and salt.
Mash until no lumps remain.
Mix in the pineapple; set.
Place 1 tablespoon brown sugar, 1 tablespoon butter, water, cinnamon and nutmeg in medium bowl.
Melt butter; add the marshmallows; toss to coat.
Top the sweet potatoes with marshmallows.
When all is cooked and melted, top with pecans.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pealing bells
directions: Combine flour and baking powder.
In a large mixer bowl, beat butter and shortening until butter is softened.
Add sugar and beat until fluffy.
Add egg, milk, orange peel and vanilla and beat well.
Add flour mixture and beat until well mixed.
Cover and chill about 30 minutes or until easy to handle.
Shape into two 8-inch rolls.
Wrap and chill for several hours or overnight.
Cut into 1/4-inch slices.
Place on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Place a cherry on the bottom half of each slice for bell clapper.
Fold in sides of slice, overlapping at top and slightly covering cherry. Pinch in sides to resemble bell shape.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 14 minutes.

title: caramel cake
directions: Cream butter and add milk or warm water.
After sifting flour 4 times, mix baking powder with it and sift into cake.
After thoroughly beating, fold in well-beaten egg whites.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla.

title: casserole for leftover turkey and stuffing
directions: Sprinkle cheese in pie shell, then ham and onions.
Beat eggs, half and half and seasoning to blend.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake on lowest rack in preheated oven at 350° for about 10 minutes or until knife inserted halfway between edge and center of pie comes out clean.
Let stand about 10 minutes before serving.

title: os good pie(makes 2 pies)
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Beat egg yolks and whites separately; mix together.
Stir lightly with sugar and butter, then add vinegar and raisins.
Pour into unbaked pie shells.
Bake about 35 minutes or until set, in 350° oven.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: watergate salad
directions: Put Cool Whip in large bowl.
Add pineapple, dry pudding mix, nuts and marshmallows.
Mix well; cool in refrigerator for few hours before serving.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix cake and tidbits and pour into 9 x 13 pan. Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°. Top with fat-free Cool Whip. Makes 12 servings.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together well in a large bowl.
Grease a large deep skillet.
Pour 1/2 of batter into the skillet. Sprinkle 1 cup grated cheese; then top with remaining batter. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: potato salad nicoise
directions: Cut potatoes in half unless they are larger, then cut them into quarters. Boil potatoes until tender, but do not overcook. Cook green beans until barely tender. Let the cooked vegetables cool while preparing the rest of the salad.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Beat 2 minutes.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for one hour or until done. While loaves are still hot in pans, drizzle glaze over top. Remove from pans and cool.

title: sauerkraut hot dish
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix together. Pour into large casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, covered, and 20 minutes uncovered.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees.
Mix shortening, margarine, sugar and eggs thoroughly.
Mix flour, soda and cream of tartar to shortening mixture.
Roll into balls the size of walnuts.
Roll balls in 2 tablespoons sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon. Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet and bake 8-10 minutes.

title: eclair dessert
directions: Line a 9 x 13-inch baking dish with graham crackers.

title: cucumber sauce
directions: Cut 1 medium unpared cucumber in half lengthwise. Scoop out seeds; shred enough cucumber to make 1 cup.
Do not drain. Combine with the sour cream, mayo, parsley, onion, vinegar, salt and pepper.
Blend.
Chill.
Serve with fish.

title: zucchini mexican style
directions: Saute zucchini, celery, carrot, onion and green pepper in hot oil in large skillet for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in the taco sauce, mustard, basil, salt and pepper.
Add tomatoes and cook 5 minutes.
Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Put 3 cups sugar over ground cranberries.
Let stand 3 hours. Mix jello according to package directions.
Add fruit, celery, nuts and cranberries.
Chill until set.

title: skillet pork chops
directions: Trim excess fat from the pork chops.
Heat this fat in skillet until you have about 2 tablespoons of drippings; remove trimmings. Coat chops with flour; brown slowly on both sides in hot fat. Combine the cheese, salt and pepper.
Sprinkle 2 tablespoons of the mixture over the meat.
Cover with potatoes.
Sprinkle with 2 tablespoons more of the cheese mixture.
Add the onions.
Dissolve the bouillon cubes in hot water; add the lemon juice and pour over all.
Sprinkle with the remaining cheese mixture.
Cover; simmer about 40 minutes until meat and vegetables are done.
Garnish with parsley; serve with green beans and applesauce.
Serves 4.

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes as usual for mashing.
When done, combine all ingredients and whip, using as little milk as possible.
Mound in casserole and refrigerate overnight.
Remove from refrigerator 3 to 4 hours before baking.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Mix all ingredients except oleo.
Melt oleo in bottom of 8-inch pan.
Pour in batter.
Pour fruit over batter.
Bake at 350° until batter has risen over fruit and is golden brown.
Sprinkle with spice mixed with sugar (cinnamon for apple, clove for peach, etc.).

title: apple bread
directions: Mix the oil, sugar, eggs and vanilla together.
Add salt, soda, flour, cinnamon, apples and nuts. Grease 2 loaf pans.
Add mixture. Sprinkle top with extra cinnamon and sugar.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: mint tea refresher
directions: Bring water to a boil.
Add tea bags and steep for 5 minutes. Remove tea bags and add sugar and mint.
Let cool.
Remove mint and add lemon juice and orange juice.
When ready to serve, pour equal parts ginger ale to tea.

title: cherry dump cake
directions: Pour 1 can crushed pineapple and 1 can cherry pie filling in pan; mix well, then pour cake mix over top.
Melt butter and pour over cake mix, then sprinkle coconut and nuts over top.
Place in oven at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: five cup salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill for 24 hours before serving.

title: tomato soup french dressing
directions: Makes about 3 cups.

title: fantasy fudge
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and milk in large saucepan.
Bring to rapid boil.
Boil 5 minutes, stirring constantly to prevent scorching.
Remove from heat, stir in chocolate chips, vanilla, marshmallow cream.
Add nuts if desired.
Pour into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: grandma's sugar cookies
directions: Sift dry ingredients together, then cut together with butter as if you were making a pie crust.
Beat eggs; add sugar and vanilla.
Add to flour mixture and blend well.
Roll then on floured board and cut with cookie cutter.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet until slightly brown.

title: spiced tea mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Use 3 teaspoons mix per 6 ounces of hot water.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Blend all ingredients thoroughly.
Use as basting sauce on pork or chicken.
Yields about 1 1/2 cups.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 10-inch tube pan.
In a large mixing bowl, sift together flour, sugar, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir until mixed.
Do not beat.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes or until done.
Let cool.
Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: hash brown bake
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cornflake crumbs and some cheese. Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with reserved cheese and crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 60 minutes, uncovered.

title: pantry cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 325 degrees.

title: banana split salad
directions: Drain pineapple, saving 1/2 of juice.
Set aside.
In a saucepan, boil water, all jello and marshmallows.
Stir until dissolved.
Chill until partially set.

title: ralph coy burba, sr.  original doughnut recipe
directions: Combine water, salt, 1/2 lb. flour in large saucepan and bring to a boil.
Then beat into mixture 1 3/4 lb. flour.
Next beat in eggs, adding 2 or 3 at a time.
Cook in hot deep grease.
Ice with any kind of icing.
Preferred as:
chocolate, lemon, or plain white flavored with vanilla.

title: peanut butter rice krispies
directions: Melt butterscotch morsels with the peanut butter in heavy skillet, stirring until well blended.
Add cereal.
Press into buttered pan and chill.

title: chocolate butterfinger truffle
directions: Crumble 1/2 chocolate cake into bottom of truffle bowl.
Pour 1/2 cup of coffee over cake to moisten.
Put 1/2 of chocolate pudding over cake.
Put 1/2 of Cool Whip over pudding.
Put crumbled Butterfinger over Cool Whip.
Repeat sequence of layers. Chill for 4 hours.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Mix rhubarb, sugar, water and flour.
Bring to boil.
Add beaten egg yolks and return to boil.
Remove from heat and add extract.
Cool, then pour into baked pie crust.
Beat egg whites; add 4 tablespoons sugar and beat again.
Put on top of pie, then brown top in oven.

title: celery seed dressing
directions: Sift first 5 ingredients together and then stir in the vinegar.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until slightly thick.
Then add lemon juice and cool.
Beat salad oil in slowly and add the onion juice and celery seed.
Stir well before using.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Put hamburger barbecue mixture in a large ovenproof casserole or 2 (8 or 9-inch) cake pans.
Cover surface with your favorite cheese slices.
Top with the biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: shortbread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Rub in margarine.
Mix in egg and knead well.
Roll 1/2-inch thick.
Prick with a fork and cut into rounds or slices.

title: christmas pumpkin bread
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients.
Then add remaining ingredients.
Grease and flour 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: corn bread muffins
directions: Sift flour, measure and sift again with corn meal, baking powder, sugar and salt.
Beat egg slightly, add milk and shortening.
Combine with dry ingredients, stirring only until moist.
Pour into well-greased square pan (8 x 8 x 2-inches). Bake in moderately hot oven (425°) for 30 minutes or until done.

title: banana cream trifle
directions: Prepare pudding and pie filling in large bowl as directed on package for pudding, using 2 c. milk. Layer half of the bread cubes, pudding, banana slices and whipped topping in 2 quart serving bowl. Repeat with remaining ingredients. Cover and refrigerate until serving time but no longer than 24 hours. Cover and refrigerate any remaining dessert.

title: rice pudding
directions: Cook rice.
Remove from stove and add margarine, mixing well, then add sugar, milk, eggs and vanilla.
Pour in a large casserole dish and cook in oven at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: golden layer cake
directions: Mix all but eggs for 2 minutes, then add eggs.
Beat 2 more minutes.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: easy potato bake
directions: Mix all ingredients together; pour into large baking dish. Cover with foil.
Bake 1 hour, remove foil and bake 30 minutes more.
Bake at 350°.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: baked scampi
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place shrimp in large roasting pan. Melt butter/margarine in pan; add pepper and garlic.
Stir in lemon juice and salad dressing.
Pour mixture over shrimp and bake, covered, for 45 minutes.
Stir once or twice while cooking.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Cook sausage and drain.
Combine remaining ingredients in a large bowl and stir.
Add sausage.
Pour into a greased dish. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: pat's easy stew recipe
directions: Mix all the ingredients together in a big, covered Dutch oven. Cover and bake in the oven at 275° for 5 or 6 hours.
Do not open the lid while cooking.

title: spicy biscuit balls
directions: Melt cheese in top of a double boiler.
Add sausage.
Stir until sausage is thoroughly cooked.
Add to biscuit mix; blend well.
Form into 1-inch balls.
Bake in a 450° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 3 to 4 dozen.

title: easy cheese ball
directions: Blend cream cheese, ham, sauce, garlic salt and Cheddar cheese.
Roll into ball and roll in extra cheese or nuts.
Chill. Serve with crackers.

title: cheese cookies
directions: Cream the cheese and butter together.
Add flour and salt and mix until dough is smooth and well blended.
Shape dough into rolls, about 1-inch in diameter.
Chill 2 hours, until dough is firm.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Slice the dough into thin rounds. Place on ungreased baking sheets at least 1-inch apart.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes about 8 dozen.

title: pinch bread
directions: Mix sugar and cinnamon together.
Pinch pieces of biscuit off and coat in cinnamon sugar mixture.
Place in a tube pan sprayed with Pam.
Pour melted butter over pieces.
Bake in 375° oven for 25 minutes or until brown.

title: buttermilk fudge cake
directions: Bring to a boil, water, shortening and margarine.
Sift together flour, sugar and cocoa.
Pour boiling mixture over dry ingredients.
Add buttermilk, eggs, soda, salt and vanilla.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake in preheated 400° oven for 40 minutes.

title: potato salad i
directions: Mix dressing ingredients and pour over potatoes, onion, eggs and celery.
Let set 2 hours in refrigerator before serving.

title: company green beans
directions: Saute slightly the onion and parsley in 2 tablespoons butter. Add flour, salt and lemon peel.
Blend.
Remove from heat and add sour cream, cheese, beans and water chestnuts.
Place in a 2-quart casserole.
Mix 2 tablespoons melted butter with cracker crumbs and spread over top of mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: four fold delight
directions: 1st Layer:
Mix together plain flour, margarine and chopped nuts.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°. Cool.

title: no crust egg pie
directions: In a large bowl, mix marshmallows in warm milk, add remaining ingredients and mix well. Pour into well greased 10-inch deep dish pie plate. Bake at 325 degrees for 45 minutes or until firm. This pie forms its own crust.

title: reese's chewy chocolate cookies
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla; mix well.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt. Gradually blend into cream mixture and mix well.
Stir in peanut butter chips.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 8 to 9 minutes.
Do not overbake!

title: pineapple cheese dip
directions: Mix cream cheese, sour cream and pineapple in a medium sized mixing bowl using hand beaters.
Place the cream cheese mixture into a serving bowl and microwave on high for 1 to 2 minutes or until warm.
Arrange the rest of the ingredients on a platter with the dip in the center.

title: stove top macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni for 4.
Drain.
Put back on stove.
Add cheese and milk to cover halfway up to macaroni.
Add salt and pepper. Cook on medium heat until cheese melts.
Serve.

title: caribbean flambeed pineapple
directions: *Canned rings can be substituted.

title: scalloped ham with asparagus
directions: Combine ham, asparagus, onions and rice.
Blend eggs, soup, milk, mayonnaise and seasonings.
Stir into ham mixture.
Turn into greased shallow 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: snow-capped grapefruit
directions: Loosen segments, remove center core and pour off juice. Sprinkle with powdered sugar and sherry.
Chill several hours.

title: barbecued hamburgers
directions: Soak corn flakes in milk until soft and drain excess milk out. Mix corn flakes, ground beef, allspice, chopped onion and tomato catsup all together (salt and pepper to taste).
Roll out in patties and fry until brown.
Lift hamburgers out of grease and brown 1 tablespoon flour in grease.

title: mom's golden potato salad
directions: Blend mayonnaise or salad dressing with mustard and vinegar. Add salt and pepper, onion, potatoes and eggs.
Mix well and chill.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: california fruit plate
directions: Place 1/2 cup cottage cheese on each of 4 salad plates. Surround cottage cheese with 8 quarters of figs; sprinkle raspberries over figs.
Drizzle honey over fruit and cottage cheese.
Squeeze lemon over all.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook the first 4 ingredients to soft ball stage (235°). Remove from heat.
Add the peanut butter and vanilla; stir until it starts to thicken.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: turnip souffle
directions: Cook turnips, drain and mash.
Add all other ingredients. Sprinkle bread crumbs on top.
Add paprika.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes, until bubbly and brown.

title: watermelon muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Sift flour, baking powder, soda, cinnamon and salt in a large bowl.
Cream butter and sugar; add eggs.
Whip in milk, juice, pulp and raisins.
Add wet mixture to dry ingredients and blend to moisten dry ingredients.
Fill greased muffin cups 2/3 full, bake approximately 25 minutes. Transfer to wire rack to cool.

title: susan kazin's chicken soup
directions: Put ingredients in an enamel pot.
Simmer for about 2 to 3 hours.
Skim off foam occasionally.
When vegetables are soft, remove vegetables.
Then refrigerate soup, covered, for at least 6 hours.
Fat will rise to the top and form a thin layer.
Remove this thin layer.

title: vinaigrette dressing
directions: Mix, blend and chill all ingredients.

title: frozen hot fudge sundae dessert
directions: Heat together all but last three ingredients.
Bring to a boil and cook 4 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Add 1 teaspoon of vanilla and set aside to cool.

title: cheesy chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken until done; take off bones and cut up into bite size pieces.
Cook broccoli about 7 minutes after it begins to boil.
Mix milk and soup together.
Prepare Stove Top stuffing according to package.
Place cooked broccoli on the bottom of an 8-inch casserole dish.
Put cut up, cooked chicken on top of broccoli.
Then sprinkle Mozzarella cheese on top of chicken; soup mixture on top of cheese.
Top it off with prepared stuffing. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: ma ma jean's russian tea
directions: If you can't find lemon juice you can use frozen lemonade. Dilute the orange juice as directed on can.
Simmer cloves, cinnamon and sugar 20 minutes in a quart of water.
Fix tea bags as you would to make tea.
Add juices and other ingredients and simmer.
May be served hot or cold.
Crock-pot is good to steep tea while serving hot.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Start with layer 1, topping with layer 2 through 6 as follows: layer 1 (torn lettuce); layer 2 (chopped celery); layer 3 (chopped green onion); layer 4 (salad dressing); layer 5 (sugar) and layer 6 (Cheddar cheese).
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Add layer 7 (crumbled bacon); toss and serve.

title: frozen strawberry yogurt pie
directions: Fold yogurt into whipped topping; blend well.
Fold in strawberries; spoon into crust.
Freeze until firm, 4 hours or overnight.
Garnish with additional whole strawberries, if desired.
Let stand at room temperature for 10 minutes before serving.

title: double chocolate crunch bars
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Stir flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt in creamed mixture.
Spread mixture in bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle marshmallows over hot brownies.
Bake 3 minutes more and cool.
Combine chocolate chips and peanut butter. Heat until chips melt.
Stir in cereal.
Spread on cooled bars. Cool before serving.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Beat cream cheese and sugar together. Mix together in large bowl. Combine fruit mixture with whipped topping and add to cheese mixture. Spoon into loaf pan or ring molds. Freeze overnight or longer. Serve frozen.

title: fried okra salad
directions: Fry okra; drain and cool.
Dice tomatoes and onions (include green tops).
Just before serving, mix all ingredients together. Serves 4 to 6.

title: southern collard greens
directions: Pull or cut stems from collard leaves.
Place leaves in container to wash real good.
Look for insects and discard any yellow leaves.
In large boiler, cut up ham hock or bacon and boil in water for 15 or 20 minutes.
Add well washed collard leaves. Cook for about 1 1/2 hours.
Check to see if leaves are tender. Pour approximately 1/2 cup oil or bacon grease over greens, continue cooking until tender.
Season to taste with small amount of sugar (if desired), approximately 1 tablespoon.

title: brown rice
directions: Put rice in casserole dish.
Stir in soups.
Put pats of butter around on top.
Cover dish with tinfoil, shiny side down. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Combine cream cheese and mayo.
Add celery, lemon juice, green onion and shrimp.
Mix and chill.
Serve with crackers.

title: lemon souffle
directions: Mix sugar, flour and rind.
Beat egg yolks and milk.
Add to sugar mixture. Then add lemon
juice.
Beat egg whites very stiff and fold into liquid mixture very carefully.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan and bake in a tray of water until brown at 350°.
Cool and keep in refrigerator at all times.

title: grandma's chili
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Add kidney beans, juice and all. (If your family is not crazy about kidney beans, you should mash or puree them.)
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook slowly for 1 1/2 to 2 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: beef chowder
directions: Brown beef, onion, pepper and celery.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook 30 minutes.

title: deluxe creamed chipped beef
directions: Cut beef into strips.
Melt butter in skillet.
Add beef and onion.
Cook until onion is transparent.
Blend in flour; add milk and stir constantly until mixture is smooth and thickened.
Add sour cream, cheese, mushrooms and parsley and blend well.
No salt is necessary.
Serve over toast points.

title: barbecued venison
directions: Tenderize steaks with meat hammer.
(Use meat tenderizer if desired according to directions.)
Brown steaks in frying pan with extra oil as required.
Set in small roasting pan and set aside.

title: chow mein noodle candy
directions: Melt butterscotch on stove or in microwave.
Add noodles and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper.
Let dry.
Keep in airtight container.

title: miracle pound cake
directions: Cream
Crisco and margarine.
Add sugar and cream well. Add 1/2 flour and 1/2 milk, alternating and mixing well.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add remaining	flour and
milk,	mix well.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour in a greased	and floured tube pan.
Put in cold oven.
Bake 1 hour at
then turn oven to 350° and bake 25 minutes longer. Do not open oven until cake is done.

title: lincoln logs
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Roll into logs and eat!
Quick and easy snack!

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Add sugar, oil, vanilla, cinnamon, salt, soda and baking powder.
Add zucchini, nuts and flour.
Mix well.
Put in 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Cool.

title: "easy" coconut cake
directions: Bake cake in 9 1/2 x 11-inch cake pan.
Let cake cool.
Punch holes in top of cake with a fork.
Pour sweetened condensed milk on top of cake.
After sweetened condensed milk has soaked in the cake, top with Cool Whip and coconut.
Chill in the refrigerator.

title: baked pancakes
directions: In blender, process eggs, milk, flour, salt and nutmeg until smooth, or whisk by hand.
Heat oven to 450°.
Heat oil in skillet, pie pan or baking dish in oven for 5 minutes.
When very hot, pour in batter.
Bake, uncovered, 18 to 20 minutes without opening door, until pancake is puffed and crisp around the edges and golden brown in the middle.
Cut in wedges.

title: dough ornaments(not eatable)
directions: Mix ingredients together, adding more flour, if necessary. Roll the dough to 1/2 inch thick.
Use cookie cutters to cut ornaments out of the dough.
Dry Tempra paint can be added for colored dough.

title: fresh apple coffee cake
directions: Combine apple, 1/4 cup orange juice and cinnamon.
Set aside. Cream sugar and oleo until light and fluffy.
Add egg substitute and blend well.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to creamed mixture.
Alternate with flour and milk; begin and end with flour.
Add remainder of orange juice and vanilla.
Pour 1/2 into 10-inch tube pan coated with cooking spray.
Top with 1/2 apple mixture.
Add remaining batter.
Top with remaining apple mixture. Sprinkle brown sugar on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.

title: royal sponge cake
directions: Combine egg yolks, salt, sugar and lemon juice in mixer bowl. Beat until very thick.
Fold into stiffly beaten egg whites.
Fold in flour gently.
Spoon into ungreased waxed paper-lined tube pan. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Invert on funnel to cool completely.
Loosen cake from side of pan.
Invert onto cake plate.

title: parsley hor d'oeuvres
directions: Mix all together. Serve chilled with fresh vegetables (carrots, celery, broccoli, etc).

title: sandwiches
directions: Cook the meat.
Put it on the buns.
Put cheese on it, then mustard, then ketchup, then pickles, then you're finished and you eat.

title: vegetable and beef soup
directions: Peel and dice potatoes.
Put potatoes and onion in large pot. Cover with water.
In skillet cook ground beef until brown.
Drain fat.
After potatoes and onion are tender, add remaining ingredients and ground beef.
Simmer until done.

title: baked caramel corn
directions: Melt butter; stir in brown sugar, corn syrup and salt.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil without stirring for 5 minutes; remove from heat.
Stir in soda and vanilla.
