Gradually pour over popcorn and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.

title: nacho dip
directions: In casserole dish spread cream cheese on bottom of dish.
Next top with chili and then cherry peppers.
Finally top with Monterey Jack cheese and sliced olives. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes. Let stand 5 to 10 minutes before serving.
Serve with your favorite nacho chips.

title: tuna macaroni salad
directions: Mix dressing, macaroni, tuna, celery, green pepper, onions and pimiento. Season with salt and pepper.
Refrigerate.
Serve on lettuce leaf.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Mix
all
ingredients except almonds.
Bake at 350° for 30
to 45 minutes.
Last five minutes of baking, sprinkle with almonds.

title: noodle soup
directions: In large heavy pan, cook onion, garlic and basil in butter until tender.
Stir in soup and water.
Add remaining ingredients. Bring to boil.
Reduce heat.
Cook 10 minutes or until noodles are done.
Stir occasionally.
Makes 8 cups.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a 9-inch pie shell. Cook at 350° until done.

title: peanut butter and jelly sam-mich (sandwich)
directions: For each salad, place a chilled peach half, cut side down, on plate.
Place a large marshmallow next to peach half for head.
Use small celery sticks for arms and legs with raisins at the ends for hands and shoes.
To make the face, use raisins for the eyes and nose and a piece of cherry for the mouth.
Add a ruffly leaf of lettice for the skirt and some shredded Cheddar cheese for the hair.

title: eggplant and garbanzo stew
directions: Saute onions in oil in saucepan.
Add seasoning, beans and eggplant.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Rotate vegetables.
Add tomatoes.
Liquid should come to half the depth of vegetables in pan.
Cook on medium until eggplant is done.
May be served hot or cold.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Steam
broccoli
until	done.
Saute chopped celery and onion in margarine.
Add with rice to drained broccoli.
Heat soup
and Cheez Whiz.
Add to other ingredients stirring well. Bake
in
2 quart buttered casserole dish at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: jezebel sauce
directions: Mix and refrigerate.
Makes 2 pints.
Good for meat garnishes or serve on crackers with cream cheese.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables and place in 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Spread cheese on top of vegetables.
Crumble crackers and top with melted butter.
Spread over top of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: baked chicken and stuffing
directions: Boil chicken. Cool and remove bones. Cut into bite size pieces.

title: taco dinner
directions: Cook and stir ground beef and onion in a 10-inch skillet until beef is cooked; drain and mix with seasoning and water.
Heat until it boils, then reduce heat and simmer, uncovered.
Stir occasionally for about 10 minutes.
Spoon beef mixture onto the chips.
Cover with remaining ingredients.

title: festive cranberry salad
directions: Combine milk and lemon juice; mix well. Stir in pineapple, cranberries, marshmallows, pecans and food coloring, if desired. Fold in Cool Whip. Spoon into 13 x 9 x 2 baking dish. Freeze until firm, 4 hours or overnight. Cut into squares. Keeps well frozen. Serve as needed. Makes 12 to 16 servings.

title: chili dip
directions: Melt chili with cheese.
Add peppers to taste.
Can use red cayenne pepper.
Serve warm with chips.

title: turkey imperial(low-fat)
directions: If turkey is thick, slice in half lengthwise, forming 2 pieces.
In shallow dish, combine lemon pepper and basil; blend well.
Coat turkey halves with seasoning.
Melt margarine in a large skillet over medium-high heat.
Add turkey; cook 6 to 7 minutes on each side or until lightly browned.
Top each piece of turkey with tomato slices, 2 asparagus spears and cheese.
Cover 1 minute to melt cheese.
Each serving contains 9 grams fat.

title: coney sauce(for large crowd)
directions: Cook hamburger so it is not lumpy.
Combine salt, pepper, sugar and chili powder and sprinkle garlic powder on these ingredients. Add tomato puree and ketchup.
Stir and simmer for a few minutes. Then add onions.
Stir together but do not cook any more.
Makes 1 gallon sauce.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli for 5 minutes and drain.
Mix in other ingredients and pour in baking dish.
Top with Ritz cracker crumbs and pour melted margarine on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Serves 10 to 15 people.

title: salsa bean salad
directions: Combine all beans, onion and green pepper in a bowl.
Combine salsa, salad dressing, sugar and salt.
Add to bean mixture.
Stir lightly.
Chill, covered, 4 to 24 hours, stirring often.
Stir in tomato just before serving.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: pumpkin blender pie
directions: Blend all ingredients for 3 minutes in blender.
Pour into greased 10-inch pie pan.
Makes its own crust.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° for 35 minutes.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Combine first four ingredients.
Mix well.
Put in a 1 1/2-quart dish.
Melt butter; pour over top.
Spread cracker crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: sour cream hot cakes
directions: Mix sour cream, eggs, flour, sugar, baking soda and salt in blender until smooth.
Transfer batter to bowl, cover and chill overnight.
Heat griddle or heavy large skillet.
Brush with butter or vegetable oil.
Spoon batter into skillet in dollar size rounds.
Cook until bubbles appear on surface.
Turn pancakes over and cook until golden brown.
Serve hot with maple syrup, honey or jam.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Combine all ingredients; beat for 2 minutes.
Pour into 6 small (or 2 large) greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes (70 minutes for large pans).
Batter is thin.

title: cranberry citrus punch
directions: In a large punch bowl, mix cranberry juice, lemonade, orange juice and water.
Just before serving, add ginger ale.
Garnish with lemon and orange slices.
Makes 36 to 42 servings.

title: easy roast
directions: Use enough aluminum foil to completely cover and wrap roast. Place foil in roaster.
Pour half the soup mix in middle of foil. Place roast on top of mix and cover with rest of soup mix.
Fold foil over and seal.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours or until done to your satisfaction.

title: chocolate mayonnaise cake
directions: Grease and flour 2 (9-inch) cake pans.
Mix and sift flour, sugar, cocoa, baking powder and soda into large mixing bowl.
Stir in mayonnaise.
Gradually stir in water and vanilla until smooth and blended.
Pour into pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 or 30 minutes, or until cake tests done.
Cool completely.
Frost with Seven Minute Frosting or Fudge Frosting.

title: corned beef salad
directions: All "chopped" should be fine.
Dissolve Jell-O in 1 cup boiling water; add all ingredients.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: butter cream frosting
directions: Put all ingredients in bowl and whip for 3 minutes.

title: italian casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Stir in cooked mixed vegetables. Add enough sauce to taste.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with cheese, then top with biscuits.
Bake at 350° for approximately 25 to 30 minutes, until bubbly and biscuits are browned.

title: coconut frosting
directions: Cook all ingredients, except egg whites, in double boiler while cake is cooking.
Remove from heat and fold in well beaten egg whites.

title: light as a cloud peach dessert
directions: Break 1/2 of angel food cake into pieces in the bottom of a deep dish.
Mix 2 cups of milk with instant pudding until thick and smooth in another bowl.
Add peach yogurt and mix well.
Cover angel food pieces with 1/2 of peach yogurt and pudding mixture. Slice 1 peach on top of pudding mixture.
Break up other 1/2 of angel food cake into pieces on top of peach.
Cover with other half of pudding mixture and top with sliced peaches in a star design. Chill thoroughly.
This dessert is very light and refreshing.

title: iron skillet chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cocoa.
Melt butter in skillet.
Add sugar mixture and mix lightly.
Combine beaten egg yolks and milk.
Add to mixture, stirring constantly.
Cook slowly until thick.	Add vanilla and blend well.
Pour in baked pie shell.

title: pralines
directions: Mix all together.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly, for 2 1/2 to 3 minutes.
Check for soft ball stage; cook up to 3 minutes more if not up to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat and beat with spoon until it loses its glossy look.
Drop onto wax paper by spoonfuls.

title: jackie's hot crab dip
directions: Blend all ingredients in blender, except crab.
Fold in crab. Put in casserole dish.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese.
Serve with crackers.

title: strawberry cheese pie
directions: In a large mixer bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy. Gradually beat in Eagle Brand milk until smooth.
Stir in lemon juice and vanilla.
Combine well and pour into crust.
Chill for 3 hours or until set.
Top with strawberries and glaze. Refrigerate.
Add whipped cream or Cool Whip as a topping.

title: pork chop dinner
directions: Coat pork chops with flour and brown.
Set aside.
Put sliced potatoes in casserole with onion, salt, and pepper.
Stir the soup well, then pour over potatoes.
Lay browned chops on top.
Bake 1 hour at 350 degrees.

title: church window(cookies)
directions: Melt and cool butter and chips so they don't melt marshmallows.
Stir in the marshmallows.
Put into 3 amounts and roll in wax paper log-style and put in freezer.
Slice off for each cookie.
Store in freezer.

title: sherbet punch
directions: Mix together juices and lemonade; chill.
Add 7-Up and sherbet before serving.

title: spicy beef with stir-fry vegetables
directions: In a small bowl, combine the beef broth, soy sauce, cornstarch and mustard.
Stir until the cornstarch is dissolved.
Set aside. Cut the broccoli into bite size pieces.

title: barbecue
directions: Put pork and beef in Dutch oven.
Brown in butter; add onions. Cover with water.
Simmer 4 or 5 hours.
Cool.
Skim off excess fat and add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 2 or 3 hours.

title: pot roast with vegetables
directions: Combine the garlic, oregano and lemon pepper; rub over roast. In a Dutch oven, brown the roast in oil.
Pour off drippings.
Add 3/4 cup water; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 1 3/4 hours.

title: zucchini nut bread
directions: Beat eggs and add other ingredients.
Bake 1 hour at 350° in 2 greased and floured loaf pans.

title: walnut squares
directions: Mix together flour, salt, soda and brown sugar in mixing bowl. In separate bowl, beat eggs, then add to main mixing bowl.
Add vanilla and walnuts.
Mix all together.
Use 13 x 9-inch pan, spray with Pam.
Even out mixture into pan.
Bake at 325° for about 30 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.
Serves 12 to 20.

title: turkey stuffing casserole(microwave)
directions: In your microwave, place margarine in round 8 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Cover and microwave on High (100%) until melted, 45 to 60 seconds.
Add stuffing and water.
Toss to coat stuffing. Remove 1 cup stuffing.
Spread remaining mixture evenly in baking dish.
Mix soup, peas, milk and onion in 1 1/2-quart casserole. Cover tightly and microwave on High (100%) for 3 minutes.
Stir. Cover and microwave until hot and bubbly, 3 to 4 minutes longer. Stir in turkey and pimiento.
Spread mixture over stuffing in baking dish.
Sprinkle with reserved stuffing mixture.
Microwave, uncovered, on High (100%) until hot and bubbly, 7 to 9 minutes. Serve with cranberry relish and any remaining stuffing.
Makes 6 servings.

title: southern peach cobbler
directions: Drain peaches and pour into pan. Add sugar, melted butter, nutmeg and flavorings.
Crust and bake at 350° until brown.

title: diabetic nut cookies
directions: Mix together first 7 ingredients and stir well.
Add nuts and orange rind.
Stir and drop by large teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: pumpkin pies
directions: Combine in blender
until well mixed.
Let set 10 to 15 minutes.
Pour into
two unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
(May
turn	oven
to
450° for 5 minutes to brown top).

title: raisin bran bread
directions: Sift the first 4 ingredients several times to mix thoroughly. Add the All Bran, then the raisins and nuts. Stir in buttermilk. Bake in 2
(8 x 4-inch) loaf pans and bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: pumpkin chocolate chip muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put almonds in baking sheet or pie pan and bake about 5 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool. Thoroughly mix flour, sugar, pie spice, baking soda, baking powder and salt in a large bowl.
Break eggs into another bowl.
Add pumpkin and butter and whisk until well blended.
Stir in chocolate chips and almonds.
Pour over dry ingredients and fold in with a rubber spatula, just until dry ingredients are moistened.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Prepare corn bread as directed on package.
Cool and crumble. Add bacon and vegetables.
Stir in mayonnaise.
Chill.

title: macaroni & cheese
directions: Cook macaroni.
Do not drain completely.
Butter 9 x 12 dish. Mix all ingredients except crackers.
Crush whole box of Cheese-It crackers and sprinkle on top.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 325° for 30-35 minutes or until crackers are brown.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Zucchini does not need to be pared. Mix all ingredients. Grease pans. Make 2 large loaves single batch or 5 (1 lb.) coffee cans for a double batch. Bake at 350° for 1 hour to 1 hour 15 minutes.

title: mexican chicken bake
directions: Mix the chicken, onions, green pepper, soup and Tabasco.
Fold in the corn chips.
Place in a shallow baking pan, about 9 x 12-inches in size.
Spread grated cheese over the top.
Place in oven at 350° for 25 minutes or until cheese has melted and started to turn golden brown.
Serve at once, piping hot.
Serves 6.

title: lima bean casserole
directions: Cook lima beans according to directions.
Drain.
Fry bacon crisp.
Crumble.
Combine limas, sour cream, soup, bacon, curry powder, onion salt and garlic salt.
Place in casserole.
Top with bread crumbs or dressing mix.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: bran muffins
directions: Stir Crisco and water to dissolve and place aside to cool. Mix all
ingredients together and add water/Crisco mixture.
When mixture is well blended refrigerate overnight.

title: egg custard
directions: Mix together and pour in pie crust, sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: mock apple pie
directions: Break Ritz crackers coarsely into pie shell.
Combine water, sugar and cream of tartar in saucepan; boil gently for 15 minutes. Add lemon juice and rind.
Cool.
Pour syrup over crackers, dot generously with margarine and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Cover with other pie shell for top crust.
Cut slits in top crust.
Flute edges together.
Bake at 425° for 30 to 35 minutes until crust is crisp and golden.
Serve warm with vanilla ice cream.

title: chicken rice soup
directions: In a big pan, saute butter, celery, carrots and onions until golden light brown, then continue to cook.
Add chicken.
Cook until it is brown.
Add water, salt, pepper, chicken base and rice.
Bring to a boil.
Boil for 10 minutes.
Lower heat to simmer; cook until rice is tender.

title: beef chow mein
directions: Brown meat in butter and add celery, onions and 1/4 cup water.
Steam on medium-high for 20 minutes.
After vegetables have steamed add bean sprouts, molasses, soy sauce and salt. Steam 10 minutes more and thicken with cornstarch.
Serve with rice or chow mein noodles.

title: after dinner refreshment
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender and serve in cocktail glasses.

title: sticky buns
directions: Spray Bundt pan with Pam heavily.
Put frozen rolls in pan. Mix sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle over.
Mix butter, brown sugar and water.
Microwave and melt.
Add raisins and nuts to mixture. Pour over rolls in pan.
Cover with wax paper; leave on counter overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Turn out immediately.

title: harold's sweet potato pie
directions: Whisk together potatoes, sugars, salt, spice and vanilla. Blend in eggs and both milks.
Place pie dish on baking sheet and carefully pour mixture into 9 or 10-inch pie shell.
Bake at 375° for about one hour, periodically checking the pie crust doesn't burn.
(Cover crust with foil if it browns too much.)
Pie is done when fork inserted into center of pie comes out clean.
Serve warm, with vanilla ice cream or whipped cream.

title: veggie dip
directions: Excellent on baked potato, as vegetable dip, for pretzels, etc.

title: lo-cal corn relish
directions: In medium size pot over high heat cook corn in small amount of boiling water 5 minutes.
Cut corn from cobs.
In large pot over high heat combine corn, peppers, onion, vinegar, water, sugar, sugar substitute, salt, dry mustard and celery seed.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to medium and simmer 35 minutes or until mixture thickens slightly.
Spoon into 3 hot sterile jars (pint) allowing 1/2 inch headspace.
Adjust lids and process in boiling water canner 20 minutes.

title: twenty-minute fudge
directions: Mix all ingredients in the order given.
Spread into buttered 8 x 8-inch pan.
Cool and cut into squares.
Makes 1 1/2 pounds.

title: breast of chicken casserole
directions: Spray inside of a large casserole with Pam.
Cover bottom of dish with stuffing 1 to 1 1/2 inches deep.
Place chicken breasts on top of stuffing.
In a separate dish, blend soup with 1 can of water, stirring until smooth.
Pour soup mixture over chicken and bake for
1 1/2 hours at 350°, covered.

title: "unstuffed" cabbage
directions: Sprinkle 3 cups shredded cabbage in bottom of a 2 to 3-quart buttered casserole.
Saute chopped onion in small amount of oil until softened, but not browned.
Add ground beef and cook and stir until lightly browned.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Spread meat over cabbage layer and top with remaining 3 cups cabbage.
Spread tomato soup over the top; sprinkle with celery seed and brown sugar.
Cover and bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour.
Makes 5 servings.

title: danish cheese crescents
directions: Place the dough of 1 package of crescent rolls in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix the cream cheese, sugar and egg yolk and spread on dough.
Place the second package of crescent rolls on top of the cream cheese mixture.
Beat egg white until frothy and spread on dough.
Mix sugar, cinnamon and nuts and spread on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown. Cool for at least 4 hours before serving.
Can be frozen.

title: deviled crabs
directions: Dice celery, green pepper and onion.
Add chili powder and cook in oil until done.
Crumble crackers and add to mixture along with Worcestershire, Tabasco sauce, chili sauce and garlic salt. Mix thoroughly.
Dice eggs.
Add eggs and crab meat and mix gently.
Fill cleaned crab shells with mixture and cook until brown.
Also may be formed into balls and deep fried.

title: jordan's cake
directions: Blend well the sugar, shortening and eggs.
Beat well.
Add milk and baking powder.
Sift flour before measuring.
Add flour and beat well.
Add extracts.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Heat the potatoes.
Add the sugar, oleo or butter, vanilla and eggs and mash.
Pour into a casserole and top with the light brown sugar, flour, oleo and pecans, crumbled together and sprinkled over potatoes.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: mother mac's banana nut bread
directions: Sift together the flour, soda, baking powder, salt, cinnamon and allspice.
With mixer, cream the sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, bananas, vanilla and dry ingredients and blend well.
Add chopped nuts.
Pour batter into a 9 x 5 x 2-inch greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes and remove from pan.
Thoroughly cool before slicing.

title: canned vegetable salad
directions: Mix green beans, peas, corn, celery and onions in a bowl. Combine oil, sugar, vinegar, salt and pepper.
Combine vegetables and dressing.
Allow to stand overnight.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli, then drain. Put in casserole dish. Crumble 1/2 pack Ritz, then mix with 1/2 stick melted butter.
Spread on top of broccoli. Melt cheese and 1/2 stick butter. Pour on top. Place in preheated 350° oven for 5 to 10 minutes or place in microwave for 1 minute.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in egg.
Add nuts and raisins. Sift flour, cinnamon and cloves.
Stir into butter mixture.
Last, add applesauce which has been heated.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Melt butter. Add mustard and flour to make paste. Then add milk; bring to a boil and then add cheese and broccoli.

title: party baked pork chops
directions: Season chops on both sides and brown in lightly greased skillet.
Remove to baking dish; top each chop with onion, 1/4 of the raw rice and whole tomatoes.
Add remaining tomatoes and juice and tomato sauce around chops.
Salt lightly.
Cover tightly with foil and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: brown and serve rolls
directions: Scald milk; add sugar, salt and butter.
Cool to lukewarm. Dissolve yeast in water.
Add to milk.
Add enough flour to make soft dough. Knead lightly.
Place in greased bowl.
Brush top with melted butter.
Cover; let rise until double in bulk.
Shape into rolls.
Brush top with melted butter.
Cover and let rise until double in bulk.
Bake in 250° oven for 20 minutes.
Remove from pan; butter top.

title: cream cheese pan cookies
directions: Grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread 1 package cookies on bottom of pan.
Mix cream cheese, eggs, sugar and vanilla together.
Spread over cookie dough.
Crumble other cookie roll over cream cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Simmer all ingredients except shrimp for about 15 to 20 minutes, then add cooked shrimp.
Simmer about 3 to 4 minutes.

title: zucchini squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Mix all ingredients together.
Spread in pan.
Bake until golden brown, 25 minutes.
Cut into pieces 2 x 1-inch.
Delicious warm or cold!

title: flan
directions: In a medium nonstick frypan, heat the sugar over medium heat, tilting and shaking pan often, until sugar melts and turns a pale amber color (about 8 minutes).
Watch closely since sugar scorches easily.
Immediately pour caramel syrup into a round 1-quart baking dish, tilting to coat bottom and 1/2-inch of sides.
Place dish in a larger pan, such as an 8-inch or 9-inch square pan and set aside.

title: italian style ground turkey cutlets
directions: Mix turkey well with Ricotta, parsley, salt and pepper. Combine bread crumbs and Parmesan on a shallow plate.
Shape turkey into four flat cutlets.
Press the cutlets into the bread crumb mixture, coating both sides.
Spray a shallow skillet with Pam.
Fry the cutlets with no fat, turning about 4 or 5 minutes per side.
Makes 4 servings, 295 calories each.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Put
asparagus	on
bottom of greased flat baking dish. Salt and pepper.
Put soup on seasoned asparagus.
Add grated cheese and cover with crushed cornflakes.	Bake, uncovered, at 300° for 25 minutes.

title: delicious banana cream delight
directions: Mix flour, sugar, oleo and nuts together for crust.
Bake at 375° in ungreased pan for 15 minutes and let cool.
Mix instant pudding with milk and beat to make pudding.
Add bananas and set aside.
Mix cream cheese, confectioners sugar and Cool Whip. Spread cheese mix over crust.
Spread pudding mix over cheese mix. Top with Cool Whip and walnuts if desired.

title: alpha nu luncheon
directions: Mix together the mayonnaise and mustard for dressing.
Mix all the rest of the ingredients together and stir in the dressing. Refrigerate for 4 hours.

title: fran's waffles or hotcakes
directions: Mix flour, eggs, cooking oil, sugar and 3/4 buttermilk.
Stir well.
Add soda to buttermilk, then add to batter.
Wait a few minutes for your batter to rise, then cook in hot waffle iron griddle.

title: salad dressing for fruit
directions: Mix all together well.
Beat until fluffy.
Refrigerate. Serve over fruit salad in lettuce cup or with party sandwiches, crusts off!

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar, butter and milk in saucepan.
Bring to boil, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Cook to soft boil or 236° or until a small amount dropped in water forms a soft ball.
Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Beat until mixture begins to thicken.
Pour into buttered 8-inch pan.
Cut into squares and chill.

title: caramel corn
directions: Mix sugar, butter, syrup and salt.
Cook and stir over medium heat until it bubbles.
Cook 5 minutes more.
Remove from heat and stir in soda and vanilla.
Pour over popcorn.
Bake 1 hour at 250° in two buttered 9 x 15-inch pans.
Stir every 15 minutes.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix flour, sugar and milk.
Pour into a deep baking dish.
Add fruit.
Drain if from a can.
Spread evenly over mixture and dot with margarine or butter.
Sprinkle a little sugar.
Now bake 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Great with ice cream.

title: baked chicken and rice
directions: Butter a large casserole.
Spread rice in the bottom. Sprinkle chicken with salt and arrange over rice.
Combine cream of celery and cream of mushroom soups.
Dribble over chicken. Sprinkle instant onion soup over all.
Pour broth around, not over, the mixture.
Cover tightly with foil and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until chicken is done.

title: brown sugar cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream shortening and sugar together in bowl.
Break one egg into bowl and beat with beater.

title: swiss vegetable bake
directions: Mix all together, reserving 1/2 the onions and 1/2 the cheese. Put in 1-quart casserole. Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Uncover and top with remaining onions and cheese. Bake 5 more minutes.

title: orange cream salad
directions: Drain pineapple and save syrup.
Dissolve jello, hot water, sugar and syrup.
Chill until partially set.
Add cream or yogurt and vanilla.
Whip until fluffy.
Fold in pineapple, oranges and coconut.
Chill.

title: surprise salad
directions: Pour pineapple into saucepan and bring to boiling point.
Add lemon Jello and cream cheese.
Stir and let cool.
Add celery, cherries, and nuts.
Add whipped cream and chill.
Serve on lettuce.

title: syllabub
directions: In large mixing bowl, stir with whisk.
Gently fold whipping cream into mixture until frothy.
Refrigerate.
Serves 12 people.

title: easy fruit dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and marshmallow cream together.
Refrigerate until ready to use.
Dip fruit of your choice.

title: raised waffles
directions: Start the night before:
In a large mixing bowl, add yeast to warm water.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Add the lukewarm milk, melted butter (or oil), salt and sugar.
Beat in flour.
Cover bowl and let stand overnight (not in refrigerator).

title: creamed chicken
directions: Cover chicken breasts with water; add next 5 ingredients and cook until tender.
Cool; drain and then cube, discarding skin and bones.
Strain stock, melt butter in saucepan and blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Stir in chicken stock and milk.
Cook over low heat until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add chicken and pimentos and heat thoroughly.
Serve in patty shells, over biscuits or cornbread squares.
Serves 6.

title: bubble bath oil
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Seal in bottles.
Sprinkle at bath time.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour, melted butter.
Add eggs and beat until smooth, add syrup and vanilla, lastly nuts.
Pour in unbaked shell and bake slowly at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hash brown quiche
directions: Press hash browns between paper towels to remove excess moisture.
Press into bottom and up sides of 9-inch pie pan. Drizzle with butter and bake at 425° for 25 minutes.
Combine the ham, cheese and green pepper and spoon over crust.
In small bowl, beat eggs, milk, salt and pepper; pour over all.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 25 to 30 minutes, until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Let stand 10 minutes and cut in wedges.

title: apple betty
directions: Mound apples in buttered 9-inch pie plate.
Sprinkle with orange juice.
Also, sprinkle a little extra cinnamon on apples. Combine sugar, flour, cinnamon and salt; cut in butter until mixture is crumbly.
Sprinkle over apples.
Can add a little oatmeal to mixture if desired.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until apples are tender and topping is crisp.
Serve warm with ice cream, if desired.
Makes 6 servings.

title: quick beef stew
directions: Cook beef, onion and garlic in large saucepan over medium-high heat until beef is brown; drain fat.
Blend tomatoes with juice in blender until smooth.
Add tomatoes, water, bouillon cubes and pepper to meat mixture.
Bring to boil; reduce heat to low. Simmer, uncovered, 20 minutes.
Add rice and vegetables.
Simmer an additional 20 minutes.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Cook ground beef and onion in 10-inch skillet until beef looses redness.
Drain and stir in Big John's Beans 'N Fixin's and seasonings.
Cut tops off the peppers and remove membrane and seeds.
Fill peppers with bean mixture.
Top with ketchup and cheese.
Place in 1 1/2-quart shallow baking dish.
Cover tightly and bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: jackie's special
directions: Clean gizzards and wash; drain.
Cut bell peppers and green onions into cubes.
Pour oil into skillet over medium heat.
Add onions, bell peppers and dash of garlic.
Lightly brown.
Remove from skillet.
Add 2 more tablespoons of oil.
Brown gizzards on low heat, stirring until browned.
Add onions and bell peppers along with bouillon, salt, black pepper, garlic, soy sauce and wine, cooking slowly for 1 minute.
Add 1 1/2 cups of water.
Let cook slowly until tender.
If liquid cooks down before tender or done, add more water.
Serve over rice or on toasted buns.

title: new orleans pralines
directions: Combine the sugars, salt, milk and cream of tartar.
Stir over low heat until sugar dissolves, wiping crystals from side of pan. Cook at 236° to 238° on a candy thermometer.
Cool to 220°.
Add butter, vanilla and pecans* and beat until creamy with a wire whisk.
Quickly drop by spoonfuls onto buttered wax paper and let cool.

title: pink stuff
directions: Mix ingredients until well blended and store in a covered bowl in refrigerator.
Keeps well for several days and freezes well. Also good with mandarin oranges.

title: play dough
directions: Mix flour, salt and tartar in pot.
Combine and add water, food coloring and oil.
Cook 3 to 5 minutes until it forms a ball. Knead on flour board.
Keeps for weeks in an airtight container.

title: cake
directions: Cream sugar, margarine and eggs.
Add flour and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Bake at 350°.
Frost with Chocolate Filling (recipe in this book).

title: ham casserole
directions: Cook potatoes, celery and carrots.
Saute ham, green peppers and onions in oleo.
Place ham mixture in greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Melt 1/4 cup oleo in heavy saucepan.
Add flour. Stir until smooth.
Gradually add milk.
Cook until thickened. Stir in cheese, salt and pepper.
Pour over ham and vegetables. Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: peggy's spaghetti
directions: Brown meat, onion and sweet pepper in margarine.
Add other ingredients.
If making large amount, use 2 cans tomato paste. Simmer on low heat as long as possible.
(The secret to a good sauce is to cook a long time.)
Mix in cooked and drained spaghetti.

title: summer slush
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pour into shallow container and freeze until slushy.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Mix cornflakes with rosemary, salt and pepper.
Dip chicken in milk and roll in seasoned crumbs.
Let stand briefly so coating will adhere.
Place chicken in an oiled baking pan.
Line pan with foil for easy clean up.
Do not crowd.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes or more.

title: swiss bread
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in saucepan over low heat.
Slice bread in half lengthways.
Spread mixture on both sides of inside of bread.
Put Swiss cheese on each side of bread.
Put both sides of bread back together and spread butter mixture on top and sides of bread.
Wrap loosely in foil; bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Fold foil back and bake another 5 minutes; serve warm.

title: easy chicken pie
directions: Boil the chicken.
Do not add salt.
Line a baking dish with the cooked chicken.
tags: cream of chicken soup or cream of celery soup

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix peanut butter, cream cheese and sugar.
Add Cool Whip. Fill pie shell and refrigerate.

title: crab spread
directions: Mix crab meat, cream cheese, onion, olives, lemon juice and Worcestershire sauce together.
Add enough ketchup to make a pinkish color.
Form into 2 logs.
Roll each log in chopped walnuts and parsley.
Serve with crackers.

title: margaret boggs time saving pickles
directions: Remove whole pickles from jar; save juice.
Slice pickles into 1/4 to 1/2-inch thick slices.
Return pickles to jar; add sugar.
Pour 1/2 cup juice over sugar.
Refrigerate and turn jar over and over once daily for 1 week.
Delicious and crisp.

title: fruit salad
directions: Dissolve marshmallows, cream cheese and Jell-O by pouring boiling water over them and stirring until dissolved. Add sugar, drained pineapple and nuts. Let it gel and add Cool Whip to the top. Add a drop or 2 of cake coloring to Cool Whip to match the color of the Jell-O.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Spread coconut over bottom of greased cake pan.
Add chopped pecans.
Mix cake mix according to directions.
Pour over coconut and pecans.
Mix sugar, cream cheese and butter.
Spread over top of cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: spiced tea
directions: Bring the water to a boil; add spices.
Simmer 10 minutes. Remove spices.
Add tea.
Allow to steep for 10 minutes.
Remove tea bags.
Add sugar and juices.
Serve warm.

title: panocha
directions: Put the sugar and milk into a saucepan and cook to the softball stage or 238°.
Remove from the fire.
Add butter and vanilla and cool without stirring.
When it is lukewarm, beat until it is creamy.
Stir in the broken nutmeats.
Hickory nuts, walnuts or pecans are especially nice.
Pour into a buttered pan and, when it hardens, mark into squares.

title: meringue
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add sugar.
Stir cornstarch in half of the water and bring to a boil.
Pour in the rest of the water and cook until clear and thick.
Cool cornstarch slightly before adding the egg whites.
Add the egg whites and add the vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: lemon pie
directions: Cook until thick and pour into cooked pie shell (9-inches).

title: easy low calorie strawberry pie
directions: Put strawberries in pie shell.
Put diet 7-Up and cornstarch in boiler and bring to almost a boil.
Remove from heat and pour dry Jell-O in this mixture.
Mix well and pour over strawberries. Put in refrigerator to gel, uncovered.
Top with light Cool Whip to serve.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Mix salt, garlic powder, parmesan cheese, and bread crumbs. Melt butter.
Dip each chicken breast into butter and roll in bread crumbs mixture.
Place into baking dish.
Mix any leftover crumbs with butter and sprinkle over chicken.
Bake at 350 degrees for about 45 minutes, or until chicken is done.

title: cauliflower-broccoli salad
directions: Combine vegetables in a bowl.
Mix remaining ingredients in separate bowl.
Pour over vegetables and refrigerate overnight.

title: baked summer squash
directions: Cook squash.
Drain and chop.
Combine squash, crumbs, eggs, milk, salt and 1 1/2 cups cheese.
Place in buttered pan.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup cheese.
Dust with paprika.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together except Ritz crackers and butter. Mix Ritz crackers and butter.
Sprinkle on top of casserole. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: flautas
directions: Season chicken with salt and pepper.
Steam the chicken until it is cooked.
Debone and shred the cooked chicken in small pieces.
Warm tortillas on a hot plate, one at a time.
Place a desired amount of chicken on the warm tortilla.
Roll the tortilla and place a toothpick to hold intact.
Fry the rolled tortilla until golden brown.

title: pecan puffs
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
Process flour and pecans in food processor or until nuts are very finely chopped.
Beat butter, sugar and vanilla until pale and fluffy.
Gradually beat in flour mixture just until blended.
Roll level tablespoons of dough into balls.
Place 1-inch apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 45 minutes or until browned.
While warm, roll in powdered sugar. Cool completely.
Then roll in powdered sugar again.

title: easy cookies
directions: Mix ingredients. Chill dough. Drop onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° about 8 minutes.

title: savory steak
directions: Pour Heinz 57 sauce on large piece of heavy aluminum foil. Place steak on foil.
Cut up green pepper and onion and spread over steaks along with mushrooms.
Pour remaining Heinz 57 sauce over steaks covering completely.
You can bake the steaks in the oven or on the grill.
Bake in 325° oven for 30 minutes or grill on low for 15 minutes or so.

title: orange no-bake cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients except coconut.
Shape mixture into small balls and roll in coconut.
Refrigerate.

title: apricot glazed chicken
directions: Place chicken, skin side up, on a rack in a large baking pan. Combine remaining ingredients and pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, basting occasionally with pan drippings.
Serves 6.

title: peach butter cake
directions: Dice peaches and set aside.
Cream butter and sugar thoroughly.
Add eggs and almond extract.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and cinnamon. Alternately add sifted dry ingredients and milk to creamed mixture.
Stir in peaches.
Pour into well-greased 8-inch square pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: scalloped sausage and potatoes
directions: Combine the
milk,
flour,
onion and celery; toss in a blender for
10 seconds.
Set aside.
Break up the sausage and brown in
a
large	skillet;
drain
well.	Add
2 tablespoons water;
cook
minutes
more, then add the first mixture and bring to
a boil.
Put the sliced potatoes in a 3-quart casserole, then add the sausage mixture.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours in a 350° oven.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Cream together the margarine, sugar and eggs.
Add the sour cream and vanilla.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt and mix with other ingredients.
In a separate bowl, combine the pecans, cinnamon and brown sugar for the topping.

title: cream of corn soup
directions: In blender, puree corn and onion with water.
Set aside.
In a heavy saucepan, cook bacon.
Remove pan from heat and add flour and pepper.
Stir into bacon fat.
Gradually add hot milk and return to heat.
Cook over medium heat until thickened.
Add corn and onion mixture; heat to serving temperature.

title: chicken delight
directions: Mix together.
Let marinate overnight.
Top with crumbled corn flakes. Bake 1 hour at 275°.

title: hearty homestyle broccoli soup
directions: Steam broccoli over 2 c. boiling water until done.
Pour water into a large soup pot and set the broccoli aside.
Add the margarine to the soup pot, then add the onion, celery and carrots. Saute 3-5 minutes then add 1/2 - 3/4 c. flour, depending on thickness desired, and stir well.
Add broccoli and remaining ingredients; mix well. Cover and cook over very low heat for 1-1/2 to 2 hours, stirring often to prevent scorching.

title: troll krem
directions: Put all ingredients in blender and beat until very fluffy. Serves 8.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly.
Make small balls and bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Makes 100 balls.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Crumble 1/2 stack of Ritz crackers and spread in bottom of ungreased 13 x 8-inch baking dish.
Combine all ingredients, except remaining crackers and margarine.
Put in dish.
Crumble remaining crackers and mix with margarine; sprinkle on top of mixture.
Bake at 350° until bubbly and toasted (25 to 30 minutes).

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, cinnamon, soda and salt.
Mix together sugar, eggs and oil.
Add sifted ingredients, carrots, drained pineapple, nuts, coconut and raisins.
Pour into a greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: upside-down gingerbread
directions: Melt butter in 9-inch square cake pan.
Add corn syrup and brown sugar; blend.
Fill 6 pear halves with walnut meats.
Place cut side down in pan.
Pour gingerbread batter over pears.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 50 to 60 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: pavlova(a favorite australian dessert.)
directions: Heat oven to 200°.
Beat egg whites with salt and cream of tartar until frothy. Gradually beat in sugar, a little at a time. Continue beating until stiff and sugar is dissolved.
Beat in vanilla extract.
Cover a cookie sheet with brown paper or aluminum foil. Draw a 9-inch circle and spread meringue evenly within the lines.
Make a slight hollow in the center for the filling. Bake for 1 hour.
Turn off heat and let dry in oven at least 2 hours.
When ready to serve, whip the cream until thick. Fold in fruit and fill center of Pavlova. Can garnish with strawberries and kiwi.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef and drain fat.
Arrange chips preferably on serving (individual sized) plates.
Put ground beef on chips.
Add shredded cheese, then picante sauce, then lettuce, then tomatoes and avocados, finish with a dollop of sour cream in center.

title: blond brownies
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Melt butter.
Remove from heat.
Stir in sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla,
stir until well blended.
Stir dry ingredients and walnuts into sugar mixture.
Spread in pan.
It is stiff.
Bake at 350°
for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cut into bars while warm.

title: roger's peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook together sugar, cocoa, salt and milk.

Cook until small amount dropped into cold water forms a ball (with your fingers). Remove from heat and add vanilla, margarine and peanut butter. Beat until it begins to lose its gloss and starts to thicken. Pour into a buttered dish.
Cool and cut.

title: snow pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour; stir in milk.
Cook until thick.
Add vanilla and beaten egg whites.
Pour into baked crust.

title: brownies
directions: Beat eggs until thickened and lemon colored.
Gradually and thoroughly beat in sugar.
Stir in vanilla, chocolate ingredients and melted butter.
Add flour and baking powder.
Add all the walnuts.
Pour into a greased 8-inch square pan and sprinkle with remaining walnuts.
Bake at 375° for 17 to 20 minutes.
Cut in 16 (2-inch) squares.

title: honey punch
directions: Mix well and chill.
Makes 2 quarts.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Mix together sour cream, egg and sugar.
Add flour, soda and rhubarb.
Sprinkle brown sugar on top of cake batter.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: lemon lush dessert
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and bake in 9 x 13-inch pan for 15 minutes at 375°.
Mix next 3 ingredients and spread over cooled crust.
Beat next 2 ingredients until thick; spread over cream cheese layer.
Add rest of Cool Whip on top and sprinkle with nuts. Refrigerate.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Fix 1 1/2 cups Minute rice according to directions on box. Chop onion fine.

Put in saucepan with oleo over medium heat. When oleo has melted, saute until onion is tender, then add frozen broccoli; let thaw, stirring until well mixed. Pour rice, Cheez Whiz, cream of mushroom and 1/2 cup sweet milk along with broccoli in fairly large baking dish.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350° or until golden brown on top.

title: yum-yum cake
directions: Mix pudding as directed on box.
Cream the cream cheese; add prepared pudding and mix together.
Spread on cake.
Then spread Cool Whip on top of pudding mixture.
Drain pineapple well. Spread over Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with coconut and garnish with cherries and nuts.
Refrigerate.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all together.
To serve, use 1/3 cup mix to 2/3 cup hot water.

title: monkey bread
directions: Set oven at 350°.
Grease Bundt or tube pan well with Crisco. Sprinkle nuts in bottom of pan.
Mix cinnamon and sugar in paper bag.
Add quartered biscuits and shake until covered.
Drop biscuit quarters ni pan.
Melt the margarine and add the dark sugar.
Pour this mixture over top of biscuits and bake 30 to 35 minutes.
Let cool.

title: coconut balls
directions: Mix ingredients and make into small balls.
Chill for about 40 minutes.
Drop into melted chocolate almond bark (melt in double boiler or in microwave; make sure no water is in your bowl). Place on wax paper to cool.

title: dill pickles
directions: Drain 1 qt. dill pickles.
Cut pickles in quarters and put back in the jar.
Pour 1 cup of sugar in the jar and fill with pickle juice.
Put the lid on and mix.
Turn the jar until the mixture is clear.

title: light potato wedges or fries
directions: Wash and peel potatoes.
(For wedges, quarter each potato. For fries, slice.)
Spray a cookie sheet with cooking spray. Place potatoes on sheet singly.
Spray potatoes with cooking spray and salt potatoes as desired.
Place in 350° preheated oven, bake until tender.

title: dirt cake
directions: Beat egg whites and salt until soft peaks form. Add superfine sugar gradually, beating well between each addition. Make sure sugar is completely dissolved. Mix together granulated sugar and cornstarch; lightly fold into meringue with lemon juice. This mixture will make one large Pavlova.

Shape the meringue on the baking sheet covered with parchment paper or try foil for it will easily peel away from the Pavlova when it is cooked. Place in an oven preheated to 225°. Bake for 40 minutes or more until the Pavlova is dry to the touch. Do not allow it to color. Turn off the oven; open the door and leave it in the oven to cool. This dries it out and makes it crisp. Pavlovas should be light, dry and pale in color.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: Fry bacon, and remove from grease. Then saute onions in bacon grease until soft. Cook potatoes and drain.
Add all other ingredients. Simmer, stirring occasionally
May be served hot or cold.

title: galloping gourmet's chicken
directions: If you are watching your fat grams, microwave the pepperoni on a plate covered with several paper towels for a minute or two to remove a lot of the fat.
(Check frequently so that the pepperoni doesn't burn.)
Saute the chopped garlic and sliced green and red peppers.
Set aside.

title: tropical cake with icing
directions: Sift flour, sugar and baking soda together.
Add oil, water, eggs and vanilla.
Mix well.
Put in the rest of the ingredients. Mix well.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan and bake at 350°
for 45 minutes or until done.

title: sweet macaroni salad
directions: Put sugar and mayonnaise in bowl.
Mix well.
Add vinegar, a little at a time.
Mix thoroughly with a whisk.
Stir in onions. Cook macaroni.
Place in bowl.
While warm, add vinegar dressing and mix well.

title: clam chowder
directions: Steam clams.
Pick
out
clams and save juice.	Dice or slice potatoes; chop
onion
fine.
Add
water to cover.	Cook for 1/2 hour.
Add	oleo
and
evaporated and fresh milk.
Add clams last. Salt
and	pepper	to taste.
Heat (do not boil). Browned, diced pork fat can also be added.

title: cream caramels
directions: Blend the sugar and corn syrup in a heavy pan.
Place over low heat, stirring constantly until it thickens and begins to dissolve. Cook to crack stage.
Take off heat and add butter a piece at a time.
Put back on heat and add cream.
Don't let it quit boiling.
Cook to hard ball stage.
Take off heat and let sit for 5 minutes.
Then add salt and vanilla.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: mother's mashed potatoes
directions: Mash potatoes and mix ingredients thoroughly.
Put into a casserole and bake for 1 hour at 250° or until potatoes are warm. This is a handy recipe to use when you are fixing a holiday dinner and want to prepare the potatoes a day ahead.
Refrigerate them and then just heat in your oven or microwave them for the dinner. They are full of cholesterol and are delicious!

title: mushroom oatmeal patties
directions: Saute onion and mushrooms in olive oil.
Mix all ingredients well.
Let stand for oatmeal to soak up moisture.
If more moisture is needed, use canned milk.
Fry slowly in either olive oil or canola oil.
Cover with gravy made from mushroom soup, celery soup and one cup of hot water.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: frittata of zucchini(vegetarian)
directions: Cut the zucchini into small pieces.
Dice and chop the onions. Heat the olive oil in a 10-inch skillet and add the onions and zucchini to it.
Saute the veggies, stirring often, until the onions are golden and the zucchini tender.
Meanwhile, beat the eggs lightly with some salt, pepper and a little crushed basil. When the zucchini is tender, spread the veggies around in the pan evenly and pour the eggs over them.
Lower the flame and cover the pan.
Cook the frittata this way until the eggs are completely set, about 15 to 20 minutes.
Check it occasionally to see if it is puffing up in a bubble, in which
case pierce it once or twice with a sharp knife.
When the eggs are firm on top, loosen frittata carefully by sliding a spatula around and under it.
Then place a plate upside down over the top of the pan like a lid and invert it, dropping the frittata out onto it.
Slide it carefully back into the pan with the top side down and brown it for a few minutes.
Then turn it out onto a serving plate.
Serve it cut in wedges, as a first course or as part of an antipasto.
It can be served hot but is best served at room temperature.
Do not serve it cold.
Serves 6.

title: italian cream cheese cake
directions: Beat butter and shortening; add sugar and beat well.
Add egg yolks, one at a time.
Sift flour and soda together and add alternately with buttermilk.
Add vanilla, coconut and pecans; mix slowly.
Fold in beaten egg whites and pour into greased cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: chocolate eclair
directions: Cover bottom and sides of pan with graham crackers.
Mix milk with pudding mix and fold in Cool Whip.
Spoon mixture into pan on top of graham crackers.
Cover with another layer of graham crackers.
Mix cream cheese and icing and spread on top of graham crackers.
Garnish with cherries and nuts.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Mix together flour, sugar and milk.
Spread fruit in the bottom of a 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Pour the mixture of flour, sugar and milk over the fruit.
Dot with pats of butter.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes, or until lightly brown.

title: easy chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli until tender and drain.
Arrange broccoli in greased 11 x 7 x 1-inch baking dish.
Place chicken on top. Combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Combine bread crumbs and butter and sprinkle over all.

title: baked macaroni-bulgaria(makarony na furna)
directions: Preheat oven to 400F. Combine salt with 3 cups water and boil. Add macaroni and simmer until soft. Rinse with cold water and drain. Place in baking dish with lightly buttered bottom. Sprinkle pieces of butter and cheese on top. Beat eggs, milk and sugar and pour on top of macaroni. Bake until top of macaroni turns red/brown. Makes 6-8 servings.

title: cream caramels
directions: Butter an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Combine sugar, syrup, butter and half the cream in a large pan.
Heat to boiling over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Stir in remaining cream.
Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally until mixture reaches 245° on candy thermometer or small amount of mixture dropped into very cold water forms a firm ball.
Add vanilla (1 teaspoon) and spread immediately into pan.
Cool.
Cut into 1-inch squares.

title: pork tenderloin in sour cream
directions: Rub meat well with salt and place in a 9x13-inch baking dish. Add pepper and cover meat with lemon slices.

title: california stew
directions: Cut potatoes into medium size chunks and place in hot steamer, then slice carrots and zucchini and add to potatoes in steamer.
Slice yellow squash and dice onion and add to steamer. Cut broccoli into small sized florets and place into steamer and remove from heat.
Keep covered for 5 minutes or until broccoli is thoroughly warm.
The cooking time for all vegetables should be about fifteen minutes.
Serves 8.

title: stuffed zucchini(romania)
directions: Pre-heat oven to 350F. Trim zucchini, don't peel. Bring a large pot of water to a boil, add zucchini. Boil zucchini for 6-7 minutes, remove from water. Cut zucchini in half length wise and remove seeds with a spoon, set aside. In a medium bowl, combine ground meat, 2 Tbsp. of chopped onions, eggs, parsley, bread crumbs, cheese, salt, and pepper. Mix together. Fill zucchini with meat mixture. In a large skillet heat olive oil and butter. Add zucchini, remaining onions, and garlic. Saute for about 10 minutes. Place zucchini in a lightly buttered oven dish. Cook uncovered for about 35 minutes.

In a small sauce pan combine flour, tomato paste, basil, salt, and pepper, simmer for a few minutes. When zucchini is done add sour cream to sauce and serve over zucchini. You may substitute another cheese for Gruyere. If using dried herbs use less than the recipe calls for since they are stronger.

title: grandma's apple butter
directions: Spice a dish with love and it will please every palate.

title: chocolate butterscotch cake
directions: Prepare cake mix and bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
When done, remove from oven and while hot, poke holes in cake with the end of a wooden spoon.
Pour the milk and the caramel topping into the holes and over the cake.
Let cool and then spread on the whipped topping.
Sprinkle crushed candy bars on top, if desired, and refrigerate.
This cake can be made a day ahead.

title: steak and rice dinner
directions: Cut steak into thin strips.
Brown meat in oil.
Add chopped onions; saute until tender.
Blend soup, garlic salt, sherry and liquid from mushrooms.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 1 hour. Serve over rice.
Serves six.

title: raisin pie
directions: Cook until thick and chill.

title: cinnamon pudding
directions: Bring sugar, water and 2 teaspoons of butter to boil; set aside.
Cream 2 tablespoons of butter and sugar together; then mix flour, baking powder, cinnamon and salt together.
Add to creamed mixture along with 1 cup milk.
Mix well.
Spread batter in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour syrup mixture over and sprinkle top with 1 cup nuts.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Layer chicken, then eggs, in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Mix broth and soups.
Pour over chicken and eggs.
Mix flour and buttermilk and pour over that mixture.
Bake for 1 hour in 375° oven.

title: strawberry yogurt fizz
directions: Whirl fresh strawberries, frozen yogurt and banana in blender until smooth.
Add ginger ale and pulse blender 2 or 3 times until mixed.
Chill for a half hour (if you can make yourself wait that long).
Serves four.

title: sausage and rice
directions: Brown sausage and drain. Cook rice.
Mix all ingredients together and heat.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Bring first 4 ingredients to boil in glass bowl and boil for 2 minutes.
Remove from microwave, add baking soda and vanilla (mix will foam up).
Pour over popped corn in grocery bag (1/3 full). Shake bag well.
Microwave for 1 minute.
Shake bag well. Microwave for another minute.
Shake again and pour into bowl.

title: barrel of muffins
directions: Mix baking soda and water.
Set aside.
Cream the oil and sugar.
Add egg whites and mix well.
Combine cereals and flour. Add to creamed mixture and stir in buttermilk.
Add water and baking soda and mix.
Store the batter in refrigerator.
When ready to bake, preheat oven to 375° and spoon batter into lightly oiled or paper lined muffin tins.
Return extra batter to refrigerator. Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Heart healthy and okay for diabetics if not eaten every day.

title: old-time buttermilk pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar together, adding other ingredients and beat well.
Pour into pie shell and bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350°. You may add 1/2 cup coconut before baking if you wish.

title: neiman marcus cake
directions: Mix cake mix with other ingredients. Grease 9x13 pan and pat mixture into it. Spread Cream Cheese Topping over unbaked cake mixture. Bake in pre-heated 350° over for 30 minutes.

title: zucchini cheddar bread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease and flour loaf pan.
Saute onion in margarine; cool.
Mix baking mix, parsley, basil, thyme, milk and eggs; beat vigorously for 1 minute.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Bake for about 40 minutes.

title: ceviche
directions: 1. Dip fish and other seafoods in boiling water and remove any bones/shells.
2. Put fish in non-aluminum bowl and cover with lime/lemon
juices and allow to stand (refrigerated) for an hour.
3. Drain fish/seafood and rinse in cold water.
4. Stir together remaining ingredients in a non aluminum
bowl and add fish/seafood and refrigerate (covered) for
an hour or so. 5. Serve chilled with Tortilla chips or bread.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown meat with onion and season with salt and pepper.
Drain. Place meat in a baking dish and spread evenly.
Add mixed vegetables to cover in a layer.
Dilute soup with water and pour over evenly.
Put Tater Tots in solid rows across the top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: chocolate peanut butter pie
directions: In the top of double boiler, over hot but not boiling water, combine sugar, flour and salt. Gradually add milk and cook for 10 minutes, stirring constantly. Pour a small amount of the hot milk mixture into the egg yolks; return all to double boiler. Cook for 4 minutes, stirring constantly. Remove from heat; stir in vanilla. Let cool for 10 to 12 minutes. Divide mixture in half. To one half, stir in peanut butter; mix well. To other half, stir in melted chocolate. Allow mixture to cool, then fill pie crust with peanut butter mixture, then the chocolate mixture. Refrigerate and chill for several hours. Just before serving, top with whipped cream and sprinkle on nuts. This is deeelicious!

title: cherry pudding
directions: Grease 8 x 8 x 2 cake pan. Sift flour, add baking powder, salt and use 1/2 c sugar.
Add butter (shortening or margarine) milk and vanilla mix with mixer.
Pour into pan, cover with cherries and sprinkle with remaining 1/2 cup of sugar.
Heat cherry juice and pour over mixture.
Bake in 375 degree oven for 40 to 50 minutes.
Serve warm, plain or with ice cream.
Newer ovens take less time to cook.

title: quick green bean casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except crackers and butter.
Put into a greased casserole dish.
Crumble crackers over top and drizzle with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: watergate cake
directions: Beat 3 to 4 minutes at medium speed.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: french onion soup
directions: Boil and simmer ingredients for 30 minutes.
Broil French bread slices and place in bottom of bowls.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Add soup and top with grated Mozzarella and Cheddar cheese.
Place in broiler until cheese melts.

title: ritz cracker pie
directions: Beat egg whites stiff. Add baking powder; add sugar, salt and vanilla. Beat until well mixed. Fold in nuts and crackers and mix lightly together. Pour into well-greased pie plate, pushing up edges a little. Bake at 325° for 30 to 45 minutes. Top with whipped cream.

title: mint smoothie
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender and blend until smooth. Pour into serving glasses and top with a dollop of whipped cream.

title: no bean dip
directions: In an 8-inch pie plate:

title: mexican salad
directions: Brown hamburger in skillet.
In a bowl, add lettuce, tomato, green pepper, black olives, cheese and Doritos.
Mix together. Drain hamburger and add to salad.
Pour French dressing and stir well.
Serve.
Good hot or cold.
Double recipe, if desired.

title: my mom's chicken and rice
directions: Combine milk and soup in bowl using whisk until smooth; stir in rice.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Place chicken breasts deep into mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: mamma's banana cake
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Mix baking soda into eggs and sour cream in a small bowl, then add this to the sugar-margarine mixture.
Add bananas, mashed lightly, vanilla and flour, then nuts and chips.
Sprinkle with cinnamon-sugar; mix well.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes for a layer cake and for 60 minutes for a loaf cake. (Double recipe for a high Bundt cake.)

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Saute onions and garlic.
Add beef.
Cook until red disappears.
Add salt, pepper,
and mushroom soup.
Stir and cook 20 minutes.
Add sour cream and parsley.
Serve on rice or noodles.
15 minutes prep. time.
30 minutes cook time.
Serves 4-6.

title: cheese grits souffle(alfresco summer dinner with leslie and bob e.)
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Place the grits, milk, water and salt in the top of a double boiler.
Cook, stirring occasionally, until moisture is absorbed.
Place butter and grated cheese in a 1-quart souffle dish and add cooked grits, blending until cheese and butter are melted.
Cool slightly, and beat in eggs.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes or until the top is browned.

title: grandma's cranberry salad
directions: Cook cranberries in as little water as possible.
Add 2 cups sugar when berries have stopped popping.
After sugar has dissolved, remove from heat and add 2 packages cherry Jell-O. Cool and add celery, nuts and pineapple.
Mix well.
Turn into desired container and chill until set.

title: roma's applesauce spice cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a bowl, mix boiling water with raisins; set aside.
In another bowl, cream together butter and dark brown sugar.
Add salt, eggs, cinnamon, cloves and allspice; mix well.
Stir in applesauce, flour, and walnuts.
Add baking soda to the raisin mixture; stir until baking soda is dissolved. Combine the flour mixture and raisin mixture.
Pour batter into a greased 13 x 9 inch baking pan.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes or until the center is set.
Cool.

title: beef casserole italino
directions: Brown beef or turkey and onion; drain off fat.

Stir in tomato sauce, parsley, oregano, basil, 1/4 teaspoon salt and pepper. Simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally. Meanwhile, combine thawed and drained spinach, Ricotta cheese and remaining salt.

title: microwave potatoes
directions: Wash and peel potatoes (can leave skin on).
Cut potatoes in slices.
Put in casserole dish.
Melt butter with water.
Lay 1 layer potatoes in dish and cut onion.
Sprinkle little Mrs. Dash, McMolly butter and cheese.
Add another layer of potatoes and sprinkle with spices.
Can do this 2 to 4 times, depending on amount.
Cover with Saran Wrap and cook in microwave oven about 20 minutes until tender!

title: cream cheese brownie pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Prepare pie crust as directed on package for a 9-inch pie. In medium bowl, combine cream cheese, sugar, vanilla and 1 egg; beat until smooth. Set aside.
Reserve hot fudge packet from brownie mix for topping. In a large bowl, combine brownie mix, 1 tablespoon of the water and 2 eggs. Beat well.

Spread half the brownie mixture in the bottom of a crust lined pan. Spoon cream cheese mixture over the brownie mixture. Top with remaining brownie mixture, spreading evenly. Sprinkle with pecans. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until center is puffed and crust is golden.
To prevent browning, you may need to place foil around crust.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package; salt and pepper to taste and drain.
Stir in Velveeta cheese, sliced.
Line casserole dish with Ritz crackers (crushed).
Pour in broccoli and top with more crushed Ritz crackers.
Place butter pats all over top.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes (hot and bubbly).

title: sloppy joe pizza
directions: Brown meat in skillet; drain.
Add Sloppy Joe sauce, onion (chopped finely) and green pepper (chopped finely).
Mix together. Pour mixture on thawed pizza crust.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 425° for 8 to 11 minutes.

title: kentucky pie
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: martha pafford's tea cakes
directions: Preheat oven to 325° to 350°.
Cream the sugar and shortening; add eggs and vanilla.
Stir well.
Add flour one cup at a time. Knead small amounts of dough until stiff; cut at desired thickness.
(Roll out with a rolling pin before cutting.)
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
bake until brown.

title: zucchini fry
directions: Cut up zucchini, put olive oil and chopped onion in skillet, saute.
Add zucchini and stir.
Add plum tomatoes, cut up.
Cover for 10 minutes.
Add spinach, stir and saute 5 to 10 minutes.

title: blackberry pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour together.
Add butter and mashed berries with juice. Pour in pie shell and cover with top crust which has been gashed to allow for steam to escape.
Bake at 425° for 40 to 45 minutes.
If desired, mash and strain the berries because of the seed.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Boil together four minutes.
Remove from stove.
Add oats and vanilla.
Stir all ingredients together and drop from spoon on wax paper.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: In large saucepan, saute onions and margarine. In bowl, dissolve bouillon cubes in boiling water.
Add bouillon, carrots and celery to onions.
Cook over moderate heat about 10 minutes. In another bowl, gradually add a small amount of the milk to the flour and stir until smooth.
Add remaining milk.
Pour milk mixture, salt, pepper and broccoli into saucepan.
Cook over moderate heat, stirring until bubbles appear.
Serves 8.

title: pap's pretzels
directions: Crush pretzels into pieces, not fine.
Add taco mix and oil. Mix well.
Spread out on cookie sheet and warm (200°) in oven. Store in covered container.

title: raspberry ice
directions: In a blender, combine the diet 7-Up, raspberry sorbet, raspberries and ice cubes and blend until smooth.
Pour into 12-ounce glass and garnish with additional raspberries.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Sift soda with flour 3 times.
Add flour and sour cream alternately to mixture.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Turn into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Remove from pan after cake has cooled.
This is like a pound cake and keeps well.

title: mock chow mein
directions: Cut pork steak in small pieces and brown with hamburger and soy sauce.
Remove from stove.
Add onions to celery.
Add water, rice and soups.
Mix well.
Put into casserole dish.
Bake 1 hour in a moderate oven.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Sift the flour, sugar, salt, baking soda and cocoa together. Add the mayonnaise, vanilla and water. Mix well. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until done in a greased and floured 9 x 13 pan.

title: spiced cider
directions: Pour apple cider and ginger ale in coffee pot (12 to 25 cups). Put whole cloves, red hots and whole cinnamon in basket of percolator.
When percolator stops, cider is ready.

title: grandma's jumbo sugar cookies
directions: Mix shortening, vanilla, butter and eggs.
Blend in baking powder, flour and salt.
Chill 1 hour.
Roll out and cut in large circles; sprinkle with sugar.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet 6 to 8 minutes at 400°.

title: salad dressing
directions: Shake 3
ingredients until well blended. Add 1/4 cup vinegar (white) and shake until blended.

title: crumb topping
directions: Crumb Topping can be used on warm cake instead of frosting. Mix together sugar, flour, soft butter, walnuts and a sprinkle of cinnamon.
Will cover top of cake in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Sprinkle powdered sugar over top with ready to serve.

title: mayflower's tomato soup
directions: Saute the onions in oil, add sugar and cook until caramelized (light gold).
Add remaining ingredients, except cream, mix well and simmer for 45 minutes.
Add cream, heat, but do not boil, and serve.
Makes about 12 cups.

title: banana pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream together shortening, margarine and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt, gradually add to creamed mixture.
Add milk and vanilla.
Fold in bananas.
Pour into a prepared tube pan and bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: pizza bunny
directions: Pizza Bunny Crust:
Combine rice, eggs, and 1 cup Cheddar cheese.
Spoon onto greased 17 x 14-inch baking sheet.
Pat into bunny shape, moistening hands to prevent sticking.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.

title: apple strudel
directions: Unfold the phyllo dough carefully; on wax paper, place 2 to 3 phyllo sheets.
On these, brush butter, then sprinkle with apples, sugar, cinnamon and bread crumbs.
On top of this, place more phyllo sheets, butter and repeat the first process; do this 3 times.
Roll up the sheets with the filling; tuck the ends under. Place in greased pan, seam side down; brush with butter and bake in oven at 350° or until golden brown.
Let cool and sprinkle with sugar; serve with ice cream.

title: blueberry jello
directions: Mix jello with boiling water until dissolved.
Add crushed pineapple with juice and pie filling. Let set overnight.

title: divinity
directions: Bring to a boil the sugar, water and corn syrup. When mixture forms wispy threads when dropped from spoon, start pouring into egg whites, 1/4 at a time.
Don't scrape pan.
Beat with wooden spoon until it forms peaks.
Make it take air. Will turn from glossy to a dull shine. Drop onto wax paper. Should have stiff peaks on top.
When firm, transfer to plate and cover.
Do not try this on a humid day.

title: barbecue "meat" balls
directions: Mix ingredients and form into balls.
Place on oiled cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Put in baking dish.

title: crab dip
directions: Spread softened cream cheese on bottom of dish.
Cover with chopped scallions.
Sprinkle with Worcestershire sauce.
Mix catsup, horseradish and Tabasco.
Spread on top of scallions. Cover with crabmeat, top with lemon juice and chopped parsley. Serve with crackers and enjoy.

title: potato dumplings
directions: Grind potatoes in meat grinder.
Add salt and flour to form stiff dough.
Form into dumplings and drop into boiling salted ham water.

title: southern cobbler
directions: Put butter in a baking dish.
Place in a 350° oven to melt. Mix sugar, flour, baking powder, salt and milk together.
Pour into a baking dish.
(Do not stir.)
Spoon fruit on top of butter and bake for 1 hour.

title: shrimp skillet
directions: Place soup in skillet.
Pour boiling water over.
Cover. Bring to boiling. Stir in rice, shrimp, celery and green peppers. Cover. Return to boil. Reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes or until done.

title: september sauce
directions: Put the tomatoes through the blender. Cut the peppers and onions into quarter-inch squares and add to tomatoes.
Add other ingredients.
Simmer until rather thick.
Bottle in sterile jars. Seal and invert to guarantee the seal.

title: moon cake
directions: Mix water and margarine.
Bring to boil.
Add flour all at once.
Stir rapidly until mixture forms a ball.
Remove from heat and cool a little while.
Beat in eggs, one at a time, beating well with mixer or spoon.
Spread on ungreased cookie sheet (11 x 15-inch).
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Cool (it will look like the moon surface).
Do not prick; leave it alone.

title: cheddary chicken pot pie
directions: In saucepan, combine soup, 1/2 cup milk, onion, cream cheese, celery, carrots, Parmesan cheese, salt and potatoes.
Cook and stir until cream cheese is melted.
Stir in chicken and broccoli; heat through.
Pour in a 2-quart baking dish.

title: lemonade pineapple pie
directions: Beat with mixer, adding Cool Whip last.
Put into 2 graham crusts.
Keep in refrigerator.
Makes 2 pies.

title: chocolate ice cream
directions: Dissolve chocolate pudding in evaporated milk with wire whisk. Add sugar, vanilla flavoring, salt and milk; mix well. Pour into electric ice cream churn and freeze as directed.

title: easy chicken breasts
directions: Place chicken in the bottom of a very large baking dish. Sprinkle chicken with soup mix.
Place all the other ingredients in dish.
Pour water over.
Bake, loosely covered, for 3 or 4 hours at 325°.
Check chicken after 3 hours to see if done.

title: coconut cake frosting
directions: Cook milk and flour in saucepan over medium heat until thick. Cool in refrigerator.
Combine sugar, shortening and margarine with mixer.
Add chilled mixture and beat until sugar is dissolved.
Spread on cake.
Pat on coconut.
Use with Betty Crocker butter pudding-in-the-mix cake mix.
Better if made in 3 layers.

title: ma's carrot cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Blend well.
Grease and flour pan and bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.

title: corn soup
directions: Chop onion coarsely; cook in broth 15 minutes.
Put corn in blender; add onion and broth.
Blend to smooth and put in casserole.
Add milk and cream.
Taste for seasoning.
Heat through but do not boil.
A little Accent adds to taste.

title: chewies, a favorite
directions: Melt margarine; stir in brown sugar real good.
Add eggs all at one time and beat real good.
Add flour, one cup at a time, and add nuts when you add the last cup of flour.
Mix well.
Spread in an 11 x 15-inch pan and bake at 325° for about 25 minutes.
The center will be a little soft but that's okay.
You can use cold oven or preheat.
Cold oven may take about 5 minutes longer.

title: hot tamales
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Roll in tamale papers or aluminum foil. Cook in boiling water about 30 to 45 minutes.

title: golden cake
directions: Sift together the flour, baking soda, spices and salt.
Cream the butter and sugar.
Add egg and beat well.
Add dry ingredients alternately with cider.
Stir in raisins.
Pour into greased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Put browned hamburger in baking dish.
Cover with cream of mushroom soup.
Add cheese (I like Velveeta).
Cover with Tater Tots.
Bake for 1/2 hour in 350° oven.

title: fresh apple muffins
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking powder, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt into mixing bowl.
In separate bowl, mix remaining ingredients. Pour apple mixture over dry ingredients and stir just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Fill greased muffin tins 3/4 full. Bake 20 minutes at 400°.

title: crema(molded custard)
directions: Combine eggs, salt and 1 cup of the sugar.
Add milk slowly, stirring constantly.
Add flavoring and mix well.
Melt or caramelize the remaining sugar in a heavy pan or skillet and glaze the bottom of a large tube pan.
Pour custard mixture over the caramelized sugar.

title: pasta salad
directions: Mix cooked pasta with onion, carrots, green pepper and olives. Mix other ingredients and toss into pasta mixture.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Note:
Canned raspberries, blueberries or loganberries may be substituted for peaches.

title: graham cracker pudding #1
directions: In a double boiler, heat milk.
Combine separately 1/2 cup sugar, flour, 1 whole egg, 2 egg yolks and salt.
Stir into hot milk and cook until thickened.
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla and graham cracker crumbs.
Beat 2 egg whites to stiff peaks.
Add sugar and fold into pudding.
Chill.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: chicken enchilada
directions: Chop and saute celery, onions and peppers in butter.
Mix all ingredients together, except tortillas and cheese.
In baking dish, put in tortillas and pour sauce mixture over and then cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: knox blox squares
directions: Mix all together and put in a 9 x 12-inch pan and refrigerate. Cut into squares.
Cover.
Great for kids!

title: bean casserole
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and bacon together.
Add beans; add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve with corn muffins.

title: red and green tomato pie
directions: Brush raw pie shell with evaporated milk or cream; bake in preheated oven at 450° for 5 minutes only. Cool slightly.

Place the sliced tomatoes in the precooked shell. Mix together the mayonnaise, cheese and garlic, then spread over tomatoes. Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350° until tomatoes are tender. Heats up well in microwave.

title: cynthia's chinese
directions: Warm up 2 cans of beef chow mein with one can of supplied vegies.
Let simmer 7 minutes.
Add the rest of ingredients; salt and pepper to taste.

title: cranberry nog
directions: Chill all ingredients; pour into blender container.
Blend until frothy.
Serve in punch cups; garnish with dollops of whipped cream and nutmeg.
Yields 2 servings.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Beat sugar, flour and eggs with a spoon.
Add pineapple with juice.
Pour into buttered casserole.
Stir melted butter into bread cubes until bread is soaked with butter.
Sprinkle bread cubes on top of casserole.
Bake 1 hour at 350 degrees.

title: seafood chowder
directions: In a large saucepan, cook rice mix according to package directions. Meanwhile, in a large bowl, whisk together milk and sour cream until well blended. Gently fold in shrimp, crabmeat, clams, cheese and seasoning. Add mixture to rice mix in saucepan. heat until cheese melts, but do not boil. Stir in corn chilies and lime juice. Serve immediately garnish with chopped parsley.

title: ultra low-fat barbecue burger patties
directions: Combine all ingredients in
a large bowl and mix.

Form into 6 patties and cook in skillet sprayed with nonstick cooking spray or grill on outdoor grill. If grilling outdoors, be sure to spray grill with nonstick cooking spray before heating or lighting. Cook over medium to low heat about 3 to 4 minutes on each side. Serves 6. Contains 1 gram of fat and 123 calories per serving.

title: canned squash
directions: Cover squash with water, salt and vinegar.
Boil 20 minutes. Put in jars and seal.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Pat crescent rolls in cookie sheet; prick with fork.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.
Beat until blended the cream cheese, mayonnaise and Hidden Valley Ranch dressing mix.
Spread over cooled crust.
Top with cauliflower, chopped onion, chopped cucumbers, green pepper, chopped tomatoes, grated carrots or any of your favorite veggies.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Chill.

title: fresh peach ice cream
directions: Combine peaches, sugar, lemon juice, orange juice and bananas. Stir to dissolve sugar. Pour into the container of a 1 gallon ice cream freezer.
Add cream and evaporated milk.
Pour in enough milk to fill container 3/4 full.
Freeze.
Serves 16.

title: cherries in the snow
directions: Prepare Dream Whip according to directions on box; beat until light and fluffy.
Add 1 cup powdered sugar.
Add cream cheese and beat until blended.
Add cubed angel food cake to 3/4 of Dream Whip mixture.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with cherry pie filling. Spread remaining Dream Whip over top and swirl with a butter knife so cherries show through.
Refrigerate.

title: boiled cookies(done on stove top, no oven.)
directions: Bring first 4 ingredients to a full boil and boil 1 minute. Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon on waxed paper; let stand about one hour.

title: tuna dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
