Place 1 small loaf of rye bread (light or dark or both) around tuna dip.
Crackers are good, too!

title: fudge pie
directions: Melt chocolate over hot water.
Cool.
Cream butter.
Add sifted sugar.
Beat until creamy.
Add egg yolks, then melted chocolate.
Beat in flour.
Add vanilla and salt to egg whites and beat until stiff.
Fold into batter.
Bake in greased 8 1/2-inch pie plate at 325° for 30 minutes.
Serve with ice cream.

title: irish coffee(yields 1 serving)
directions: Place ingredients, except whipped cream, in a large ceramic or glass mug.
Heat in microwave on High for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes or until warmed. Do not boil.
Add whipped cream.

title: cheese rice krispies
directions: Mash flour and oleo together.
Add cheese, salt and seasoning.
Add Rice Krispies.
Form into small balls.
Bake 18 minutes at 350°.

title: kentucky pound cake
directions: Mix first six ingredients together, then add crushed pineapple (drained) and 1 cup nuts. Bake at 325 degrees for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until done. Pour pineapple juice over cake while cake is still warm.

title: monkey bread #1
directions: Cut biscuits in half; coat each with brown sugar and cinnamon (mix together).
Place all halves in greased pan.
(Use loaf pan or pound cake pan.)
Melt the margarine and pour it over bread. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: susie's peach preserve cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs.
Mix dry ingredients and add alternately with buttermilk.
Stir in pecans and preserves. Bake in greased and floured Bundt or tube pan at 350° for 1 hour and ten minutes or until tests done with toothpick.
Glaze with the following:

title: marcia's jello salad
directions: Combine cottage cheese, Jell-O and Cool Whip.
Fold in fruit cocktail, drained oranges and cherries.
Refrigerate.

title: baked potato salad
directions: Mix the potatoes with the cheese, onion and mayonnaise and spread into large casserole dish. Top with the crumbled bacon. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until cheese is melted through.

title: white sauce
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate.

title: broccoli orange salad
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a bowl. Set aside. Combine the mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.
Add to broccoli mixture, stirring to coat. Gently stir in mandarin oranges.
Cover and refrigerate at least 3 hours.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix together as usual.
Chill dough until firm.
Roll in small balls size of walnut.
Press with glass dipped in sugar.
Colored sugar makes them pretty.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes (no longer). The best sugar cookie ever - melts in your mouth.

title: quick beef stroganoff
directions: Start a large pot of water on high to boil.
Add noodles to the boiling water.
Next, melt butter in a skillet.
Add chopped onion and saute until translucent.
Add meat and brown.
When meat is browned, add garlic powder and turn heat down.
When noodles are done, drain and add 1 or 2 tablespoons of sour cream to noodles and stir.
Add rest of sour cream to meat mixture (1 big spoonful at a time) and stir.
Sprinkle paprika in with the meat and sour cream mixture.
Place noodles on a large plate and pour meat mixture on top.

title: sparkle mystery salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water; add Tabasco and stewed tomatoes, chopped up.
Chill until firm in a lightly oiled 3-quart ring mold.
Unmold on greens and fill center with sour cream flavored with horseradish, salt and sugar.
Makes 12 servings.

title: cheesey ritz bits buttons
directions: Put Ritz bits in foil pan.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over crackers-make sure all the crackers are covered. Refrigerate 24 hours.
remove from fridge about 2 hours before eating.

title: lemon pork chops
directions: Heat cooker; add oil and brown the pork chops on both sides. Top each chop with a lemon slice.
Add onion, salt and pepper. Combine catsup and water; pour over chops.
Close cover securely. Place pressure regulator on vent pipe and cook 10 minutes with pressure regulator rocking slowly.
Cool cooker at once.
Serve chops with the sauce.

title: taco corn bread pizza
directions: Mix corn muffin mix as directed.
Spread batter in greased 12-inch pizza pan. Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Brown meat and drain.
Add seasonings and prepare as directed on package.
Sprinkle 1 cup cheese on top of crust.
Top with meat and then remaining cheese.
Bake 4 to 5 minutes or until cheese melts.
Serve with toppings such as shredded lettuce, chopped tomatoes, chopped onions, sour cream, etc.

title: tropical cheese balls
directions: Combine softened
cream cheese and pineapple; mix well. Add remaining	ingredients;
mix
well.
Chill.
Shape
into ball, slightly
flatten top.
Garnish with coconut if desired. Serve with assorted crackers.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix together flour, butter and powdered sugar and put in pan, 8 x 8 x 2-inch or 9 x 9 x 2-inch.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Beat eggs, sugar, baking powder, salt and lemon juice until fluffy, 3 minutes.
Pour over crust.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Put powdered sugar on top while still warm.

title: pasta fresca
directions: Bring a large covered pot of water to a rapid boil.
Set aside 1 cup of the chopped tomatoes and 2 of the basil leaves.
In a blender or food processor, puree the remaining tomatoes and basil with the garlic and olive oil until smooth.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
When water comes to rolling boil, stir in the pasta, re-cover the pot and return to a boil.
Uncover and cook pasta until al dente, 8 to 10 minutes.
Cut the reserved basil into thin strips.
Drain the cooked pasta and toss immediately with Mozzarella cubes.
Add sauce, mix well.
Top with remaining tomatoes, basil and grated cheese, if desired.
Serve immediately.

title: baked chicken
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Dip chicken in Wesson oil, then roll in crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: oreo pie
directions: Mix pudding according to package directions.
Place a layer of Oreos in the bottom of a casserole dish, then a layer of pudding and a layer of Cool Whip.
Start over with Oreos.
Make layers until all ingredients are used, ending with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle cookie crumbs on top.

title: apricot nectar cake
directions: Mix cake mix, sugar, oil and apricot nectar together. Add eggs, one at a time.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour. Cool 15 minutes. Remove from pan and glaze with 2 cups powdered sugar and juice from 1 lemon.
Pour over still warm cake.

title: oven-fried chicken
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Wash chicken and pat dry.
In oven, melt shortening and butter in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Mix flour, salt, paprika and pepper.
Coat chicken pieces thoroughly with flour mixture.

title: hawaiian pie
directions: Beat the cream cheese until soft.
Fold in other ingredients. Pour in pie crust. Place in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: fluffy potato casserole
directions: Saute onion in small amount of butter until soft, or use dehydrated onion.
In large mixing bowl, beat potatoes, cream cheese, onion, eggs and flour.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Top with French fried onions.
Bake, uncovered, for 35 minutes at 300°.

title: peanut butter cake
directions: Boil together water, peanut butter, margarine and salt.
Mix together flour, sugar, baking soda, eggs and buttermilk.
Combine all.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: big soft cookie
directions: This is a cake-like cookie.
Mix ingredients together and chill for 1 hour.
Drop onto cookie sheet and bake at 375°. Glaze, if desired.

title: icebox cake
directions: Beat cream until thick.
Stack cookies 6 high and spread cream between each cookie.
Lay stacks down sideways, one stack behind the other, icing tops and sides.
Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours. Slice on an angle when serving.

title: potato latkes (pancakes)
directions: Shred potatoes and onion; transfer to bowl.
Stir in flour and next 3 ingredients until blended.
Drop mixture by 2 tablespoonfuls into hot oil in a large skillet.
Fry over medium-high heat, turning once until browned.
Drain on paper towels.

title: tuna macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni.
Drain; rinse with cold water.
Combine macaroni, cheese, tuna, pickle and onion in large bowl.
Stir together with the rest of the ingredients.
Pour over macaroni mixture and toss.
Cover and chill at least 3 hours.

title: crab mousse(make this appetizer using any 4 cup mold or 2 cup mold)
directions: Coat a 4 cup mold with cooking spray and set aside.
Sprinkle gelatin over skim milk in a small saucepan.
Let stand 1 minute. Add cream cheese and cook over low heat, stirring until gelatin dissolves and mixture is smooth.
Add yogurt, stirring until well blended.

title: homemade chili
directions: *I buy Ranch pinto beans, 1 can plain and 1 can with jalapenos.
It's a little warm, but good.

title: zucchini parmesan
directions: Brown meat and sausage.
Season with salt, pepper and garlic powder to taste. Drain well.
In greased casserole dish, alternate layers, starting with meat sausage, zucchini, mushrooms, onions and cheese, ending with cheese on the final top layer.
Pour tomato sauce over all, but don't use all (3/4 of a large can). Bake at 350° for 1 hour, uncovered.
You can also substitute summer squash or eggplant for the zucchini.

title: beef tapa
directions: Slice beef thinly, to desired size, preferably across the grain.
In a bowl, mix the rest of the ingredients and spread this on the meat.
Allow beef to marinate for at least 24 hours in refrigerator.
Fry in hot fat and serve.

title: ruth's christmas cookies
directions: Cream sugar and oleo.
Add vanilla and flour.
Mix well. Shape in crescents or balls.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet.
Remove from cookie sheet and roll in powdered sugar.

title: angel food donuts
directions: Combine the ingredients; mix well.
Turn onto floured board. Roll 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with floured cutter.
Fry in hot greased; drain on paper towels.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients well and spoon onto nongreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: no peek casserole
directions: Combine ingredients well in 2-quart casserole.
Cover.
Bake at 300° for 3 hours.
Don't peek until it's done.
Serve over rice or noodles.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: hungarian goulash
directions: Melt shortening in pan. Brown meat on all sides. Stir in onion. Combine mustard, paprika, salt and sugar. Combine Worcestershire, vinegar, ketchup and 3 cups of water. Add to the mustard mixture. Add combined ingredients to meat. Blend. Cover. Reduce heat. Cook 2 1/2 hours or until meat is very tender. Stir occasionally. Blend flour with remaining water. Add to meat mixture. Stir until thickened. Serve over cooked noodles. Serves 14 to 16.

title: wonderful whole wheat waffles
directions: Mix together dry ingredients.
Add honey, milk and water, then yolks and oil.
Beat until smooth.
Fold in whites.
Bake on medium heat waffle iron.

title: carol's cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together except pie filling.
Put cake into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Put cherry pie filling over cake.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Take out of oven and put a thin glaze of icing over top of cake while still warm.

title: chicken delight
directions: Cut chicken into cubes and layer in the bottom of a lightly greased deep casserole.
Layer cheese over chicken.
Spread the soup like icing over cheese.
In a separate bowl mix stuffing and broth together to make it wet.
Place on top of other ingredients. Bake at 350 degrees, covered for 50-60 minutes.

title: easy hamburger casserole
directions: Crumble ground beef in casserole dish.
Arrange onion ring slices on top.
Cover with Tater Tots.
Spoon mushroom soup on top.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: mexican fruit cake
directions: Mix flour, soda, eggs, sugar, pineapple and pecans.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan at 350° for 45 minutes.
Pour frosting over cake when out of oven.

title: vegetable macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni.
Drain.
Cool and add vegetables and mix. Combine milk, vinegar, sugar, mayonnaise, salt and pepper.
Add macaroni to mixture.
Mix thoroughly and chill at least 4 hours.

title: orange sherbet
directions: Mix ingredients.
Chill.
Place in electric or hand-cranked freezer.
Freeze by directions of your freezer.
Makes 1 gallon of sherbet.

title: colossal cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars.
Add vanilla and eggs, beat well. Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Drop spoonfuls on greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 6 to 8 minutes.

title: nacho dip
directions: Mix refried beans and jalapeno beans with taco seasoning mix. Pour in bottom of a 2-quart casserole dish.
Spread sour cream over beans.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Microwave 7 minutes.
Eat with nacho chips.

title: wadmalaw onion spread
directions: Slice onions very thin.
Combine with vinegar, sugar and water; let stand in refrigerator 3 to 4 hours.
Drain liquid from onions thoroughly (let drain about 1 hour).
Combine onions with mayonnaise and celery salt.
Serve with Melba rounds.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Mix sugar, egg and sour cream.
Add dry ingredients, then stir in blueberries.
Put in muffin pans and bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: corn chowder
directions: Melt butter in skillet; add onion and saute until soft.
Add potatoes, 2 cups boiling water, salt and pepper.
Cook until potatoes are tender.
Add corn and milk, bring to a boil.
Add additional seasonings, if necessary.
Serves 6.

title: maureen's pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs well with sugar, salt, syrup and butter.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pie shell (9-inch).
Bake in a 350° oven until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: whiskey slush
directions: Bring 7 cups of water and sugar to a boil.
Cool.
Make tea with 2 cups of boiling water.
Cool.
Combine sugar mixture, tea, orange juice, lemonade and whiskey.
Freeze 2 days.

title: swiss steak
directions: Coat aluminum foil with butter and place in center of pan. Arrange pieces of meat on foil slightly overlapping.
Put soup mix, tomatoes, seasonings and sliced pepper over top of steak. Mix cornstarch, A.1. sauce and tomato juice.
Pour over meat. Cover with foil.
Bake 2 hours at 375°.

title: chicken sour cream enchiladas
directions: Boil chicken in large pot.
While chicken is boiling, in another pot add diced onion, Ortega chillies, whole tomatoes, tomato sauce, seasoning and Salsa Ranchera.
Simmer salsa mixture at low heat until chicken is done.
Remove chicken from pan into a large bowl, skin chicken and remove from bone (if applies).
Shred chicken.
Add to chicken, sour cream, 1 cup salsa mixture and approximately 1 cup of shredded cheese.
Mix well.
Remove salsa mixture from stove.
Using cup to pour with pour approximately 3/4 cup of salsa mixture into bottom of large baking pan.
Using one flour tortilla at a time, pour approximately 3/4 cup of chicken/sour cream mixture onto a flour tortilla.
Roll up tortilla and place in baking pan.
Continue placing filled tortillas in a row in baking pan until full (one layer only).
Cover with remaining salsa and sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for one hour, uncovered.
Yields approximately 20 enchiladas.

title: cranberry cream salad
directions: Add cranberry sauce to dissolved Jell-O.
Mix well and chill until thickened.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into dish and chill until firm.

title: chicken and stuffing casserole
directions: Boil chicken in water until partially done.
Break in pieces and put in 9 x 13-inch pan that is sprayed with Pam.
Combine the milk, sour cream and soup (do not mix soup with water, use as is). Do not cook.
Just mix and pour over chicken.

title: pancake syrup
directions: Be careful in your selection.
Do not choose too young and take only such as have been carefully raised.
Some wives keep them in a pickle while others insist on keeping them in hot water.
This only makes them sour, hard and sometimes bitter.
Even poor varieties may be made sweet, tender and good by garnishing them with patience, well sweetened smiles and flavored with kisses.
Then, wrap them in a mantle of charity.
Keep warm with a steady fire of domestic devotion, and serve with angel food and peaches and cream. When thus prepared, they will last forever!!!

title: southern living's broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions; drain well. Place broccoli in a lightly greased 11 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish. Sprinkle with cheese and set aside.
Combine eggs and next 3 ingredients; spread over cheese.
Set aside.
Combine stuffing mix and butter; sprinkle over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until thoroughly heated.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake in tube pan 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: pie crust
directions: With pastry blender blend flour and Crisco until size of peas. Add milk and blend just until of dough consistency.

title: black-eyed pea salad
directions: Prepare vegetables; combine in a bowl.
Combine garlic, sugar, oil, vinegar, Worcestershire sauce and soup; stir to mix well. Refrigerate for 24 hours.
Will keep for several days.

title: alabama cornbread
directions: Beat egg until fluffy.
Mix all ingredients well and pour into greased 14 x 10 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 400° until golden brown.

title: crab, carrot, basil bisque soup
directions: Saute onions in butter.
Add carrots, 1/2 of the crab meat, basil and potatoes.
Cover with clam juice and cook 1/2 hour.
Let cool slightly and puree.
Add cream and remaining crab meat.
Heat and serve.

title: cherry cornbread(cake)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9 1/2 x 2-inch pan.
Blend all dry ingredients.
Add butter, eggs and milk.
Stir until mixed well.
Put into pan.
Spoon pie filling on top, leaving space between spoonfuls.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes.
Drizzle powdered sugar frosting on top while still warm.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Mix ingredients and pour in 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Cook at 350° until brown, approximately 40 to 45 minutes.

title: moist and rich coconut cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on box.
Allow to cool.
Poke holes in cake several inches apart using end of wooden spoon.
Mix cream of coconut with milk and pour over cake.
Cover cake with Cool Whip. Sprinkle coconut on top of cake.
Refrigerate.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Bake pie shell.
In a large saucepan, stir dry jello, sugar and flour thoroughly.
Add water slowly, stirring as you add it. Cook until thick (about 15 minutes), stirring often.
Cool.
Add cold, whole strawberries.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Spread on whipped topping.
Refrigerate until set.
Store in refrigerator.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Combine vegetables, mayonnaise, cheese, onion and soup; mix well.
Pour into baking dish.
Combine cracker crumbs and melted butter and spread on top of veggies.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: russian tea
directions: Iced tea tastes even better when poured over ice cubes made of tea.
Simply pour cold or room temperature tea into ice cube trays and freeze.
Empty into freezer bag and keep on hand in the freezer.

title: texas hash
directions: Brown beef, onions and pepper until tender.
Drain off fat and add rest of ingredients.
Pour into ungreased 2-quart casserole.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Bake or microwave chicken until done, then cube.
Cook rice as directed.
Saute onion in butter.
Blend in flour, soup and milk. Add mushrooms and seasoning.
Mix in bowl, then put in casserole dish.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 300° until heated through (30 minutes).

title: sweet corn relish
directions: Combine corn, cabbage, onions, green and red pepper in a large kettle.
Mix together mustard, flour and turmeric; add vinegar to mustard mixture.
Stir to blend well.
Add mustard mixture, remaining vinegar, sugar and salt to vegetables, mixing well.
Bring vegetables to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 15 minutes.
Ladle into hot jars.
Adjust lids. Process in boiling water bath, 15 minutes.
Makes 8 pints.

title: golden potato balls
directions: Melt butter in a shallow pan.
Add the potatoes.
Shake pan to coat the potatoes; sprinkle with salt.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and shake pan; sprinkle with salt again.
Bake for another 30 minutes.

title: chicken casserole(good!!)
directions: Boil chicken until tender with salt and pepper.
Debone chicken.
Mix oleo with stuffing mix.
Layer 1/2 of stuffing mix in bottom of casserole dish.
Put chicken as next layer, then combine sour cream and soup.
Put as next layer.
Add the other 1/2 of stuffing mix.
Pour broth over it.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes until brown.
Don't cover.

title: banana cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs; beat until light and foamy; set aside.
Sift flour, baking powder and baking soda; add to mixture.
Add vanilla and milk; mix well.
Add mashed banana; mix well.
Make 2 layers or 1 loaf pan.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: nantucket morning glory muffins
directions: In a large bowl, sift together flour, sugar, baking soda and cinnamon.
Stir in apples, nuts, carrots, raisins and coconut.
Mix well!
(Also works to hold fruit and nuts out to stir into wet ingredients.)
In a separate bowl, beat just until smooth the eggs, oil and vanilla.
Combine with flour mixture; stir only until dry ingredients are moistened.
Spoon into greased or lined muffin pans.
Fill 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: cranberry tea(great for a chilly morning!)
directions: Put all ingredients in a large pot.
Simmer for 1/2 hour and serve in a pretty mug!

title: waldorf pasta salad
directions: Cook macaroni
according to package directions, using 1 teaspoon salt in water; drain and set aside.
In a large bowl, combine oil, lemon juice, sugar, poppy seeds, mustard and remaining 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Add drained macaroni, walnuts, apples, celery, cheese, raisins, and chicken, if desired.
Toss to blend well.
Serve with crackers.

title: salmon quiche
directions: Mix and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until firm.
Serves 4.
Good any time, but makes an excellent, economical company dish.

title: layered microwave cake
directions: Mix together; set aside in refrigerator.
Mix cake mix together, lightly as per ingredients on box.
Divide batter into 3 parts and place each in round glass cake pans lined with wax paper.
Bake each cake on Medium power for 5 minutes or until done.
Layer cake with pudding mix, saving 1/3 for top icing.

title: simple minestrone
directions: Brown chopped beef; add chopped onion and garlic.
Add can tomatoes, can of water and can of mixed vegetables.
Let simmer for 10 minutes.
Add 1 cup of ditalini or other small pasta.
Cook for 15 minutes until pasta is cooked.
Add more water if soup is too thick.
Serve hot with some grated cheese.

title: tex mex dip
directions: Spread refried beans in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
In a separate bowl, mix cream cheese and taco seasoning.
It is easier if you put cream cheese in the microwave for 30 to 45 seconds to soften before adding the mix.
Spread cheese mixture on top of refried beans.
Top with remaining ingredients.

title: he man ham casserole
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in butter or margarine.
Add flour and pepper; stir until smooth.
Gradually stir in milk and broth.
Cook, stirring until thickened.
Combine with ham and beans in a 3-quart casserole.
Combine mashed potatoes, egg and cheese.
Drop by spoonfuls onto mixture in casserole.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until bubbly.
Makes 10 servings.

title: large chocolate chip cookie
directions: Line 12-inch pizza pan with waxed paper.

title: peppermint dessert
directions: Crush wafers and put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Reserve small amount for top.
Melt oleo and chocolate.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Mix egg yolks, vanilla, sugar, chocolate and oleo.
Fold in egg whites and pecans.
Spread over crumbs.
Put soft peppermint ice cream over top with reserved small amount of crushed wafers on top.
Freeze.

title: that fruit salad
directions: Mix pudding with juice of pineapple and oranges.
Add rest of ingredients.
Add poppy seed, bananas, coconut and nuts to suit your taste.
Refrigerate.

title: lemonade pie
directions: In large bowl, combine Cool Whip, lemonade and milk; blend well.
Pour into crust and chill until firm, about 2 hours.

title: baked fish fillets with vegetables
directions: With the exception of tomatoes, place vegetables in saucepan, barely covered with water.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Place fillets in shallow pan.
Drain parboiled vegetables.
Place vegetables and tomatoes over and around fillets.
Bake in a 375° oven for 20 minutes or until fish flakes easily.

title: pasta pizza salad
directions: Toss all until well coated.
Add Parmesan cheese last and toss again.
Make ahead of time as it tastes better.
Enjoy!!

title: lemon-go-lightly cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off.
In a large bowl, blend flour and remaining ingredients except 1/4 cup of sugar until well mixed.
(Mixture will be crumbly.)
Firmly press mixture into 1-inch balls.
Roll in 1/4 cup of sugar.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheets. Bake at 350° for 9 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool 1 minute.
Remove from cookie sheets.
Makes 6 dozen cookies.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix eggs and salt together.
In bowl combine milk, cornstarch and baking powder.
Add egg mixture to boil, mix well.
Pour corn into small pan.
Cover corn with mixture and add butter on top. Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Mix all together.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: german potato salad
directions: In a large skillet, fry bacon crisp.
Remove and set aside. Drain and discard all but 3 tablespoons of drippings.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Partially defrost hash browns.
Mix potatoes, 1/2 cup margarine, cheese, onion, sour cream, soup and spices.
Put in greased 9 x 13-inch pan or dish.
Sprinkle corn flakes on top. Pour 1/4 cup margarine over corn flakes and bake, uncovered, for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix cake mix, Jell-O, oil, eggs and buttermilk together.
Set aside.
Mix strawberries, pecans and coconut; divide in half.
Add first half to cake batter and mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Mix second half of strawberry mixture with margarine and powdered sugar.
Ice cake after it cools with this.

title: italian green beans
directions: Brown sausage and onions, drain.
Add mushrooms (cut into pieces).
Add tomatoes and mash with potato masher.
Drain beans and add with seasoning to meat mixture and simmer on low 10 to 12 minutes or until hot.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Simmer 15 to 20 minutes.

title: ham salad
directions: Mix vegetables, ham and cooked shells together.
Add Ranch dressing to suit taste.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Boil chicken in seasonings.
Cool and debone.
Add rice and soup to chicken pieces.
Add some of the seasoned chicken stock to desired consistency.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or microwave for 10 minutes on High.

title: snacker crackers
directions: Mix dressing with oil and dill weed. Put crackers in large Ziploc bag and shake with oil dressing.
Place in microwave 1 minute.
Take out; shake well.
Return to microwave 1 more minute. Spread to cool, 20-30 minutes.

title: blintz souffle
directions: Melt butter in 2-quart casserole and place blintzes over butter in one layer.
Blend other ingredients with well beaten eggs and pour over the blintzes.
Bake 45 minutes in 350° oven or until top starts to brown.
Serve with powdered sugar, strawberries, raspberries or sour cream.
Great for a brunch.

title: buttermilk bran muffin mix
directions: Combine bran cereal, flour, buttermilk powder, sugar, cinnamon and baking soda in food processor.
Add butter (cut up in pads) and vanilla.
Divide batter up into 4 equal parts.
Can be kept up to 2 months refrigerated.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in 2 pie shells (8-inch). Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cut in thin slices (it is very rich!).
Tastes like pecan pie.

title: crustless coconut pie
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl.
Mix well, pour in 2 greased 9-inch pie plates and bake at 350 degrees for 30-40 mins.

title: streusselkuchen(kuczinskikuchen)
directions: Mix flour, milk and yeast.
Add butter, sugar and egg.
Mix butter mixture into flour mixture.
Spread in buttered jelly loaf pan.
The thinner the better.
Than add the streussel:
butter, sugar and flour.
Bake for 10 minutes at 250°, then 300° until brown.
Instead of streussel, fruit can be added, peaches, plums and apples.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix the first three ingredients until smooth.
Add the next four ingredients combined.
Now add the next three ingredients, one at a time.
Now mix all the ingredients together well.
No other liquid is necessary.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: dorothy's vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except onions.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.
At half way point, top casserole with onions and finish baking.

title: stuffed-cabbage soup
directions: Heat oil in 6-quart pot.
Add beef chunks; brown about 6 minutes.
Add coleslaw mix and onion.
Cook, covered, for 4 minutes, stirring after about 2 minutes of cooking.
Add tomatoes, beef broth, water, brown sugar, lemon juice and salt.
Bring to a boil.
Add rice; reduce to a simmer.
Cover; cook 45 minutes.

title: savory pork chops
directions: Brown chops; drain off grease and place in baking dish. Combine remaining ingredients in frypan that chops were fried in to heat.
Pour over chops.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour.
The sauce is good when served over rice or boiled potatoes.

title: cheese salad
directions: Heat pineapple with juice and sugar until sugar dissolves. Stir to keep from sticking.
Dilute gelatin in 1/4 cup cold water. Stir gelatin into pineapple mixture after gelatin begins to congeal. Add grated cheese to pineapple mixture then fold in whipped cream. Let congeal.
Best put into a mold as salad is difficult to cut.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Cook
eggplant	until
mushy;
drain
and add remaining ingredients.
Reserve
1/2	cup cheese, 1/2 cup cracker crumbs and small
amount of butter for topping.
Mix well and pour in baking dish.
Sprinkle
cheese
and
cracker
mixture on top. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes; or until brown.

title: pear relish
directions: Grind together the pears,
peppers
and onions; add the salt and let stand 1 hour.
Drain off and discard liquid.
Add to the relish mixture
the
vinegar,
sugar,
mustard seed and turmeric and bring to a boil.
Boil
5 minutes.
Put into pint jars with 2-piece canning
lids
and seal according to package directions.

title: bean soup
directions: Soak beans overnight in water.
In the morning, add salt, pepper and ham.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 2 1/2 hours.
Serve with Scalded Corn Cakes (recipe follows).

title: baked clams
directions: Saute garlic, onion, parsley, oregano and bread crumbs in oil (2 minutes); mix.
When onion and garlic turn brown (start), remove mixture from pan and mix with clams, juice and salt.
Spoon into shells; sprinkle with cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Yields 12 clams.

title: glazed fruit medley
directions: Mix
ingredients well.
Chill and serve.
May be kept 2 or 3 days in refrigerator.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook meat and chop tomatoes; stir in tomatoes, sauce, sauce mix and V-8 juice.
Bring to a boil, lower heat and simmer for 10 minutes.
Oil lightly a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Place a thin layer of meat sauce, layer of uncooked noodles, cottage cheese and Mozzarella cheese.
Start over, finishing with meat sauce.
Cover with heavy duty aluminum foil.
Seal edges.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let stand 15 minutes before serving.

title: enchiladas
directions: Brown meat in pot with water.
Drain water, mix chili with ground beef; add taco seasoning and 1/2 cup water; mix well.
Warm enchilada sauce in pan.
Warm tortillas according to package directions.
Dip tortillas in enchilada sauce, one by one.
Place 3 tablespoons of meat mixture in each tortilla, roll up; place in casserole dish.
Pour rest of meat mixture over rolled up tortillas.
Spread onion, then cheese on top of mix.
Bake in 375° oven until cheese is melted.

title: bread pudding
directions: Scald milk first, remove from heat and soak bread in milk for 5 minutes.
Add butter, salt and sugar.
Pour slowly over eggs; add vanilla and mix well.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Bake in pan of hot water in moderate oven (350°) until firm, about 50 minutes.
Serve warm with Lemon Sauce or Raisin Sauce.
Add 1/2 cup seeded raisins, if desired.
Serves 8.

title: quick and easy meat loaf
directions: In large bowl, mix thoroughly the ingredients.
In 12 x 8-inch baking pan, firmly shape meat mixture into 8 x 4-inch loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours or until done.

title: chicken divan
directions: Arrange asparagus in 1 1/2-quart shallow baking dish (10 x 6 x 2-inch). Top with chicken.
Blend soup and milk; pour over all. Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes or until hot.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix the above.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.

title: mommie's pound cake
directions: Cream together butter, oleo and cream cheese.
Add sugar slowly, beat well.
Add eggs, 2 at a time.
Beat after each.
Mix in vanilla and salt.
Add in flour slowly while mixing.
Grease and flour a tube pan.
Cut circle of waxed paper and put in bottom of pan.
Pour in cake batter.

title: cheese straws
directions: Mix butter and cheese.
Add flour, pepper and paprika.
Knead well, press onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° until lightly brown. Don't overcook.
Cut into strips while hot.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender.
Drain and place in casserole dish.
Combine butter and flour in saucepan.
Add milk, stirring until almost thickened.
Add cheese, salt and pepper.
Stir until thickened.
Spread water chestnuts and crumbled bacon over broccoli.
Pour sauce over all.
Top with buttered bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: brownies(chewy and fudgy)
directions: Blend Crisco, sugar, eggs and oil.
Mix thoroughly.
Stir in mixed dry ingredients.
Blend in vanilla and nuts.
Spread in a 13 x 9-inch pan or 2 (9-inch) square pans which have been rubbed with Crisco.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.
I dust with powdered sugar.
My daughter puts a chocolate frosting on them.
My 15 grandkids love these!

title: strawberry sponge cake
directions: Cut
cake
into
slices;
line	spring-form pan on both sides. Cut
the rest of the cake into the strawberries.
Stir marshmallows
in the strawberry mixture.
Fold in enough heavy cream
to
set.
Refrigerate the rest for later.
Pour mixture in between
cake
slices;
refrigerate.
When	ready,	put on plate; take spring-form pan off.
Put remaining whipped cream on top of cake.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown beef, garlic, salt, onion and bell pepper.
Cook until all ingredients are blended.
Place Doritos on bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Pour soup mixture over Doritos.
Layer with meat.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.
Great for church-family dinners!

title: s'more cookie bars
directions: Cream margarine or butter and sugar until light and fluffy. Beat in egg and vanilla.
Combine flour, graham cracker crumbs, baking powder and salt.
Add to creamed mixture.
Spread half of dough in bottom of greased 8-inch square baking pan.
Arrange candy bars over dough, breaking as needed to fit.
Spread with Marshmallow Creme.
Scatter bits of remaining dough over Marshmallow Creme and carefully spread to form layer.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until done.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: plum cake
directions: Mix and bake at 350° or 375° from 45 to 65 minutes.

title: old fashioned meat loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Soak bread in milk until saturated.
Place remaining ingredients in a mixing bowl.
Break the bread up into bits; add with milk to mixing bowl.
Thoroughly combine all ingredients; shape into an oval loaf.
Place in a lightly greased loaf pan or in the center of an ovenproof pan.
Bake for 1 hour, pouring off the fat as it accumulates in the pan.
Let cool for at least 10 minutes before slicing.

title: plum cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in a greased and floured Bundt pan at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool slightly in pan and remove.
After cooling, glaze.

title: quickie potatoes
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients in a large bowl.
Pour in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Top with cereal, then pour over melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until bubbly in center.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: salad dressing
directions: Combine sugar, mustard, salt and 1/2 of vinegar.
Heat well. Add oil gradually.
While heating, a thick emulsion will form. Add remaining vinegar and celery seed.

title: dinosaur punch
directions: In a large nonmetallic pitcher, combine first 3 ingredients. Blend well.
If desired, stir in a few drops of green food coloring.
Just before serving, add 1 liter bottle (4 cups) chilled ginger ale; stir gently to blend.
Serve over ice.
Makes 14 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: spinach fettucine
directions: Cook fettucine and chopped fresh spinach together in boiling water for 10 minutes.
Drain and put in serving bowl.
Stir in garlic salt, heavy cream and grated Parmesan cheese.

title: old fashioned gingerbread
directions: Mix and beat well. Cook in an 8 x 10-inch pan. Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Serve warm with whipped cream.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix flour, sugar and milk.
Melt margarine in oblong casserole dish.
Add batter, then pour the can of peaches (with juice).
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: homemade bread
directions: Let rise in greased loaf pan 45 minutes, then bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Makes 2 large loaves.
Grease loaf pans and bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: lemon bread
directions: Combine sugar, salt, flour and yeast.
Head milk, butter and water until very warm.
Pour into flour mixture and beat; add eggs, lemon juice and the grated rind.
Let rise.
Turn on floured board.
Knead.
Place in greased and floured loaf pans.
Let rise again.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes; let cool.
Put topping of powdered sugar, butter and lemon extract.

title: green rice casserole
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Cook broccoli until tender.
Mix with remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter swirl candy
directions: Mix all ingredients, except peanut butter, into a well combined mixture.
Roll out on wax paper, using some sugar to keep from sticking.
Spread peanut butter over dough.
Roll up in jellyroll fashion.
Let sit in refrigerator 3 hours.
Cut into 1/4-inch slices.

title: irish stew
directions: Brown
beef
in
cooking oil.
Add beef broth bouillon. Cook on low about 1 hour.
Add carrots and potatoes and about 2
cups water.
Cook on low another hour.
Add cream of mushroom soup. Simmer 30 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: zippy hot appetizers
directions: Mix and boil brown sugar, salt, cornstarch, vinegar, pineapple juice and water for 5 minutes.
Add pineapple chunks, green pepper and cherries.
